{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784691892255,"sessionID":"ses_07813ae6bffeXSfNUcMKmjadEz","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_QWBhVrN61XyBdp7y2lW6TZve","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/README.md","offset":1,"limit":1600},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"runtime/ Scripts\"\n3: description: \"CLI entry points for deep-loop runtime operations: convergence detection, graph upsert, query, status, fan-out, and loop locking.\"\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # runtime/ Scripts\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n11: \n12: CLI invocation surface for deep-loop runtime operations. Consumed by active `/deep:*` workflows under `.opencode/commands/deep`, including research, review, ai-council, and the four improvement commands. Each script is a thin CommonJS wrapper around the domain library at `../lib/`. The deprecated standalone context loop no longer consumes fan-out; legacy context parsing remains only where a script explicitly documents historical artifact compatibility.\n13: \n14: ## 2. SCRIPTS\n15: \n16: | File | Purpose |\n17: |------|---------|\n18: | `convergence.cjs` | Computes typed graph convergence decisions for research, review, council, and legacy context artifacts |\n19: | `query.cjs` | Queries coverage gaps, unverified claims, contradictions, council graph state, and related graph state |\n20: | `status.cjs` | Reports session-scoped graph health and stored row counts |\n21: | `upsert.cjs` | Stores graph nodes, edges, and iteration events for research, review, council, and legacy context artifacts |\n22: | `fanout-run.cjs` | Runs parallel research or review lineages through headless CLI subprocesses. Deprecated context fan-out is rejected before dispatch. On `SIGINT`/`SIGTERM` it flushes a partial summary marked `stopped:true` instead of dying silently, and treats an empty / no-new-findings tick as valid convergence rather than failure |\n23: | `fanout-pool.cjs` | Provides the concurrency-capped worker pool and status ledger for fan-out lineages. Pool events and the final summary carry read-side `lag` / `pending` / `failed` gauges plus an `oldest_pending_lag_ms` heartbeat (it does not duplicate the upstream failure classification). The lag ceiling is a true stall detector measuring time since the pool last settled while work is still queued, not queue backpressure, so it no longer false-fires on every pool wider than the concurrency cap |\n24: | `fanout-salvage.cjs` | Recovers missing iteration artifacts from captured subprocess stdout |\n25: | `fanout-merge.cjs` | Merges research or review fan-out lineage outputs into consolidated artifacts, applying a deterministic content-derived total-order sort (on top of id-or-title dedup and, when `SPECKIT_FANOUT_NEAR_DUP_DEDUP` is enabled, a title-aware Jaccard near-dup gate that treats same-body findings with distinct titles as distinct) so merged findings order reproducibly across runs. `--loop-type context` is accepted but currently uses research registry and state filenames, so it is not a correct context-output merger |\n26: | `loop-lock.cjs` | CLI adapter for shared loop-lock acquire, heartbeat, stale reclaim, and release operations |\n27: \n28: ## 3. INTERNAL LIBRARY\n29: \n30: `scripts/lib/cli-guards.cjs` - CLI-specific guards for input validation, error formatting, signal handling, and writer-lock coordination. Kept separate from top-level `lib/` because it serves CLI infrastructure, not domain logic.\n31: \n32: ## 4. USAGE\n33: \n34: ```bash\n35: node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/<script-name>.cjs <args>\n36: ```\n37: \n38: ## 5. RELATED RESOURCES\n39: \n40: - Parent SKILL.md: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/SKILL.md`\n41: - Domain library: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/`\n42: - Tests: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/tests/`\n\n(End of file - total 42 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"runtime/ Scripts\"\ndescription: \"CLI entry points for deep-loop runtime operations: convergence detection, graph upsert, query, status, fan-out, and loop locking.\"\n---\n\n# runtime/ Scripts\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nCLI invocation surface for deep-loop runtime operations. Consumed by active `/deep:*` workflows under `.opencode/commands/deep`, including research, review, ai-council, and the four improvement commands. Each script is a thin CommonJS wrapper around the domain library at `../lib/`. The deprecated standalone context loop no longer consumes fan-out; legacy context parsing remains only where a script explicitly documents historical artifact compatibility.\n\n## 2. SCRIPTS\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `convergence.cjs` | Computes typed graph convergence decisions for research, review, council, and legacy context artifacts |\n| `query.cjs` | Queries coverage gaps, unverified claims, contradictions, council graph state, and related graph state |\n| `status.cjs` | Reports session-scoped graph health and stored row counts |","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/README.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"runtime/ Scripts\"\ndescription: \"CLI entry points for deep-loop runtime operations: convergence detection, graph upsert, query, status, fan-out, and loop locking.\"\n---\n\n# runtime/ Scripts\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nCLI invocation surface for deep-loop runtime operations. Consumed by active `/deep:*` workflows under `.opencode/commands/deep`, including research, review, ai-council, and the four improvement commands. Each script is a thin CommonJS wrapper around the domain library at `../lib/`. The deprecated standalone context loop no longer consumes fan-out; legacy context parsing remains only where a script explicitly documents historical artifact compatibility.\n\n## 2. SCRIPTS\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `convergence.cjs` | Computes typed graph convergence decisions for research, review, council, and legacy context artifacts |\n| `query.cjs` | Queries coverage gaps, unverified claims, contradictions, council graph state, and related graph state |\n| `status.cjs` | Reports session-scoped graph health and stored row counts |\n| `upsert.cjs` | Stores graph nodes, edges, and iteration events for research, review, council, and legacy context artifacts |\n| `fanout-run.cjs` | Runs parallel research or review lineages through headless CLI subprocesses. Deprecated context fan-out is rejected before dispatch. On `SIGINT`/`SIGTERM` it flushes a partial summary marked `stopped:true` instead of dying silently, and treats an empty / no-new-findings tick as valid convergence rather than failure |\n| `fanout-pool.cjs` | Provides the concurrency-capped worker pool and status ledger for fan-out lineages. Pool events and the final summary carry read-side `lag` / `pending` / `failed` gauges plus an `oldest_pending_lag_ms` heartbeat (it does not duplicate the upstream failure classification). The lag ceiling is a true stall detector measuring time since the pool last settled while work is still queued, not queue backpressure, so it no longer false-fires on every pool wider than the concurrency cap |\n| `fanout-salvage.cjs` | Recovers missing iteration artifacts from captured subprocess stdout |\n| `fanout-merge.cjs` | Merges research or review fan-out lineage outputs into consolidated artifacts, applying a deterministic content-derived total-order sort (on top of id-or-title dedup and, when `SPECKIT_FANOUT_NEAR_DUP_DEDUP` is enabled, a title-aware Jaccard near-dup gate that treats same-body findings with distinct titles as distinct) so merged findings order reproducibly across runs. `--loop-type context` is accepted but currently uses research registry and state filenames, so it is not a correct context-output merger |\n| `loop-lock.cjs` | CLI adapter for shared loop-lock acquire, heartbeat, stale reclaim, and release operations |\n\n## 3. INTERNAL LIBRARY\n\n`scripts/lib/cli-guards.cjs` - CLI-specific guards for input validation, error formatting, signal handling, and writer-lock coordination. Kept separate from top-level `lib/` because it serves CLI infrastructure, not domain logic.\n\n## 4. USAGE\n\n```bash\nnode .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/<script-name>.cjs <args>\n```\n\n## 5. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n- Parent SKILL.md: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/SKILL.md`\n- Domain library: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/`\n- Tests: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/tests/`","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":42,"totalLines":42,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/README.md","time":{"start":1784691892222,"end":1784691892249}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0c2ff4dd619f1f4b016a603cb426e88191a6f0c2372f53adbd"}},"id":"prt_f87ed1ffa001gabuk6SSRNnKrJ","sessionID":"ses_07813ae6bffeXSfNUcMKmjadEz","messageID":"msg_f87ecf9df001hwbObtyOL00KA7"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784691892266,"sessionID":"ses_07813ae6bffeXSfNUcMKmjadEz","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ShLxu8iZz8GPWTimE0ea2miN","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts","offset":1,"limit":1800},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2: // MODULE: Deep-Loop Executor Config\n3: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n4: \n5: import { z } from 'zod';\n6: \n7: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n8: // 1. TYPE DEFINITIONS\n9: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n10: \n11: export const EXECUTOR_KINDS = ['native', 'cli-codex', 'cli-claude-code', 'cli-opencode'] as const;\n12: export type ExecutorKind = typeof EXECUTOR_KINDS[number];\n13: \n14: // Ordered low→high. `ultra` is codex gpt-5.6-sol's top reasoning tier, above `max`.\n15: export const REASONING_EFFORTS = ['none', 'minimal', 'low', 'medium', 'high', 'xhigh', 'max', 'ultra'] as const;\n16: export type ReasoningEffort = typeof REASONING_EFFORTS[number];\n17: \n18: export const SERVICE_TIERS = ['priority', 'standard', 'fast'] as const;\n19: export type ServiceTier = typeof SERVICE_TIERS[number];\n20: \n21: export const WEB_SEARCH_POLICIES = ['inherit', 'disabled', 'cached', 'live'] as const;\n22: export type WebSearchPolicy = typeof WEB_SEARCH_POLICIES[number];\n23: \n24: /** Live-tool policies resolved for one executor invocation. */\n25: export interface LiveToolsConfig {\n26:   readonly webSearch: WebSearchPolicy;\n27: }\n28: \n29: /** Fan-out assignment models accepted by the schema. */\n30: export const FANOUT_ASSIGNMENT_MODELS = ['flat_pool', 'wave'] as const;\n31: \n32: /** Fan-out assignment model selected for a lineage or fan-out block. */\n33: export type FanoutAssignmentModel = typeof FANOUT_ASSIGNMENT_MODELS[number];\n34: \n35: const SANDBOX_MODES = ['read-only', 'workspace-write', 'danger-full-access'] as const;\n36: export type SandboxMode = typeof SANDBOX_MODES[number];\n37: export type ClaudePermissionMode = 'plan' | 'acceptEdits' | 'bypassPermissions';\n38: \n39: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n40: // 2. CONSTANTS\n41: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n42: \n43: export const liveToolsSchema = z.object({\n44:   webSearch: z.enum(WEB_SEARCH_POLICIES).default('inherit'),\n45: }).default({ webSearch: 'inherit' });\n46: \n47: export const executorConfigSchema = z.object({\n48:   kind: z.enum(EXECUTOR_KINDS).default('native'),\n49:   model: z.string().min(1).nullable().default(null),\n50:   configDir: z.string().trim().min(1).nullable().default(null),\n51:   reasoningEffort: z.enum(REASONING_EFFORTS).nullable().default(null),\n52:   serviceTier: z.enum(SERVICE_TIERS).nullable().default(null),\n53:   sandboxMode: z.enum(SANDBOX_MODES).nullable().default(null),\n54:   // Hard ceiling of 1 hour per iteration: bounds a single executor invocation so a\n55:   // runaway per-iteration call cannot by itself consume the whole autonomous lifetime budget.\n56:   timeoutSeconds: z.number().int().positive().max(3600).default(900),\n57:   // Optional fable-5 governor capsule for this executor's prompts. Universal and\n58:   // kind-agnostic on purpose: intentionally absent from EXECUTOR_KIND_FLAG_SUPPORT\n59:   // and the unsupported-field scan, so any executor kind may carry it. null = none.\n60:   governor: z.string().min(1).nullable().default(null),\n61:   liveTools: liveToolsSchema,\n62: });\n63: \n64: export type ExecutorConfig = z.infer<typeof executorConfigSchema>;\n65: \n66: export const EXECUTOR_KIND_FLAG_SUPPORT: Record<ExecutorKind, readonly (keyof ExecutorConfig)[]> = {\n67:   native: ['liveTools'],\n68:   'cli-codex': ['model', 'reasoningEffort', 'serviceTier', 'sandboxMode', 'timeoutSeconds', 'liveTools'],\n69:   'cli-claude-code': ['model', 'configDir', 'reasoningEffort', 'sandboxMode', 'timeoutSeconds', 'liveTools'],\n70:   'cli-opencode': ['model', 'reasoningEffort', 'sandboxMode', 'timeoutSeconds', 'liveTools'],\n71: };\n72: \n73: /** Proven web-search policies for every shipped executor kind. */\n74: export const EXECUTOR_WEB_SEARCH_CAPABILITY_MATRIX = {\n75:   native: {\n76:     inherit: true,\n77:     disabled: false,\n78:     cached: false,\n79:     live: false,\n80:   },\n81:   'cli-codex': {\n82:     inherit: true,\n83:     disabled: true,\n84:     cached: false,\n85:     live: true,\n86:   },\n87:   'cli-claude-code': {\n88:     inherit: true,\n89:     disabled: false,\n90:     cached: false,\n91:     live: false,\n92:   },\n93:   'cli-opencode': {\n94:     inherit: true,\n95:     disabled: false,\n96:     cached: false,\n97:     live: true,\n98:   },\n99: } as const satisfies Record<ExecutorKind, Record<WebSearchPolicy, boolean>>;\n100: \n101: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n102: // 3. DOMAIN ERRORS\n103: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n104: \n105: type ExecutorConfigIssue = {\n106:   path: PropertyKey[];\n107:   message: string;\n108: };\n109: \n110: /** Error thrown when a reserved executor kind is selected before wiring exists. */\n111: export class ExecutorNotWiredError extends Error {\n112:   kind: Extract<ExecutorKind, 'cli-claude-code'>;\n113: \n114:   constructor(kind: Extract<ExecutorKind, 'cli-claude-code'>) {\n115:     super(`Executor kind '${kind}' is reserved in the schema but not yet wired. Awaiting future spec for ${kind} integration.`);\n116:     this.name = 'ExecutorNotWiredError';\n117:     this.kind = kind;\n118:   }\n119: }\n120: \n121: /** Error thrown when executor configuration validation fails. */\n122: export class ExecutorConfigError extends Error {\n123:   issues: ExecutorConfigIssue[];\n124: \n125:   constructor(input: { issues: ExecutorConfigIssue[] }) {\n126:     super(input.issues.map((issue) => `${issue.path.map(String).join('.') || '<root>'}: ${issue.message}`).join('; '));\n127:     this.name = 'ExecutorConfigError';\n128:     this.issues = input.issues;\n129:   }\n130: }\n131: \n132: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n133: // 4. HELPERS\n134: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n135: \n136: function isRecord(value: unknown): value is Record<string, unknown> {\n137:   return value !== null && !Array.isArray(value) && typeof value === 'object';\n138: }\n139: \n140: function normalizeSandboxMode(mode: SandboxMode | null | undefined): SandboxMode {\n141:   return mode ?? 'workspace-write';\n142: }\n143: \n144: function normalizeExecutorConfigInput(raw: unknown): unknown {\n145:   if (!isRecord(raw) || !Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(raw, 'type')) {\n146:     return raw;\n147:   }\n148: \n149:   const legacyKind = raw.type;\n150:   if (typeof legacyKind !== 'string') {\n151:     return raw;\n152:   }\n153: \n154:   if (typeof raw.kind === 'string' && raw.kind !== legacyKind) {\n155:     throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n156:       issues: [{\n157:         path: ['type'],\n158:         message: `deprecated executor field 'type' conflicts with canonical kind '${raw.kind}'`,\n159:       }],\n160:     });\n161:   }\n162: \n163:   console.warn(\"[executor-config] Deprecated executor field 'type' was provided; use 'kind' instead.\");\n164:   const { type: _legacyType, ...rest } = raw;\n165:   return {\n166:     ...rest,\n167:     kind: typeof raw.kind === 'string' ? raw.kind : legacyKind,\n168:   };\n169: }\n170: \n171: function normalizeIssues(error: z.ZodError<ExecutorConfig>): ExecutorConfigIssue[] {\n172:   return error.issues.map((issue) => ({\n173:     path: issue.path,\n174:     message: issue.message,\n175:   }));\n176: }\n177: \n178: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n179: // 5. EXPORTS\n180: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n181: \n182: /**\n183:  * Map a generic sandbox mode to the executor-agnostic CLI sandbox mode.\n184:  *\n185:  * @param mode - Generic sandbox mode or undefined.\n186:  * @returns CLI-compatible sandbox mode.\n187:  */\n188: export function resolveSandboxMode(mode: SandboxMode | null | undefined): SandboxMode {\n189:   return normalizeSandboxMode(mode);\n190: }\n191: \n192: /**\n193:  * Map a generic sandbox mode to the Claude Code permission mode.\n194:  *\n195:  * @param mode - Generic sandbox mode or undefined.\n196:  * @returns Claude-compatible permission mode.\n197:  */\n198: export function resolveClaudePermissionMode(mode: SandboxMode | null | undefined): ClaudePermissionMode {\n199:   switch (normalizeSandboxMode(mode)) {\n200:     case 'read-only':\n201:       return 'plan';\n202:     case 'danger-full-access':\n203:       return 'bypassPermissions';\n204:     default:\n205:       return 'acceptEdits';\n206:   }\n207: }\n208: \n209: /**\n210:  * Parse and validate a raw executor configuration.\n211:  *\n212:  * Normalizes legacy `type` fields, validates against the Zod schema,\n213:  * and enforces executor-kind-specific field support.\n214:  *\n215:  * @param raw - Raw input to parse (JSON-parsed object).\n216:  * @returns Validated ExecutorConfig.\n217:  * @throws {@link ExecutorConfigError} If validation fails.\n218:  */\n219: export function parseExecutorConfig(raw: unknown): ExecutorConfig {\n220:   const parsed = executorConfigSchema.safeParse(normalizeExecutorConfigInput(raw));\n221:   if (!parsed.success) {\n222:     throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n223:       issues: normalizeIssues(parsed.error),\n224:     });\n225:   }\n226: \n227:   const config = parsed.data;\n228:   const supportedFlags = EXECUTOR_KIND_FLAG_SUPPORT[config.kind];\n229:   const unsupportedFields: string[] = [];\n230:   const allOptionalFields: (keyof ExecutorConfig)[] = [\n231:     'model',\n232:     'configDir',\n233:     'reasoningEffort',\n234:     'serviceTier',\n235:     'sandboxMode',\n236:     'timeoutSeconds',\n237:     'liveTools',\n238:   ];\n239: \n240:   for (const field of allOptionalFields) {\n241:     if (!supportedFlags.includes(field) && config[field] !== null && !(field === 'timeoutSeconds' && config[field] === 900)) {\n242:       unsupportedFields.push(field);\n243:     }\n244:   }\n245: \n246:   if (unsupportedFields.length > 0) {\n247:     throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n248:       issues: unsupportedFields.map((field) => ({\n249:         path: [field],\n250:         message: `field '${field}' is not supported by executor kind '${config.kind}'. Supported fields for ${config.kind}: ${\n251:           supportedFlags.length ? supportedFlags.join(', ') : 'none'\n252:         }.`,\n253:       })),\n254:     });\n255:   }\n256: \n257:   return config;\n258: }\n259: \n260: /**\n261:  * Reject an executor policy unless its adapter has a proven implementation.\n262:  *\n263:  * @param config - Validated executor configuration.\n264:  * @param path - Error path prefix for nested fan-out entries.\n265:  * @throws {@link ExecutorConfigError} If the requested policy is unsupported.\n266:  */\n267: export function assertExecutorWebSearchCapability(\n268:   config: ExecutorConfig,\n269:   path: PropertyKey[] = [],\n270: ): void {\n271:   const policy = config.liveTools.webSearch;\n272:   if (EXECUTOR_WEB_SEARCH_CAPABILITY_MATRIX[config.kind][policy]) {\n273:     return;\n274:   }\n275: \n276:   throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n277:     issues: [{\n278:       path: [...path, 'liveTools', 'webSearch'],\n279:       message: `web-search policy '${policy}' is not supported by executor kind '${config.kind}'`,\n280:     }],\n281:   });\n282: }\n283: \n284: /**\n285:  * Resolve an executor configuration by merging CLI and file sources.\n286:  *\n287:  * @param sources - CLI and file partial configs (CLI takes precedence).\n288:  * @returns Validated ExecutorConfig.\n289:  */\n290: export function resolveExecutorConfig(sources: {\n291:   cli?: Partial<ExecutorConfig>;\n292:   file?: Partial<ExecutorConfig>;\n293: }): ExecutorConfig {\n294:   const merged = {\n295:     ...(sources.file ?? {}),\n296:     ...(sources.cli ?? {}),\n297:   };\n298:   return parseExecutorConfig(merged);\n299: }\n300: \n301: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n302: // 6. FAN-OUT CONFIG\n303: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n304: //\n305: // Opt-in layer ABOVE the single-executor path. When a fan-out config is present,\n306: // the loop runs N executor \"lineages\" concurrently (capped), each running the\n307: // existing sequential loop in its own isolated sub-packet. The single-executor\n308: // path (executorConfigSchema / parseExecutorConfig) is untouched and remains the\n309: // default; callers use EITHER a single `executor` OR a `fanout` block, never both.\n310: \n311: const LINEAGE_LABEL_PATTERN = /^[a-z0-9][a-z0-9-]*$/;\n312: const MAX_FANOUT_MODELS = 16;\n313: const MAX_FANOUT_BRANCHES = 16;\n314: const MAX_FANOUT_REPLICAS = 16;\n315: const MAX_EXPANDED_LINEAGES = 256;\n316: \n317: const lineageMetadataShape = {\n318:   iterations: z.number().int().positive().nullable().default(null),\n319:   promptFramework: z.string().min(1).nullable().default(null),\n320:   assignment_model: z.enum(FANOUT_ASSIGNMENT_MODELS).default('flat_pool'),\n321:   depends_on: z.array(z.string().trim().min(1)).default([]),\n322:   touches: z.array(z.string().trim().min(1)).default([]),\n323: };\n324: \n325: /**\n326:  * One fan-out lineage: a single executor config plus fan-out metadata.\n327:  *\n328:  * - `label`: directory-safe id for the lineage's isolated sub-packet.\n329:  * - `count`: number of replicas of THIS config to run (e.g. 5x the same model).\n330:  * - `iterations`: per-lineage max-iterations override; null = packet default.\n331:  * - `promptFramework`: optional per-model prompt framing key (e.g. \"costar\",\n332:  *   \"tidd-ec\") resolved against sk-prompt/prompt-models when a consumer renders the\n333:  *   lineage prompt. null = consumer default. Loop-type-agnostic and optional, so\n334:  *   research/review lineages that omit it are unaffected.\n335:  * - `assignment_model`: defaults to the existing flat pool; `wave` is accepted\n336:  *   only so the runtime guard can reject activation attempts explicitly.\n337:  * - `depends_on` / `touches`: reserved dependency and path-domain metadata for\n338:  *   a future guarded planner; flat-pool execution ignores them after logging.\n339:  */\n340: export const lineageExecutorSchema = executorConfigSchema.extend({\n341:   label: z.string().min(1).regex(LINEAGE_LABEL_PATTERN, {\n342:     message: \"label must match /^[a-z0-9][a-z0-9-]*$/ (lowercase, digits, hyphens; dir-safe)\",\n343:   }),\n344:   count: z.number().int().positive().max(MAX_FANOUT_REPLICAS).default(1),\n345:   ...lineageMetadataShape,\n346: });\n347: \n348: export type LineageExecutor = z.infer<typeof lineageExecutorSchema>;\n349: \n350: export const fanoutModelSchema = executorConfigSchema.extend({\n351:   id: z.string().min(1).regex(LINEAGE_LABEL_PATTERN, {\n352:     message: \"id must match /^[a-z0-9][a-z0-9-]*$/ (lowercase, digits, hyphens; dir-safe)\",\n353:   }),\n354: });\n355: \n356: export const fanoutBranchSchema = z.object({\n357:   id: z.string().min(1).regex(LINEAGE_LABEL_PATTERN, {\n358:     message: \"id must match /^[a-z0-9][a-z0-9-]*$/ (lowercase, digits, hyphens; dir-safe)\",\n359:   }),\n360:   ...lineageMetadataShape,\n361: });\n362: \n363: const fanoutControlShape = {\n364:   assignment_model: z.enum(FANOUT_ASSIGNMENT_MODELS).default('flat_pool'),\n365:   concurrency: z.number().int().positive().max(8).default(2),\n366:   maxRetries: z.number().int().nonnegative().max(5).default(5),\n367:   // Stall detection defaults ON and is non-disableable while running autonomously: a\n368:   // lineage that stops emitting progress is aborted and requeued within the ceiling and\n369:   // fails loud, instead of hanging silently at 0% CPU until the hours-scale subprocess\n370:   // timeout. Capped at 5 minutes; zero (the old opt-out) is now rejected, not accepted.\n371:   lagCeilingMs: z.number().int().positive().max(300000).default(300000),\n372:   progressHeartbeatSeconds: z.number().nonnegative().default(60),\n373: };\n374: \n375: export const legacyFanoutConfigSchema = z.object({\n376:   executors: z.array(lineageExecutorSchema).min(1).max(MAX_FANOUT_BRANCHES),\n377:   models: z.never().optional(),\n378:   branches: z.never().optional(),\n379:   replicas: z.never().optional(),\n380:   ...fanoutControlShape,\n381: });\n382: \n383: export const fanoutManifestSchema = z.object({\n384:   executors: z.never().optional(),\n385:   models: z.array(fanoutModelSchema).min(1).max(MAX_FANOUT_MODELS),\n386:   branches: z.array(fanoutBranchSchema).min(1).max(MAX_FANOUT_BRANCHES),\n387:   replicas: z.number().int().positive().max(MAX_FANOUT_REPLICAS),\n388:   ...fanoutControlShape,\n389: });\n390: \n391: /** Legacy executor lists and Cartesian manifests are intentionally exclusive. */\n392: export const fanoutConfigSchema = z.union([\n393:   legacyFanoutConfigSchema,\n394:   fanoutManifestSchema,\n395: ]);\n396: \n397: export type FanoutManifest = z.infer<typeof fanoutManifestSchema>;\n398: type ParsedFanoutConfig = z.infer<typeof fanoutConfigSchema>;\n399: \n400: /** Normalized fan-out config consumed by the existing scheduler. */\n401: export interface FanoutConfig {\n402:   readonly executors: LineageExecutor[];\n403:   readonly assignment_model: FanoutAssignmentModel;\n404:   readonly concurrency: number;\n405:   readonly maxRetries: number;\n406:   readonly lagCeilingMs: number;\n407:   readonly progressHeartbeatSeconds: number;\n408: }\n409: \n410: function isFanoutManifest(config: ParsedFanoutConfig): config is FanoutManifest {\n411:   return Array.isArray(config.models);\n412: }\n413: \n414: function assertUniqueManifestIds(\n415:   values: readonly { id: string }[],\n416:   field: 'models' | 'branches',\n417: ): void {\n418:   const seen = new Set<string>();\n419:   values.forEach((value, index) => {\n420:     if (seen.has(value.id)) {\n421:       throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n422:         issues: [{ path: [field, index, 'id'], message: `duplicate ${field.slice(0, -1)} id '${value.id}'` }],\n423:       });\n424:     }\n425:     seen.add(value.id);\n426:   });\n427: }\n428: \n429: /**\n430:  * Compile a Cartesian manifest into the scheduler's existing lineage shape.\n431:  *\n432:  * @param manifest - Validated models-by-branches manifest.\n433:  * @returns Deterministically ordered single-replica lineages.\n434:  * @throws {@link ExecutorConfigError} If identifiers collide or exceed the legacy ceiling.\n435:  */\n436: export function compileFanoutManifest(manifest: FanoutManifest): LineageExecutor[] {\n437:   assertUniqueManifestIds(manifest.models, 'models');\n438:   assertUniqueManifestIds(manifest.branches, 'branches');\n439: \n440:   const expandedCount = manifest.models.length * manifest.branches.length * manifest.replicas;\n441:   if (expandedCount > MAX_EXPANDED_LINEAGES) {\n442:     throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n443:       issues: [{\n444:         path: ['replicas'],\n445:         message: `manifest expands to ${expandedCount} lineages; maximum is ${MAX_EXPANDED_LINEAGES}`,\n446:       }],\n447:     });\n448:   }\n449: \n450:   const lineages: LineageExecutor[] = [];\n451:   const seenLabels = new Set<string>();\n452:   for (const modelEntry of manifest.models) {\n453:     const { id: modelId, ...executor } = modelEntry;\n454:     for (const branchEntry of manifest.branches) {\n455:       const { id: branchId, ...branch } = branchEntry;\n456:       for (let replica = 1; replica <= manifest.replicas; replica += 1) {\n457:         const label = `${branchId}-${modelId}-r${replica}`;\n458:         if (seenLabels.has(label)) {\n459:           throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n460:             issues: [{\n461:               path: ['branches'],\n462:               message: `compiled lineage label '${label}' collides; choose unambiguous model and branch ids`,\n463:             }],\n464:           });\n465:         }\n466:         seenLabels.add(label);\n467:         lineages.push({\n468:           ...executor,\n469:           ...branch,\n470:           label,\n471:           count: 1,\n472:         });\n473:       }\n474:     }\n475:   }\n476:   return lineages;\n477: }\n478: \n479: /**\n480:  * Parse and validate a raw fan-out configuration.\n481:  *\n482:  * Each entry's executor subset is routed through {@link parseExecutorConfig} so\n483:  * ALL existing kind/model/flag rules apply per lineage with zero duplication.\n484:  * Labels must be unique and base-label (count>1) expansion must not collide.\n485:  *\n486:  * @param raw - Raw input to parse (JSON-parsed object).\n487:  * @returns Validated FanoutConfig.\n488:  * @throws {@link ExecutorConfigError} If validation fails.\n489:  */\n490: export function parseFanoutConfig(raw: unknown): FanoutConfig {\n491:   const parsed = fanoutConfigSchema.safeParse(raw);\n492:   if (!parsed.success) {\n493:     throw new ExecutorConfigError({ issues: parsed.error.issues.map((issue) => ({ path: issue.path, message: issue.message })) });\n494:   }\n495: \n496:   const parsedConfig = parsed.data;\n497:   const hasManifest = isFanoutManifest(parsedConfig);\n498: \n499:   if (hasManifest) {\n500:     parsedConfig.models.forEach((entry, index) => {\n501:       const { id: _id, ...executorSubset } = entry;\n502:       try {\n503:         parseExecutorConfig(executorSubset);\n504:       } catch (err: unknown) {\n505:         if (err instanceof ExecutorConfigError) {\n506:           throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n507:             issues: err.issues.map((issue) => ({ path: ['models', index, ...issue.path], message: issue.message })),\n508:           });\n509:         }\n510:         throw err;\n511:       }\n512:     });\n513:   }\n514: \n515:   const executors = hasManifest\n516:     ? compileFanoutManifest(parsedConfig)\n517:     : parsedConfig.executors;\n518:   const config: FanoutConfig = {\n519:     executors,\n520:     assignment_model: parsedConfig.assignment_model,\n521:     concurrency: parsedConfig.concurrency,\n522:     maxRetries: parsedConfig.maxRetries,\n523:     lagCeilingMs: parsedConfig.lagCeilingMs,\n524:     progressHeartbeatSeconds: parsedConfig.progressHeartbeatSeconds,\n525:   };\n526: \n527:   // Reuse the canonical single-executor validator per entry (kind/model/flags).\n528:   if (!hasManifest) {\n529:     config.executors.forEach((entry, index) => {\n530:       const {\n531:         label: _label,\n532:         count: _count,\n533:         iterations: _iterations,\n534:         promptFramework: _promptFramework,\n535:         assignment_model: _assignmentModel,\n536:         depends_on: _dependsOn,\n537:         touches: _touches,\n538:         ...executorSubset\n539:       } = entry;\n540:       try {\n541:         parseExecutorConfig(executorSubset);\n542:       } catch (err: unknown) {\n543:         if (err instanceof ExecutorConfigError) {\n544:           throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n545:             issues: err.issues.map((issue) => ({ path: ['executors', index, ...issue.path], message: issue.message })),\n546:           });\n547:         }\n548:         throw err;\n549:       }\n550:     });\n551:   }\n552: \n553:   // Labels must be unique among the declared lineages.\n554:   const seenLabels = new Set<string>();\n555:   config.executors.forEach((entry, index) => {\n556:     if (seenLabels.has(entry.label)) {\n557:       throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n558:         issues: [{ path: ['executors', index, 'label'], message: `duplicate lineage label '${entry.label}'` }],\n559:       });\n560:     }\n561:     seenLabels.add(entry.label);\n562:   });\n563: \n564:   // Expanded labels (count>1 → label-1, label-2, …) must not collide either.\n565:   const expandedLabels = new Set<string>();\n566:   for (const lineage of expandLineages(config)) {\n567:     if (expandedLabels.has(lineage.label)) {\n568:       throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n569:         issues: [{ path: ['executors'], message: `expanded lineage label '${lineage.label}' collides; rename base labels` }],\n570:       });\n571:     }\n572:     expandedLabels.add(lineage.label);\n573:   }\n574: \n575:   return config;\n576: }\n577: \n578: /**\n579:  * Validate every expanded lineage before the scheduler or a subprocess can run.\n580:  *\n581:  * @param lineages - Concrete scheduler inputs after replica expansion.\n582:  * @throws {@link ExecutorConfigError} If any kind-policy combination is unsupported.\n583:  */\n584: export function preflightFanoutCapabilities(lineages: readonly LineageExecutor[]): void {\n585:   lineages.forEach((lineage, index) => {\n586:     assertExecutorWebSearchCapability(lineage, ['lineages', index]);\n587:   });\n588: }\n589: \n590: /**\n591:  * Expand a fan-out config into concrete per-replica lineages.\n592:  *\n593:  * A `count` of 1 keeps the base label; `count > 1` yields `${label}-1` …\n594:  * `${label}-N`. Each expanded lineage carries `count: 1` so downstream\n595:  * consumers see one runnable unit per element.\n596:  *\n597:  * @param config - Validated FanoutConfig.\n598:  * @returns Flat list of single-replica lineages (one runnable unit each).\n599:  */\n600: export function expandLineages(config: FanoutConfig): LineageExecutor[] {\n601:   const lineages: LineageExecutor[] = [];\n602:   for (const entry of config.executors) {\n603:     if (entry.count === 1) {\n604:       lineages.push({ ...entry, count: 1 });\n605:       continue;\n606:     }\n607:     for (let replica = 1; replica <= entry.count; replica += 1) {\n608:       lineages.push({ ...entry, label: `${entry.label}-${replica}`, count: 1 });\n609:     }\n610:   }\n611:   return lineages;\n612: }\n\n(End of file - total 612 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// MODULE: Deep-Loop Executor Config\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nimport { z } from 'zod';\n\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 1. TYPE DEFINITIONS\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nexport const EXECUTOR_KINDS = ['native', 'cli-codex', 'cli-claude-code', 'cli-opencode'] as const;\nexport type ExecutorKind = typeof EXECUTOR_KINDS[number];\n\n// Ordered low→high. `ultra` is codex gpt-5.6-sol's top reasoning tier, above `max`.\nexport const REASONING_EFFORTS = ['none', 'minimal', 'low', 'medium', 'high', 'xhigh', 'max', 'ultra'] as const;\nexport type ReasoningEffort = typeof REASONING_EFFORTS[number];\n\nexport const SERVICE_TIERS = ['priority', 'standard', 'fast'] as const;\nexport type ServiceTier = typeof SERVICE_TIERS[number];\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts","text":"// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// MODULE: Deep-Loop Executor Config\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nimport { z } from 'zod';\n\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 1. TYPE DEFINITIONS\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nexport const EXECUTOR_KINDS = ['native', 'cli-codex', 'cli-claude-code', 'cli-opencode'] as const;\nexport type ExecutorKind = typeof EXECUTOR_KINDS[number];\n\n// Ordered low→high. `ultra` is codex gpt-5.6-sol's top reasoning tier, above `max`.\nexport const REASONING_EFFORTS = ['none', 'minimal', 'low', 'medium', 'high', 'xhigh', 'max', 'ultra'] as const;\nexport type ReasoningEffort = typeof REASONING_EFFORTS[number];\n\nexport const SERVICE_TIERS = ['priority', 'standard', 'fast'] as const;\nexport type ServiceTier = typeof SERVICE_TIERS[number];\n\nexport const WEB_SEARCH_POLICIES = ['inherit', 'disabled', 'cached', 'live'] as const;\nexport type WebSearchPolicy = typeof WEB_SEARCH_POLICIES[number];\n\n/** Live-tool policies resolved for one executor invocation. */\nexport interface LiveToolsConfig {\n  readonly webSearch: WebSearchPolicy;\n}\n\n/** Fan-out assignment models accepted by the schema. */\nexport const FANOUT_ASSIGNMENT_MODELS = ['flat_pool', 'wave'] as const;\n\n/** Fan-out assignment model selected for a lineage or fan-out block. */\nexport type FanoutAssignmentModel = typeof FANOUT_ASSIGNMENT_MODELS[number];\n\nconst SANDBOX_MODES = ['read-only', 'workspace-write', 'danger-full-access'] as const;\nexport type SandboxMode = typeof SANDBOX_MODES[number];\nexport type ClaudePermissionMode = 'plan' | 'acceptEdits' | 'bypassPermissions';\n\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 2. CONSTANTS\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nexport const liveToolsSchema = z.object({\n  webSearch: z.enum(WEB_SEARCH_POLICIES).default('inherit'),\n}).default({ webSearch: 'inherit' });\n\nexport const executorConfigSchema = z.object({\n  kind: z.enum(EXECUTOR_KINDS).default('native'),\n  model: z.string().min(1).nullable().default(null),\n  configDir: z.string().trim().min(1).nullable().default(null),\n  reasoningEffort: z.enum(REASONING_EFFORTS).nullable().default(null),\n  serviceTier: z.enum(SERVICE_TIERS).nullable().default(null),\n  sandboxMode: z.enum(SANDBOX_MODES).nullable().default(null),\n  // Hard ceiling of 1 hour per iteration: bounds a single executor invocation so a\n  // runaway per-iteration call cannot by itself consume the whole autonomous lifetime budget.\n  timeoutSeconds: z.number().int().positive().max(3600).default(900),\n  // Optional fable-5 governor capsule for this executor's prompts. Universal and\n  // kind-agnostic on purpose: intentionally absent from EXECUTOR_KIND_FLAG_SUPPORT\n  // and the unsupported-field scan, so any executor kind may carry it. null = none.\n  governor: z.string().min(1).nullable().default(null),\n  liveTools: liveToolsSchema,\n});\n\nexport type ExecutorConfig = z.infer<typeof executorConfigSchema>;\n\nexport const EXECUTOR_KIND_FLAG_SUPPORT: Record<ExecutorKind, readonly (keyof ExecutorConfig)[]> = {\n  native: ['liveTools'],\n  'cli-codex': ['model', 'reasoningEffort', 'serviceTier', 'sandboxMode', 'timeoutSeconds', 'liveTools'],\n  'cli-claude-code': ['model', 'configDir', 'reasoningEffort', 'sandboxMode', 'timeoutSeconds', 'liveTools'],\n  'cli-opencode': ['model', 'reasoningEffort', 'sandboxMode', 'timeoutSeconds', 'liveTools'],\n};\n\n/** Proven web-search policies for every shipped executor kind. */\nexport const EXECUTOR_WEB_SEARCH_CAPABILITY_MATRIX = {\n  native: {\n    inherit: true,\n    disabled: false,\n    cached: false,\n    live: false,\n  },\n  'cli-codex': {\n    inherit: true,\n    disabled: true,\n    cached: false,\n    live: true,\n  },\n  'cli-claude-code': {\n    inherit: true,\n    disabled: false,\n    cached: false,\n    live: false,\n  },\n  'cli-opencode': {\n    inherit: true,\n    disabled: false,\n    cached: false,\n    live: true,\n  },\n} as const satisfies Record<ExecutorKind, Record<WebSearchPolicy, boolean>>;\n\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 3. DOMAIN ERRORS\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\ntype ExecutorConfigIssue = {\n  path: PropertyKey[];\n  message: string;\n};\n\n/** Error thrown when a reserved executor kind is selected before wiring exists. */\nexport class ExecutorNotWiredError extends Error {\n  kind: Extract<ExecutorKind, 'cli-claude-code'>;\n\n  constructor(kind: Extract<ExecutorKind, 'cli-claude-code'>) {\n    super(`Executor kind '${kind}' is reserved in the schema but not yet wired. Awaiting future spec for ${kind} integration.`);\n    this.name = 'ExecutorNotWiredError';\n    this.kind = kind;\n  }\n}\n\n/** Error thrown when executor configuration validation fails. */\nexport class ExecutorConfigError extends Error {\n  issues: ExecutorConfigIssue[];\n\n  constructor(input: { issues: ExecutorConfigIssue[] }) {\n    super(input.issues.map((issue) => `${issue.path.map(String).join('.') || '<root>'}: ${issue.message}`).join('; '));\n    this.name = 'ExecutorConfigError';\n    this.issues = input.issues;\n  }\n}\n\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 4. HELPERS\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nfunction isRecord(value: unknown): value is Record<string, unknown> {\n  return value !== null && !Array.isArray(value) && typeof value === 'object';\n}\n\nfunction normalizeSandboxMode(mode: SandboxMode | null | undefined): SandboxMode {\n  return mode ?? 'workspace-write';\n}\n\nfunction normalizeExecutorConfigInput(raw: unknown): unknown {\n  if (!isRecord(raw) || !Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(raw, 'type')) {\n    return raw;\n  }\n\n  const legacyKind = raw.type;\n  if (typeof legacyKind !== 'string') {\n    return raw;\n  }\n\n  if (typeof raw.kind === 'string' && raw.kind !== legacyKind) {\n    throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n      issues: [{\n        path: ['type'],\n        message: `deprecated executor field 'type' conflicts with canonical kind '${raw.kind}'`,\n      }],\n    });\n  }\n\n  console.warn(\"[executor-config] Deprecated executor field 'type' was provided; use 'kind' instead.\");\n  const { type: _legacyType, ...rest } = raw;\n  return {\n    ...rest,\n    kind: typeof raw.kind === 'string' ? raw.kind : legacyKind,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction normalizeIssues(error: z.ZodError<ExecutorConfig>): ExecutorConfigIssue[] {\n  return error.issues.map((issue) => ({\n    path: issue.path,\n    message: issue.message,\n  }));\n}\n\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 5. EXPORTS\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/**\n * Map a generic sandbox mode to the executor-agnostic CLI sandbox mode.\n *\n * @param mode - Generic sandbox mode or undefined.\n * @returns CLI-compatible sandbox mode.\n */\nexport function resolveSandboxMode(mode: SandboxMode | null | undefined): SandboxMode {\n  return normalizeSandboxMode(mode);\n}\n\n/**\n * Map a generic sandbox mode to the Claude Code permission mode.\n *\n * @param mode - Generic sandbox mode or undefined.\n * @returns Claude-compatible permission mode.\n */\nexport function resolveClaudePermissionMode(mode: SandboxMode | null | undefined): ClaudePermissionMode {\n  switch (normalizeSandboxMode(mode)) {\n    case 'read-only':\n      return 'plan';\n    case 'danger-full-access':\n      return 'bypassPermissions';\n    default:\n      return 'acceptEdits';\n  }\n}\n\n/**\n * Parse and validate a raw executor configuration.\n *\n * Normalizes legacy `type` fields, validates against the Zod schema,\n * and enforces executor-kind-specific field support.\n *\n * @param raw - Raw input to parse (JSON-parsed object).\n * @returns Validated ExecutorConfig.\n * @throws {@link ExecutorConfigError} If validation fails.\n */\nexport function parseExecutorConfig(raw: unknown): ExecutorConfig {\n  const parsed = executorConfigSchema.safeParse(normalizeExecutorConfigInput(raw));\n  if (!parsed.success) {\n    throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n      issues: normalizeIssues(parsed.error),\n    });\n  }\n\n  const config = parsed.data;\n  const supportedFlags = EXECUTOR_KIND_FLAG_SUPPORT[config.kind];\n  const unsupportedFields: string[] = [];\n  const allOptionalFields: (keyof ExecutorConfig)[] = [\n    'model',\n    'configDir',\n    'reasoningEffort',\n    'serviceTier',\n    'sandboxMode',\n    'timeoutSeconds',\n    'liveTools',\n  ];\n\n  for (const field of allOptionalFields) {\n    if (!supportedFlags.includes(field) && config[field] !== null && !(field === 'timeoutSeconds' && config[field] === 900)) {\n      unsupportedFields.push(field);\n    }\n  }\n\n  if (unsupportedFields.length > 0) {\n    throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n      issues: unsupportedFields.map((field) => ({\n        path: [field],\n        message: `field '${field}' is not supported by executor kind '${config.kind}'. Supported fields for ${config.kind}: ${\n          supportedFlags.length ? supportedFlags.join(', ') : 'none'\n        }.`,\n      })),\n    });\n  }\n\n  return config;\n}\n\n/**\n * Reject an executor policy unless its adapter has a proven implementation.\n *\n * @param config - Validated executor configuration.\n * @param path - Error path prefix for nested fan-out entries.\n * @throws {@link ExecutorConfigError} If the requested policy is unsupported.\n */\nexport function assertExecutorWebSearchCapability(\n  config: ExecutorConfig,\n  path: PropertyKey[] = [],\n): void {\n  const policy = config.liveTools.webSearch;\n  if (EXECUTOR_WEB_SEARCH_CAPABILITY_MATRIX[config.kind][policy]) {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n    issues: [{\n      path: [...path, 'liveTools', 'webSearch'],\n      message: `web-search policy '${policy}' is not supported by executor kind '${config.kind}'`,\n    }],\n  });\n}\n\n/**\n * Resolve an executor configuration by merging CLI and file sources.\n *\n * @param sources - CLI and file partial configs (CLI takes precedence).\n * @returns Validated ExecutorConfig.\n */\nexport function resolveExecutorConfig(sources: {\n  cli?: Partial<ExecutorConfig>;\n  file?: Partial<ExecutorConfig>;\n}): ExecutorConfig {\n  const merged = {\n    ...(sources.file ?? {}),\n    ...(sources.cli ?? {}),\n  };\n  return parseExecutorConfig(merged);\n}\n\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 6. FAN-OUT CONFIG\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n//\n// Opt-in layer ABOVE the single-executor path. When a fan-out config is present,\n// the loop runs N executor \"lineages\" concurrently (capped), each running the\n// existing sequential loop in its own isolated sub-packet. The single-executor\n// path (executorConfigSchema / parseExecutorConfig) is untouched and remains the\n// default; callers use EITHER a single `executor` OR a `fanout` block, never both.\n\nconst LINEAGE_LABEL_PATTERN = /^[a-z0-9][a-z0-9-]*$/;\nconst MAX_FANOUT_MODELS = 16;\nconst MAX_FANOUT_BRANCHES = 16;\nconst MAX_FANOUT_REPLICAS = 16;\nconst MAX_EXPANDED_LINEAGES = 256;\n\nconst lineageMetadataShape = {\n  iterations: z.number().int().positive().nullable().default(null),\n  promptFramework: z.string().min(1).nullable().default(null),\n  assignment_model: z.enum(FANOUT_ASSIGNMENT_MODELS).default('flat_pool'),\n  depends_on: z.array(z.string().trim().min(1)).default([]),\n  touches: z.array(z.string().trim().min(1)).default([]),\n};\n\n/**\n * One fan-out lineage: a single executor config plus fan-out metadata.\n *\n * - `label`: directory-safe id for the lineage's isolated sub-packet.\n * - `count`: number of replicas of THIS config to run (e.g. 5x the same model).\n * - `iterations`: per-lineage max-iterations override; null = packet default.\n * - `promptFramework`: optional per-model prompt framing key (e.g. \"costar\",\n *   \"tidd-ec\") resolved against sk-prompt/prompt-models when a consumer renders the\n *   lineage prompt. null = consumer default. Loop-type-agnostic and optional, so\n *   research/review lineages that omit it are unaffected.\n * - `assignment_model`: defaults to the existing flat pool; `wave` is accepted\n *   only so the runtime guard can reject activation attempts explicitly.\n * - `depends_on` / `touches`: reserved dependency and path-domain metadata for\n *   a future guarded planner; flat-pool execution ignores them after logging.\n */\nexport const lineageExecutorSchema = executorConfigSchema.extend({\n  label: z.string().min(1).regex(LINEAGE_LABEL_PATTERN, {\n    message: \"label must match /^[a-z0-9][a-z0-9-]*$/ (lowercase, digits, hyphens; dir-safe)\",\n  }),\n  count: z.number().int().positive().max(MAX_FANOUT_REPLICAS).default(1),\n  ...lineageMetadataShape,\n});\n\nexport type LineageExecutor = z.infer<typeof lineageExecutorSchema>;\n\nexport const fanoutModelSchema = executorConfigSchema.extend({\n  id: z.string().min(1).regex(LINEAGE_LABEL_PATTERN, {\n    message: \"id must match /^[a-z0-9][a-z0-9-]*$/ (lowercase, digits, hyphens; dir-safe)\",\n  }),\n});\n\nexport const fanoutBranchSchema = z.object({\n  id: z.string().min(1).regex(LINEAGE_LABEL_PATTERN, {\n    message: \"id must match /^[a-z0-9][a-z0-9-]*$/ (lowercase, digits, hyphens; dir-safe)\",\n  }),\n  ...lineageMetadataShape,\n});\n\nconst fanoutControlShape = {\n  assignment_model: z.enum(FANOUT_ASSIGNMENT_MODELS).default('flat_pool'),\n  concurrency: z.number().int().positive().max(8).default(2),\n  maxRetries: z.number().int().nonnegative().max(5).default(5),\n  // Stall detection defaults ON and is non-disableable while running autonomously: a\n  // lineage that stops emitting progress is aborted and requeued within the ceiling and\n  // fails loud, instead of hanging silently at 0% CPU until the hours-scale subprocess\n  // timeout. Capped at 5 minutes; zero (the old opt-out) is now rejected, not accepted.\n  lagCeilingMs: z.number().int().positive().max(300000).default(300000),\n  progressHeartbeatSeconds: z.number().nonnegative().default(60),\n};\n\nexport const legacyFanoutConfigSchema = z.object({\n  executors: z.array(lineageExecutorSchema).min(1).max(MAX_FANOUT_BRANCHES),\n  models: z.never().optional(),\n  branches: z.never().optional(),\n  replicas: z.never().optional(),\n  ...fanoutControlShape,\n});\n\nexport const fanoutManifestSchema = z.object({\n  executors: z.never().optional(),\n  models: z.array(fanoutModelSchema).min(1).max(MAX_FANOUT_MODELS),\n  branches: z.array(fanoutBranchSchema).min(1).max(MAX_FANOUT_BRANCHES),\n  replicas: z.number().int().positive().max(MAX_FANOUT_REPLICAS),\n  ...fanoutControlShape,\n});\n\n/** Legacy executor lists and Cartesian manifests are intentionally exclusive. */\nexport const fanoutConfigSchema = z.union([\n  legacyFanoutConfigSchema,\n  fanoutManifestSchema,\n]);\n\nexport type FanoutManifest = z.infer<typeof fanoutManifestSchema>;\ntype ParsedFanoutConfig = z.infer<typeof fanoutConfigSchema>;\n\n/** Normalized fan-out config consumed by the existing scheduler. */\nexport interface FanoutConfig {\n  readonly executors: LineageExecutor[];\n  readonly assignment_model: FanoutAssignmentModel;\n  readonly concurrency: number;\n  readonly maxRetries: number;\n  readonly lagCeilingMs: number;\n  readonly progressHeartbeatSeconds: number;\n}\n\nfunction isFanoutManifest(config: ParsedFanoutConfig): config is FanoutManifest {\n  return Array.isArray(config.models);\n}\n\nfunction assertUniqueManifestIds(\n  values: readonly { id: string }[],\n  field: 'models' | 'branches',\n): void {\n  const seen = new Set<string>();\n  values.forEach((value, index) => {\n    if (seen.has(value.id)) {\n      throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n        issues: [{ path: [field, index, 'id'], message: `duplicate ${field.slice(0, -1)} id '${value.id}'` }],\n      });\n    }\n    seen.add(value.id);\n  });\n}\n\n/**\n * Compile a Cartesian manifest into the scheduler's existing lineage shape.\n *\n * @param manifest - Validated models-by-branches manifest.\n * @returns Deterministically ordered single-replica lineages.\n * @throws {@link ExecutorConfigError} If identifiers collide or exceed the legacy ceiling.\n */\nexport function compileFanoutManifest(manifest: FanoutManifest): LineageExecutor[] {\n  assertUniqueManifestIds(manifest.models, 'models');\n  assertUniqueManifestIds(manifest.branches, 'branches');\n\n  const expandedCount = manifest.models.length * manifest.branches.length * manifest.replicas;\n  if (expandedCount > MAX_EXPANDED_LINEAGES) {\n    throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n      issues: [{\n        path: ['replicas'],\n        message: `manifest expands to ${expandedCount} lineages; maximum is ${MAX_EXPANDED_LINEAGES}`,\n      }],\n    });\n  }\n\n  const lineages: LineageExecutor[] = [];\n  const seenLabels = new Set<string>();\n  for (const modelEntry of manifest.models) {\n    const { id: modelId, ...executor } = modelEntry;\n    for (const branchEntry of manifest.branches) {\n      const { id: branchId, ...branch } = branchEntry;\n      for (let replica = 1; replica <= manifest.replicas; replica += 1) {\n        const label = `${branchId}-${modelId}-r${replica}`;\n        if (seenLabels.has(label)) {\n          throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n            issues: [{\n              path: ['branches'],\n              message: `compiled lineage label '${label}' collides; choose unambiguous model and branch ids`,\n            }],\n          });\n        }\n        seenLabels.add(label);\n        lineages.push({\n          ...executor,\n          ...branch,\n          label,\n          count: 1,\n        });\n      }\n    }\n  }\n  return lineages;\n}\n\n/**\n * Parse and validate a raw fan-out configuration.\n *\n * Each entry's executor subset is routed through {@link parseExecutorConfig} so\n * ALL existing kind/model/flag rules apply per lineage with zero duplication.\n * Labels must be unique and base-label (count>1) expansion must not collide.\n *\n * @param raw - Raw input to parse (JSON-parsed object).\n * @returns Validated FanoutConfig.\n * @throws {@link ExecutorConfigError} If validation fails.\n */\nexport function parseFanoutConfig(raw: unknown): FanoutConfig {\n  const parsed = fanoutConfigSchema.safeParse(raw);\n  if (!parsed.success) {\n    throw new ExecutorConfigError({ issues: parsed.error.issues.map((issue) => ({ path: issue.path, message: issue.message })) });\n  }\n\n  const parsedConfig = parsed.data;\n  const hasManifest = isFanoutManifest(parsedConfig);\n\n  if (hasManifest) {\n    parsedConfig.models.forEach((entry, index) => {\n      const { id: _id, ...executorSubset } = entry;\n      try {\n        parseExecutorConfig(executorSubset);\n      } catch (err: unknown) {\n        if (err instanceof ExecutorConfigError) {\n          throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n            issues: err.issues.map((issue) => ({ path: ['models', index, ...issue.path], message: issue.message })),\n          });\n        }\n        throw err;\n      }\n    });\n  }\n\n  const executors = hasManifest\n    ? compileFanoutManifest(parsedConfig)\n    : parsedConfig.executors;\n  const config: FanoutConfig = {\n    executors,\n    assignment_model: parsedConfig.assignment_model,\n    concurrency: parsedConfig.concurrency,\n    maxRetries: parsedConfig.maxRetries,\n    lagCeilingMs: parsedConfig.lagCeilingMs,\n    progressHeartbeatSeconds: parsedConfig.progressHeartbeatSeconds,\n  };\n\n  // Reuse the canonical single-executor validator per entry (kind/model/flags).\n  if (!hasManifest) {\n    config.executors.forEach((entry, index) => {\n      const {\n        label: _label,\n        count: _count,\n        iterations: _iterations,\n        promptFramework: _promptFramework,\n        assignment_model: _assignmentModel,\n        depends_on: _dependsOn,\n        touches: _touches,\n        ...executorSubset\n      } = entry;\n      try {\n        parseExecutorConfig(executorSubset);\n      } catch (err: unknown) {\n        if (err instanceof ExecutorConfigError) {\n          throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n            issues: err.issues.map((issue) => ({ path: ['executors', index, ...issue.path], message: issue.message })),\n          });\n        }\n        throw err;\n      }\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Labels must be unique among the declared lineages.\n  const seenLabels = new Set<string>();\n  config.executors.forEach((entry, index) => {\n    if (seenLabels.has(entry.label)) {\n      throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n        issues: [{ path: ['executors', index, 'label'], message: `duplicate lineage label '${entry.label}'` }],\n      });\n    }\n    seenLabels.add(entry.label);\n  });\n\n  // Expanded labels (count>1 → label-1, label-2, …) must not collide either.\n  const expandedLabels = new Set<string>();\n  for (const lineage of expandLineages(config)) {\n    if (expandedLabels.has(lineage.label)) {\n      throw new ExecutorConfigError({\n        issues: [{ path: ['executors'], message: `expanded lineage label '${lineage.label}' collides; rename base labels` }],\n      });\n    }\n    expandedLabels.add(lineage.label);\n  }\n\n  return config;\n}\n\n/**\n * Validate every expanded lineage before the scheduler or a subprocess can run.\n *\n * @param lineages - Concrete scheduler inputs after replica expansion.\n * @throws {@link ExecutorConfigError} If any kind-policy combination is unsupported.\n */\nexport function preflightFanoutCapabilities(lineages: readonly LineageExecutor[]): void {\n  lineages.forEach((lineage, index) => {\n    assertExecutorWebSearchCapability(lineage, ['lineages', index]);\n  });\n}\n\n/**\n * Expand a fan-out config into concrete per-replica lineages.\n *\n * A `count` of 1 keeps the base label; `count > 1` yields `${label}-1` …\n * `${label}-N`. Each expanded lineage carries `count: 1` so downstream\n * consumers see one runnable unit per element.\n *\n * @param config - Validated FanoutConfig.\n * @returns Flat list of single-replica lineages (one runnable unit each).\n */\nexport function expandLineages(config: FanoutConfig): LineageExecutor[] {\n  const lineages: LineageExecutor[] = [];\n  for (const entry of config.executors) {\n    if (entry.count === 1) {\n      lineages.push({ ...entry, count: 1 });\n      continue;\n    }\n    for (let replica = 1; replica <= entry.count; replica += 1) {\n      lineages.push({ ...entry, label: `${entry.label}-${replica}`, count: 1 });\n    }\n  }\n  return lineages;\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":612,"totalLines":612,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts","time":{"start":1784691892227,"end":1784691892256}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0c2ff4dd619f1f4b016a603cb426f081918be7a8ab4c1c31ff"}},"id":"prt_f87ed2001001N59lMTDfZ0KSMb","sessionID":"ses_07813ae6bffeXSfNUcMKmjadEz","messageID":"msg_f87ecf9df001hwbObtyOL00KA7"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784691892266,"sessionID":"ses_07813ae6bffeXSfNUcMKmjadEz","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_U0ciH0I4exp62ERrUGroWhic","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs","offset":1,"limit":1800},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: // ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n2: // ║ Deep-Loop Runtime — Fan-Out Cross-Lineage Merge                          ║\n3: // ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n4: // ║ Input:  CLI args (--loop-type, --artifact-dir).                          ║\n5: // ║ Output: JSON to stdout.                                                  ║\n6: // ║ Exit:   0=ok, 1=script error, 3=input validation error.                 ║\n7: // ║                                                                          ║\n8: // ║ Reads every {artifact-dir}/lineages/{label}/ sub-packet and produces:   ║\n9: // ║   research: deduplicated deep-research-findings-registry.json +          ║\n10: // ║             fanout-attribution.md                                        ║\n11: // ║   review:   severity-rollup deep-review-findings-registry.json           ║\n12: // ║             (strongest-restriction: any lineage P0 → merged FAIL) +     ║\n13: // ║             fanout-attribution.md                                        ║\n14: // ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n15: \n16: 'use strict';\n17: \n18: const crypto = require('node:crypto');\n19: const fs = require('node:fs');\n20: const path = require('node:path');\n21: const { spawnSync } = require('node:child_process');\n22: \n23: const SEVERITY_RANK = { P0: 3, P1: 2, P2: 1 };\n24: \n25: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n26: // 1. TSX BOOTSTRAP\n27: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n28: \n29: const TSX_LOADER = require.resolve('tsx');\n30: \n31: // The merged registry and attribution share the runtime's atomic-state helpers,\n32: // which are TypeScript ESM. Re-exec once under the tsx loader so the dynamic\n33: // import below resolves them; mirrors convergence.cjs. Only the CLI entrypoint\n34: // re-execs — module consumers (unit tests) import the pure helpers directly.\n35: if (require.main === module && process.env.DEEP_LOOP_TSX_LOADED !== '1') {\n36:   const child = spawnSync(\n37:     process.execPath,\n38:     ['--import', TSX_LOADER, __filename, ...process.argv.slice(2)],\n39:     {\n40:       cwd: process.cwd(),\n41:       env: { ...process.env, DEEP_LOOP_TSX_LOADED: '1' },\n42:       encoding: 'utf8',\n43:     },\n44:   );\n45:   if (child.stdout) process.stdout.write(child.stdout);\n46:   if (child.stderr) process.stderr.write(child.stderr);\n47:   process.exit(child.status === null ? 1 : child.status);\n48: }\n49: \n50: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n51: // 2. HELPERS\n52: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n53: \n54: function inputError(message) {\n55:   const err = new Error(message);\n56:   err.code = 'INPUT_VALIDATION';\n57:   return err;\n58: }\n59: \n60: function jsonOut(payload) {\n61:   process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(payload)}\\n`);\n62: }\n63: \n64: function parseArgs(argv = process.argv.slice(2)) {\n65:   const args = {};\n66:   for (let i = 0; i < argv.length; i += 1) {\n67:     const token = argv[i];\n68:     if (!token.startsWith('--')) {\n69:       throw inputError(`Unexpected positional argument: ${token}`);\n70:     }\n71:     const key = token.slice(2).replace(/-([a-z])/g, (_, c) => c.toUpperCase());\n72:     const next = argv[i + 1];\n73:     if (next === undefined || next.startsWith('--')) {\n74:       args[key] = true;\n75:     } else {\n76:       args[key] = next;\n77:       i += 1;\n78:     }\n79:   }\n80:   return args;\n81: }\n82: \n83: function ensureString(args, key) {\n84:   if (!args[key] || typeof args[key] !== 'string') {\n85:     throw inputError(`${key} is required`);\n86:   }\n87:   return args[key];\n88: }\n89: \n90: function tryReadJson(filePath) {\n91:   if (!fs.existsSync(filePath)) return null;\n92:   try {\n93:     return JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8'));\n94:   } catch {\n95:     return null;\n96:   }\n97: }\n98: \n99: function readStateLog(stateLogPath) {\n100:   if (!fs.existsSync(stateLogPath)) return [];\n101:   const lines = fs.readFileSync(stateLogPath, 'utf8').trim().split('\\n').filter(Boolean);\n102:   return lines.flatMap((line) => {\n103:     try {\n104:       return [JSON.parse(line)];\n105:     } catch {\n106:       return [];\n107:     }\n108:   });\n109: }\n110: \n111: function stableValue(value) {\n112:   if (Array.isArray(value)) {\n113:     return value.map(stableValue);\n114:   }\n115:   if (value && typeof value === 'object') {\n116:     const sorted = {};\n117:     for (const key of Object.keys(value).sort()) {\n118:       sorted[key] = stableValue(value[key]);\n119:     }\n120:     return sorted;\n121:   }\n122:   return value;\n123: }\n124: \n125: function stableStringify(value) {\n126:   return JSON.stringify(stableValue(value));\n127: }\n128: \n129: function normalizeSortText(value) {\n130:   return typeof value === 'string' ? value.trim().toLowerCase().replace(/\\s+/g, ' ') : '';\n131: }\n132: \n133: function contentSortKey(record) {\n134:   const durableText = [\n135:     record.title,\n136:     record.summary,\n137:     record.description,\n138:     record.finding,\n139:     record.question,\n140:     record.direction,\n141:     record.severity,\n142:     record.status,\n143:   ].map(normalizeSortText).filter(Boolean).join('\\u0001');\n144:   return durableText || stableStringify({ ...record, _lineages: undefined });\n145: }\n146: \n147: function contentIdentityKey(record) {\n148:   const durableText = [\n149:     record.title,\n150:     record.summary,\n151:     record.description,\n152:     record.finding,\n153:     record.question,\n154:     record.direction,\n155:   ].map(normalizeSortText).filter(Boolean).join('\\u0001');\n156:   return durableText || stableStringify({\n157:     ...record,\n158:     _conflictOf: undefined,\n159:     _conflict_id: undefined,\n160:     _conflicts: undefined,\n161:     _lineages: undefined,\n162:     severity: undefined,\n163:     status: undefined,\n164:   });\n165: }\n166: \n167: function nearDuplicateContentKey(record) {\n168:   const durableText = [\n169:     record.summary,\n170:     record.description,\n171:     record.finding,\n172:     record.question,\n173:     record.direction,\n174:   ].map(normalizeSortText).filter(Boolean).join('\\u0001');\n175:   return durableText || contentIdentityKey(record);\n176: }\n177: \n178: // Stopwords stripped before comparing titles so the overlap signal keys on the content\n179: // nouns/verbs that distinguish one finding from another, not on filler.\n180: const TITLE_STOPWORDS = new Set([\n181:   'a', 'an', 'the', 'in', 'on', 'at', 'to', 'of', 'for', 'and', 'or', 'with', 'without',\n182:   'is', 'are', 'was', 'were', 'be', 'no', 'not', 'so', 'that', 'this', 'it', 'its', 'as',\n183:   'by', 'from', 'into', 'after', 'before', 'when', 'where', 'which', 'has', 'have',\n184: ]);\n185: \n186: function titleContentTokens(record) {\n187:   const raw = typeof record.title === 'string' ? record.title : '';\n188:   return new Set(\n189:     normalizeSortText(raw)\n190:       .split(/[^a-z0-9]+/)\n191:       .filter((tok) => tok && !TITLE_STOPWORDS.has(tok)),\n192:   );\n193: }\n194: \n195: // Jaccard overlap of two title token sets. 1 when both are empty (no title signal to\n196: // distinguish on → fall back to body-only collapse, the original contract for title-less\n197: // findings).\n198: function titleOverlap(aTokens, bTokens) {\n199:   if (aTokens.size === 0 && bTokens.size === 0) return 1;\n200:   if (aTokens.size === 0 || bTokens.size === 0) return 0;\n201:   let shared = 0;\n202:   for (const tok of aTokens) if (bTokens.has(tok)) shared += 1;\n203:   const union = aTokens.size + bTokens.size - shared;\n204:   return union === 0 ? 1 : shared / union;\n205: }\n206: \n207: // Below this title overlap two same-body findings are treated as DISTINCT (their titles\n208: // name substantively different things — e.g. a generic \"missing auth check\" body whose\n209: // titles name two different endpoints with no shared subject). At or above it the titles\n210: // are paraphrases of one point that share their subject noun, and the same-body findings\n211: // collapse, preserving the designed-for restatement collapse. The threshold is low because\n212: // legitimate restatement titles often share only the one key subject noun (\"cache\",\n213: // \"retry\") while genuinely-distinct titles share no content token at all.\n214: const TITLE_DISTINCT_OVERLAP_THRESHOLD = 0.15;\n215: \n216: // Title-aware near-dup match (deep-review P2-15 fix): two findings are near-duplicates\n217: // only if their body-content key matches AND their titles are not substantively divergent.\n218: // This closes the title blind spot — genuinely-distinct findings that share an identical\n219: // body but carry different distinguishing titles no longer collapse — without breaking the\n220: // designed-for collapse of restatements that share a body and paraphrase the same title.\n221: function nearDuplicateMatches(a, b) {\n222:   if (nearDuplicateContentKey(a) !== nearDuplicateContentKey(b)) return false;\n223:   return titleOverlap(titleContentTokens(a), titleContentTokens(b)) >= TITLE_DISTINCT_OVERLAP_THRESHOLD;\n224: }\n225: \n226: function contentDigest(record) {\n227:   return crypto.createHash('sha256').update(contentIdentityKey(record)).digest('hex').slice(0, 12);\n228: }\n229: \n230: function compareByContentThenId(left, right, idKeys) {\n231:   const leftContent = contentSortKey(left);\n232:   const rightContent = contentSortKey(right);\n233:   if (leftContent < rightContent) return -1;\n234:   if (leftContent > rightContent) return 1;\n235: \n236:   const leftId = normalizeSortText(idKeys.map((key) => left[key]).find(Boolean));\n237:   const rightId = normalizeSortText(idKeys.map((key) => right[key]).find(Boolean));\n238:   if (leftId < rightId) return -1;\n239:   if (leftId > rightId) return 1;\n240: \n241:   const leftFull = stableStringify(left);\n242:   const rightFull = stableStringify(right);\n243:   if (leftFull < rightFull) return -1;\n244:   if (leftFull > rightFull) return 1;\n245:   return 0;\n246: }\n247: \n248: function sortByContentThenId(records, idKeys) {\n249:   return [...records].sort((left, right) => compareByContentThenId(left, right, idKeys));\n250: }\n251: \n252: function addLineage(existing, label) {\n253:   if (!existing._lineages) existing._lineages = [];\n254:   if (!existing._lineages.includes(label)) existing._lineages.push(label);\n255:   existing._lineages.sort();\n256: }\n257: \n258: function mergeLineageLabels(existing, incoming, label) {\n259:   const lineages = new Set([...(existing._lineages || []), ...(incoming._lineages || []), label].filter(Boolean));\n260:   return [...lineages].sort();\n261: }\n262: \n263: function comparableRecord(record) {\n264:   const copy = { ...record };\n265:   delete copy._conflictOf;\n266:   delete copy._conflict_id;\n267:   delete copy._conflicts;\n268:   delete copy._lineages;\n269:   return copy;\n270: }\n271: \n272: function replaceRecord(target, source, lineages) {\n273:   const next = { ...source, _lineages: lineages };\n274:   for (const key of Object.keys(target)) {\n275:     delete target[key];\n276:   }\n277:   Object.assign(target, next);\n278: }\n279: \n280: function chooseCanonicalRecord(existing, incoming, idKeys) {\n281:   return compareByContentThenId(comparableRecord(incoming), comparableRecord(existing), idKeys) < 0\n282:     ? incoming\n283:     : existing;\n284: }\n285: \n286: function chooseReviewCanonicalRecord(existing, incoming, idKeys) {\n287:   const incomingRank = SEVERITY_RANK[incoming.severity] ?? 0;\n288:   const existingRank = SEVERITY_RANK[existing.severity] ?? 0;\n289:   if (incomingRank > existingRank) return incoming;\n290:   if (incomingRank < existingRank) return existing;\n291:   return chooseCanonicalRecord(existing, incoming, idKeys);\n292: }\n293: \n294: function conflictSafeRecord(record, baseId, idKey) {\n295:   const conflictId = `${baseId}--${contentDigest(record)}`;\n296:   return {\n297:     ...record,\n298:     [idKey]: conflictId,\n299:     _conflictOf: baseId,\n300:     _conflict_id: conflictId,\n301:   };\n302: }\n303: \n304: function attachConflictMarkers(records, baseId, idKey) {\n305:   if (records.length < 2) return records;\n306:   return records.map((record) => ({\n307:     ...record,\n308:     _conflicts: records\n309:       .filter((other) => other !== record)\n310:       .map((other) => ({\n311:         relation: 'CONTRADICTS',\n312:         originalId: baseId,\n313:         peerId: other[idKey],\n314:         peerLineages: other._lineages || [],\n315:         basis: 'same-id-different-content',\n316:       })),\n317:   }));\n318: }\n319: \n320: function parseBooleanOption(value) {\n321:   if (value === true) return true;\n322:   if (typeof value !== 'string') return false;\n323:   return ['1', 'true', 'yes', 'on'].includes(value.trim().toLowerCase());\n324: }\n325: \n326: function resolveMergeOptions(options = {}) {\n327:   return {\n328:     enableNearDuplicateDedup: parseBooleanOption(\n329:       options.enableNearDuplicateDedup ?? process.env.SPECKIT_FANOUT_NEAR_DUP_DEDUP,\n330:     ),\n331:   };\n332: }\n333: \n334: function createFindingBucketIndex() {\n335:   return {\n336:     buckets: [],\n337:     byContent: new Map(),\n338:     byId: new Map(),\n339:   };\n340: }\n341: \n342: function getFindingBucket(index, id, finding, enableNearDuplicateDedup) {\n343:   const contentKey = enableNearDuplicateDedup ? nearDuplicateContentKey(finding) : '';\n344:   const exactBucket = index.byId.get(id);\n345:   if (exactBucket) {\n346:     return exactBucket;\n347:   }\n348: \n349:   // Title-aware bucketing (deep-review P2-15 fix): a content key can host MORE than one\n350:   // bucket when several genuinely-distinct findings share an identical body but carry\n351:   // divergent titles. byContent maps a content key to the LIST of buckets seen for it; a\n352:   // same-body finding joins the bucket whose records its title actually matches, and\n353:   // otherwise opens a new bucket. Without this a distinct finding would share a bucket with\n354:   // a different finding and be mis-tagged as a same-id conflict variant by\n355:   // flattenFindingBucketIndex.\n356:   const candidateBuckets = contentKey ? index.byContent.get(contentKey) : undefined;\n357:   if (candidateBuckets) {\n358:     const titleMatch = enableNearDuplicateDedup\n359:       ? candidateBuckets.find((b) => b.records.some((entry) => nearDuplicateMatches(entry, finding)))\n360:       : candidateBuckets[0];\n361:     if (titleMatch) {\n362:       index.byId.set(id, titleMatch);\n363:       return titleMatch;\n364:     }\n365:   }\n366: \n367:   const bucket = { baseId: id, records: [] };\n368:   index.buckets.push(bucket);\n369:   index.byId.set(id, bucket);\n370:   if (contentKey) {\n371:     if (candidateBuckets) candidateBuckets.push(bucket);\n372:     else index.byContent.set(contentKey, [bucket]);\n373:   }\n374:   return bucket;\n375: }\n376: \n377: function flattenFindingBucketIndex(index, idKey, sortKeys) {\n378:   const records = [];\n379:   for (const { baseId, records: bucket } of index.buckets) {\n380:     const variants = sortByContentThenId(bucket, sortKeys);\n381:     if (variants.length === 1) {\n382:       records.push(variants[0]);\n383:       continue;\n384:     }\n385:     records.push(...attachConflictMarkers(\n386:       variants.map((variant) => conflictSafeRecord(variant, baseId, idKey)),\n387:       baseId,\n388:       idKey,\n389:     ));\n390:   }\n391:   return sortByContentThenId(records, sortKeys);\n392: }\n393: \n394: function addResearchFinding(bucket, finding, label, options = {}) {\n395:   const matches = options.enableNearDuplicateDedup\n396:     ? (entry) => nearDuplicateMatches(entry, finding)\n397:     : (entry) => contentIdentityKey(entry) === contentIdentityKey(finding);\n398:   const existing = bucket.find(matches);\n399:   if (existing) {\n400:     if (options.enableNearDuplicateDedup) {\n401:       replaceRecord(existing, chooseCanonicalRecord(existing, finding, ['id', 'title']), mergeLineageLabels(existing, finding, label));\n402:       return;\n403:     }\n404:     addLineage(existing, label);\n405:     return;\n406:   }\n407:   bucket.push({ ...finding, _lineages: [label] });\n408: }\n409: \n410: function addReviewFinding(bucket, finding, label, options = {}) {\n411:   const matches = options.enableNearDuplicateDedup\n412:     ? (entry) => nearDuplicateMatches(entry, finding)\n413:     : (entry) => contentIdentityKey(entry) === contentIdentityKey(finding);\n414:   const existing = bucket.find(matches);\n415:   if (!existing) {\n416:     bucket.push({ ...finding, _lineages: [label] });\n417:     return;\n418:   }\n419: \n420:   if (options.enableNearDuplicateDedup) {\n421:     replaceRecord(\n422:       existing,\n423:       chooseReviewCanonicalRecord(existing, finding, ['findingId', 'title']),\n424:       mergeLineageLabels(existing, finding, label),\n425:     );\n426:     return;\n427:   }\n428: \n429:   const incomingRank = SEVERITY_RANK[finding.severity] ?? 0;\n430:   const existingRank = SEVERITY_RANK[existing.severity] ?? 0;\n431:   if (incomingRank > existingRank) {\n432:     Object.assign(existing, {\n433:       ...finding,\n434:       _lineages: mergeLineageLabels(existing, finding, label),\n435:     });\n436:     return;\n437:   }\n438:   addLineage(existing, label);\n439: }\n440: \n441: function flattenFindingBuckets(findingById, idKey, sortKeys) {\n442:   const records = [];\n443:   for (const [baseId, bucket] of findingById) {\n444:     const variants = sortByContentThenId(bucket, sortKeys);\n445:     if (variants.length === 1) {\n446:       records.push(variants[0]);\n447:       continue;\n448:     }\n449:     records.push(...attachConflictMarkers(\n450:       variants.map((variant) => conflictSafeRecord(variant, baseId, idKey)),\n451:       baseId,\n452:       idKey,\n453:     ));\n454:   }\n455:   return sortByContentThenId(records, sortKeys);\n456: }\n457: \n458: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n459: // 2b. SCHEMA NORMALIZATION\n460: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n461: \n462: /**\n463:  * Normalize a registry object so that the canonical findings key is populated,\n464:  * tolerating known aliases (e.g. `findings` → `keyFindings` for research,\n465:  * `findings` → `openFindings` for review).\n466:  *\n467:  * Returns { registry, warnings } where warnings is an array of structured\n468:  * schema_mismatch events for every alias hit or unusable-registry skip.\n469:  *\n470:  * @param {object|null} registry\n471:  * @param {{ canonicalKey: string, aliases: Record<string, string>, lineage: string }} opts\n472:  * @returns {{ registry: object|null, warnings: object[] }}\n473:  */\n474: function normalizeRegistrySchema(registry, { canonicalKey, aliases, lineage }) {\n475:   if (!registry) return { registry, warnings: [] };\n476:   const warnings = [];\n477: \n478:   // If canonical key is already present and an array, nothing to do.\n479:   if (Array.isArray(registry[canonicalKey])) {\n480:     return { registry, warnings };\n481:   }\n482: \n483:   // Try each alias in priority order.\n484:   for (const [aliasKey, targetKey] of Object.entries(aliases)) {\n485:     if (Array.isArray(registry[aliasKey])) {\n486:       // Alias found — coerce to canonical key.\n487:       registry[targetKey] = registry[aliasKey];\n488:       warnings.push({\n489:         type: 'schema_mismatch',\n490:         severity: 'warn',\n491:         lineage,\n492:         message: `Registry uses non-canonical key \"${aliasKey}\" instead of \"${targetKey}\"; coerced ${registry[aliasKey].length} entries.`,\n493:         aliasKey,\n494:         canonicalKey: targetKey,\n495:         coercedCount: registry[aliasKey].length,\n496:       });\n497:       return { registry, warnings };\n498:     }\n499:   }\n500: \n501:   // No usable findings array found — registry will be skipped.\n502:   // We cannot count entries that don't exist, but report the skip.\n503:   warnings.push({\n504:     type: 'schema_mismatch',\n505:     severity: 'warn',\n506:     lineage,\n507:     message: `Registry has no usable \"${canonicalKey}\" array (checked aliases: ${Object.keys(aliases).join(', ')}); lineage findings will be skipped.`,\n508:     aliasKey: null,\n509:     canonicalKey,\n510:     coercedCount: 0,\n511:   });\n512: \n513:   return { registry, warnings };\n514: }\n515: \n516: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n517: // 3. RESEARCH MERGE\n518: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n519: \n520: /**\n521:  * Merge research findings registries from all lineages.\n522:  * Deduplicates by findingId; cross-model attribution via lineage labels.\n523:  * Returns the merged registry object.\n524:  */\n525: function mergeResearchRegistries(lineageData, options = {}) {\n526:   const mergeOptions = resolveMergeOptions(options);\n527:   const findingById = mergeOptions.enableNearDuplicateDedup ? createFindingBucketIndex() : new Map();\n528:   const schemaWarnings = [];\n529: \n530:   for (const { label, registry: rawRegistry } of lineageData) {\n531:     const { registry, warnings } = normalizeRegistrySchema(rawRegistry, {\n532:       canonicalKey: 'keyFindings',\n533:       aliases: { findings: 'keyFindings' },\n534:       lineage: label,\n535:     });\n536:     for (const w of warnings) {\n537:       schemaWarnings.push(w);\n538:       process.stderr.write(JSON.stringify(w) + '\\n');\n539:     }\n540:     if (!registry || !Array.isArray(registry.keyFindings)) continue;\n541:     for (const finding of registry.keyFindings) {\n542:       const id = finding.id || finding.title;\n543:       if (!id) continue;\n544:       if (mergeOptions.enableNearDuplicateDedup) {\n545:         addResearchFinding(getFindingBucket(findingById, id, finding, true).records, finding, label, mergeOptions);\n546:       } else {\n547:         if (!findingById.has(id)) findingById.set(id, []);\n548:         addResearchFinding(findingById.get(id), finding, label, mergeOptions);\n549:       }\n550:     }\n551:   }\n552: \n553:   const mergedFindings = mergeOptions.enableNearDuplicateDedup\n554:     ? flattenFindingBucketIndex(findingById, 'id', ['id', 'title'])\n555:     : flattenFindingBuckets(findingById, 'id', ['id', 'title']);\n556:   const openQuestionsById = new Map();\n557:   const resolvedQuestionsById = new Map();\n558:   const ruledOutById = new Map();\n559: \n560:   for (const { label, registry } of lineageData) {\n561:     if (!registry) continue;\n562:     for (const q of registry.openQuestions ?? []) {\n563:       const id = q.id || q.question || q.text;\n564:       if (!id) continue;\n565:       if (!openQuestionsById.has(id)) openQuestionsById.set(id, { ...q, _lineages: [label] });\n566:       else {\n567:         const existing = openQuestionsById.get(id);\n568:         addLineage(existing, label);\n569:       }\n570:     }\n571:     // Resolved questions are produced per-lineage by the research reducer but\n572:     // were previously dropped here, under-reporting answered coverage in the\n573:     // merged registry. Collect them with the same id/_lineages discipline.\n574:     for (const q of registry.resolvedQuestions ?? []) {\n575:       const id = q.id || q.question || q.text;\n576:       if (!id) continue;\n577:       if (!resolvedQuestionsById.has(id)) resolvedQuestionsById.set(id, { ...q, _lineages: [label] });\n578:       else {\n579:         const existing = resolvedQuestionsById.get(id);\n580:         addLineage(existing, label);\n581:       }\n582:     }\n583:     for (const d of registry.ruledOutDirections ?? []) {\n584:       const id = d.id || d.direction;\n585:       if (!id) continue;\n586:       if (!ruledOutById.has(id)) ruledOutById.set(id, { ...d, _lineages: [label] });\n587:     }\n588:   }\n589: \n590:   const totalIters = lineageData.reduce((sum, { registry }) => {\n591:     return sum + (registry?.metrics?.iterationsCompleted ?? 0);\n592:   }, 0);\n593: \n594:   const avgConvergence =\n595:     lineageData.length > 0\n596:       ? lineageData.reduce((sum, { registry }) => sum + (registry?.metrics?.convergenceScore ?? 0), 0) /\n597:         lineageData.length\n598:       : 0;\n599: \n600:   return {\n601:     mergedFrom: lineageData.map(({ label }) => label).sort(),\n602:     openQuestions: sortByContentThenId([...openQuestionsById.values()], ['id', 'question', 'text']),\n603:     resolvedQuestions: sortByContentThenId([...resolvedQuestionsById.values()], ['id', 'question', 'text']),\n604:     keyFindings: mergedFindings,\n605:     ruledOutDirections: sortByContentThenId([...ruledOutById.values()], ['id', 'direction']),\n606:     metrics: {\n607:       iterationsCompleted: totalIters,\n608:       openQuestions: openQuestionsById.size,\n609:       resolvedQuestions: resolvedQuestionsById.size,\n610:       keyFindings: mergedFindings.length,\n611:       convergenceScore: Math.round(avgConvergence * 1000) / 1000,\n612:       coverageBySources: {},\n613:     },\n614:     ...(schemaWarnings.length > 0 ? { schema_mismatch: schemaWarnings } : {}),\n615:   };\n616: }\n617: \n618: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n619: // 4. REVIEW MERGE  (strongest-restriction)\n620: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n621: \n622: /**\n623:  * Merge review findings registries with strongest-restriction severity rollup.\n624:  * Any lineage with an active P0 finding causes the merged result to be FAIL.\n625:  * Deduplication is by findingId; cross-lineage P0 wins if any lineage reports it.\n626:  */\n627: function mergeReviewRegistries(lineageData, options = {}) {\n628:   const mergeOptions = resolveMergeOptions(options);\n629:   const findingById = mergeOptions.enableNearDuplicateDedup ? createFindingBucketIndex() : new Map();\n630:   const schemaWarnings = [];\n631: \n632:   for (const { label, registry: rawRegistry } of lineageData) {\n633:     const { registry, warnings } = normalizeRegistrySchema(rawRegistry, {\n634:       canonicalKey: 'openFindings',\n635:       aliases: { findings: 'openFindings' },\n636:       lineage: label,\n637:     });\n638:     for (const w of warnings) {\n639:       schemaWarnings.push(w);\n640:       process.stderr.write(JSON.stringify(w) + '\\n');\n641:     }\n642:     if (!registry || !Array.isArray(registry.openFindings)) continue;\n643:     for (const finding of registry.openFindings) {\n644:       if (finding.status !== 'active') continue;\n645:       const id = finding.findingId || finding.title;\n646:       if (!id) continue;\n647:       if (mergeOptions.enableNearDuplicateDedup) {\n648:         addReviewFinding(getFindingBucket(findingById, id, finding, true).records, finding, label, mergeOptions);\n649:       } else {\n650:         if (!findingById.has(id)) findingById.set(id, []);\n651:         addReviewFinding(findingById.get(id), finding, label, mergeOptions);\n652:       }\n653:     }\n654:   }\n655: \n656:   // Resolved findings are tracked separately per lineage and were previously\n657:   // dropped here, zeroing the merged resolved coverage. Collect them by id with\n658:   // _lineages attribution, without touching open-finding/verdict semantics.\n659:   const resolvedFindingById = mergeOptions.enableNearDuplicateDedup ? createFindingBucketIndex() : new Map();\n660:   for (const { label, registry } of lineageData) {\n661:     if (!registry || !Array.isArray(registry.resolvedFindings)) continue;\n662:     for (const finding of registry.resolvedFindings) {\n663:       const id = finding.findingId || finding.title;\n664:       if (!id) continue;\n665:       if (mergeOptions.enableNearDuplicateDedup) {\n666:         addReviewFinding(getFindingBucket(resolvedFindingById, id, finding, true).records, finding, label, mergeOptions);\n667:       } else if (resolvedFindingById.has(id)) {\n668:         addLineage(resolvedFindingById.get(id), label);\n669:       } else {\n670:         resolvedFindingById.set(id, { ...finding, _lineages: [label] });\n671:       }\n672:     }\n673:   }\n674:   const mergedResolvedFindings = mergeOptions.enableNearDuplicateDedup\n675:     ? flattenFindingBucketIndex(resolvedFindingById, 'findingId', ['findingId', 'title'])\n676:     : sortByContentThenId([...resolvedFindingById.values()], ['findingId', 'title']);\n677: \n678:   const mergedFindings = mergeOptions.enableNearDuplicateDedup\n679:     ? flattenFindingBucketIndex(findingById, 'findingId', ['findingId', 'title'])\n680:     : flattenFindingBuckets(findingById, 'findingId', ['findingId', 'title']);\n681:   const activeP0 = mergedFindings.filter((f) => f.severity === 'P0' && f.status === 'active').length;\n682:   const activeP1 = mergedFindings.filter((f) => f.severity === 'P1' && f.status === 'active').length;\n683:   const activeP2 = mergedFindings.filter((f) => f.severity === 'P2' && f.status === 'active').length;\n684: \n685:   // Strongest-restriction verdict\n686:   let mergedVerdict;\n687:   if (activeP0 > 0) {\n688:     mergedVerdict = 'FAIL';\n689:   } else if (activeP1 > 0) {\n690:     mergedVerdict = 'CONDITIONAL';\n691:   } else {\n692:     mergedVerdict = 'PASS';\n693:   }\n694: \n695:   return {\n696:     mergedFrom: lineageData.map(({ label }) => label).sort(),\n697:     mergedVerdict,\n698:     openFindings: mergedFindings,\n699:     resolvedFindings: mergedResolvedFindings,\n700:     findingsBySeverity: { P0: activeP0, P1: activeP1, P2: activeP2 },\n701:     openFindingsCount: mergedFindings.length,\n702:     resolvedFindingsCount: mergedResolvedFindings.length,\n703:     activeP0,\n704:     activeP1,\n705:     activeP2,\n706:     ...(schemaWarnings.length > 0 ? { schema_mismatch: schemaWarnings } : {}),\n707:   };\n708: }\n709: \n710: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n711: // 5. ATTRIBUTION\n712: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n713: \n714: /**\n715:  * Build fanout-attribution.md summarizing per-lineage convergence, iters, salvage, model.\n716:  */\n717: function buildAttributionMd(lineageData, loopType) {\n718:   const lines = [\n719:     `# Fan-Out Attribution`,\n720:     ``,\n721:     `Loop type: **${loopType}**  |  Lineage count: **${lineageData.length}**`,\n722:     ``,\n723:     `| Label | Kind | Model | Iterations | Convergence | Salvaged | Verdict |`,\n724:     `|-------|------|-------|-----------|-------------|----------|---------|`,\n725:   ];\n726: \n727:   for (const { label, registry, stateRecords, kind, model } of lineageData) {\n728:     const iters = stateRecords.filter((r) => r.type === 'iteration').length;\n729:     const salvage = stateRecords.filter((r) => r.type === 'event' && r.event === 'salvaged_from_stdout').length;\n730:     const convergenceScore = registry?.metrics?.convergenceScore ?? registry?.convergenceScore ?? 'n/a';\n731:     const verdict =\n732:       loopType === 'review'\n733:         ? registry?.findingsBySeverity?.P0 > 0\n734:           ? 'FAIL'\n735:           : registry?.findingsBySeverity?.P1 > 0\n736:           ? 'CONDITIONAL'\n737:           : 'PASS'\n738:         : 'n/a';\n739:     lines.push(`| ${label} | ${kind ?? 'unknown'} | ${model ?? 'default'} | ${iters} | ${convergenceScore} | ${salvage} | ${verdict} |`);\n740:   }\n741: \n742:   lines.push('');\n743:   return lines.join('\\n');\n744: }\n745: \n746: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n747: // 6. MAIN\n748: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n749: \n750: /**\n751:  * Reconstruct a minimal review findings registry from a lineage state log.\n752:  *\n753:  * Leaf-only review lineages may carry active findings only in their state log\n754:  * iteration records (`findingDetails`), with no registry file on disk. This maps\n755:  * those findingDetails into the openFindings shape mergeReviewRegistries consumes,\n756:  * so registry-absent lineages are not silently dropped from merge/synthesis.\n757:  *\n758:  * @param {Array<Object>} stateRecords - Parsed JSONL state records.\n759:  * @param {string} label - Lineage label, for attribution.\n760:  * @returns {{openFindings:Array,Object}|null} Reconstructed registry, or null when no findings exist.\n761:  */\n762: function reconstructReviewRegistryFromState(stateRecords, label) {\n763:   if (!Array.isArray(stateRecords)) return null;\n764:   const openFindings = [];\n765:   const resolvedFindings = [];\n766:   for (const record of stateRecords) {\n767:     if (!record || record.type !== 'iteration' || !Array.isArray(record.findingDetails)) continue;\n768:     for (const detail of record.findingDetails) {\n769:       if (!detail || typeof detail !== 'object') continue;\n770:       const id = detail.id || detail.findingId || detail.title;\n771:       if (!id) continue;\n772:       const isActive = (detail.disposition || detail.status || 'active') === 'active';\n773:       const mapped = {\n774:         findingId: id,\n775:         title: detail.title || id,\n776:         severity: detail.severity || 'P2',\n777:         status: isActive ? 'active' : 'resolved',\n778:         ...(detail.dimension ? { dimension: detail.dimension } : {}),\n779:         ...(detail.file ? { file: detail.file } : {}),\n780:         ...(detail.recommendation ? { recommendation: detail.recommendation } : {}),\n781:         _lineages: [label],\n782:         _reconstructed_from_state: true,\n783:       };\n784:       if (isActive) openFindings.push(mapped);\n785:       else resolvedFindings.push(mapped);\n786:     }\n787:   }\n788:   if (openFindings.length === 0 && resolvedFindings.length === 0) return null;\n789:   const bySeverity = {\n790:     P0: openFindings.filter((f) => f.severity === 'P0').length,\n791:     P1: openFindings.filter((f) => f.severity === 'P1').length,\n792:     P2: openFindings.filter((f) => f.severity === 'P2').length,\n793:   };\n794:   return { openFindings, resolvedFindings, findingsBySeverity: bySeverity, _reconstructed: true };\n795: }\n796: \n797: function firstNonEmptyString(values) {\n798:   for (const value of values) {\n799:     if (typeof value === 'string' && value.trim() !== '') return value.trim();\n800:     if (value && typeof value === 'object' && !Array.isArray(value)) {\n801:       const objectText = firstNonEmptyString([value.title, value.summary, value.text, value.finding, value.description]);\n802:       if (objectText) return objectText;\n803:     }\n804:   }\n805:   return '';\n806: }\n807: \n808: function normalizeResearchFindingCandidate(candidate, record, index) {\n809:   const run = Number.isFinite(Number(record.run ?? record.iteration)) ? Math.floor(Number(record.run ?? record.iteration)) : 0;\n810:   if (typeof candidate === 'string') {\n811:     const text = candidate.trim();\n812:     if (!text) return null;\n813:     return {\n814:       id: `state-finding-${run}-${index + 1}-${crypto.createHash('sha256').update(text).digest('hex').slice(0, 12)}`,\n815:       title: text,\n816:       text,\n817:       addedAtIteration: run,\n818:       _reconstructed_from_state: true,\n819:     };\n820:   }\n821:   if (!candidate || typeof candidate !== 'object' || Array.isArray(candidate)) return null;\n822:   const text = firstNonEmptyString([candidate.title, candidate.summary, candidate.text, candidate.finding, candidate.description]);\n823:   if (!text) return null;\n824:   return {\n825:     id: candidate.id || candidate.findingId || `state-finding-${run}-${index + 1}-${crypto.createHash('sha256').update(text).digest('hex').slice(0, 12)}`,\n826:     title: candidate.title || text,\n827:     ...(candidate.summary ? { summary: candidate.summary } : {}),\n828:     ...(candidate.text ? { text: candidate.text } : { text }),\n829:     ...(candidate.confidence ? { confidence: candidate.confidence } : {}),\n830:     addedAtIteration: candidate.addedAtIteration ?? run,\n831:     _reconstructed_from_state: true,\n832:   };\n833: }\n834: \n835: function researchCandidatesFromIteration(record) {\n836:   if (!record || record.type !== 'iteration') return [];\n837:   const structured = [record.keyFindings, record.findings, record.findingDetails]\n838:     .find((value) => Array.isArray(value) && value.length > 0);\n839:   if (Array.isArray(structured)) {\n840:     return structured;\n841:   }\n842: \n843:   const findingsCount = Number(record.findingsCount);\n844:   if (!Number.isFinite(findingsCount) || findingsCount <= 0) return [];\n845:   const run = Number.isFinite(Number(record.run ?? record.iteration)) ? Math.floor(Number(record.run ?? record.iteration)) : 0;\n846:   const narrative = firstNonEmptyString([\n847:     record.summary,\n848:     record.findingsSummary,\n849:     record.focus,\n850:     record.nextFocus,\n851:     record.reflection,\n852:   ]);\n853:   return [{\n854:     id: `state-finding-${run}-1-${crypto.createHash('sha256').update(narrative || String(run)).digest('hex').slice(0, 12)}`,\n855:     title: narrative || `Iteration ${run} recorded ${Math.floor(findingsCount)} finding(s)`,\n856:     summary: narrative || `State log recorded ${Math.floor(findingsCount)} finding(s) but no structured finding text.`,\n857:     addedAtIteration: run,\n858:   }];\n859: }\n860: \n861: /**\n862:  * Reconstruct a minimal research findings registry from a lineage state log.\n863:  *\n864:  * Leaf-only research lineages may have substantive iteration records but no\n865:  * registry file on disk. This maps state-log findings into keyFindings so the\n866:  * research merge does not silently drop a registry-absent lineage.\n867:  *\n868:  * @param {Array<Object>} stateRecords - Parsed JSONL state records.\n869:  * @param {string} label - Lineage label, for attribution.\n870:  * @returns {{keyFindings:Array,Object}|null} Reconstructed registry, or null when no findings exist.\n871:  */\n872: function reconstructResearchRegistryFromState(stateRecords, label) {\n873:   if (!Array.isArray(stateRecords)) return null;\n874:   const keyFindings = [];\n875:   for (const record of stateRecords) {\n876:     const candidates = researchCandidatesFromIteration(record);\n877:     candidates.forEach((candidate, index) => {\n878:       const mapped = normalizeResearchFindingCandidate(candidate, record, index);\n879:       if (!mapped) return;\n880:       keyFindings.push({ ...mapped, _lineages: [label] });\n881:     });\n882:   }\n883:   if (keyFindings.length === 0) return null;\n884:   const iterationsCompleted = stateRecords.filter((record) => record?.type === 'iteration').length;\n885:   const latestIteration = stateRecords.filter((record) => record?.type === 'iteration').at(-1);\n886:   const convergenceScore = latestIteration?.convergenceSignals?.compositeStop\n887:     ?? latestIteration?.newInfoRatio\n888:     ?? 0;\n889:   return {\n890:     keyFindings,\n891:     openQuestions: [],\n892:     resolvedQuestions: [],\n893:     ruledOutDirections: [],\n894:     metrics: {\n895:       iterationsCompleted,\n896:       openQuestions: 0,\n897:       resolvedQuestions: 0,\n898:       keyFindings: keyFindings.length,\n899:       convergenceScore,\n900:       coverageBySources: {},\n901:     },\n902:     _reconstructed: true,\n903:   };\n904: }\n905: \n906: async function main() {\n907:   const { writeStateAtomic, writeTextAtomic } = await import('../lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts');\n908:   const args = parseArgs();\n909:   const loopType = ensureString(args, 'loopType');\n910:   if (loopType !== 'research' && loopType !== 'review' && loopType !== 'context') {\n911:     throw inputError('loopType must be \"research\", \"review\", or \"context\"');\n912:   }\n913:   const artifactDir = ensureString(args, 'artifactDir');\n914:   const lineagesDir = path.join(artifactDir, 'lineages');\n915: \n916:   if (!fs.existsSync(lineagesDir)) {\n917:     jsonOut({ status: 'ok', message: 'no lineages directory — nothing to merge', merged: 0 });\n918:     return;\n919:   }\n920: \n921:   const labelDirs = fs.readdirSync(lineagesDir)\n922:     .filter((entry) => fs.statSync(path.join(lineagesDir, entry)).isDirectory())\n923:     .sort();\n924: \n925:   if (labelDirs.length === 0) {\n926:     jsonOut({ status: 'ok', message: 'no lineage subdirs found', merged: 0 });\n927:     return;\n928:   }\n929: \n930:   // Load per-lineage data\n931:   const registryName =\n932:     loopType === 'review' ? 'deep-review-findings-registry.json' : 'deep-research-findings-registry.json';\n933:   const stateLogName = loopType === 'review' ? 'deep-review-state.jsonl' : 'deep-research-state.jsonl';\n934:   const summaryPath = path.join(artifactDir, 'orchestration-summary.json');\n935:   const orchestrationSummary = tryReadJson(summaryPath) ?? {};\n936: \n937:   const lineageData = labelDirs.map((label) => {\n938:     const lineageDir = path.join(lineagesDir, label);\n939:     let registry = tryReadJson(path.join(lineageDir, registryName));\n940:     const stateRecords = readStateLog(path.join(lineageDir, stateLogName));\n941:     // Leaf-only review/research lineages (orchestrator-managed direct-leaf convention) may carry\n942:     // active findings only in their state log's findingDetails, with no registry file.\n943:     // Without a registry, such a lineage was silently skipped by the registry-only merge,\n944:     // dropping its findings from synthesis. Reconstruct a minimal registry from the\n945:     // state log so leaf-only lineages reach merge without a separate reducer step.\n946:     if (!registry && loopType === 'review') {\n947:       registry = reconstructReviewRegistryFromState(stateRecords, label);\n948:     }\n949:     if (!registry && loopType === 'research') {\n950:       registry = reconstructResearchRegistryFromState(stateRecords, label);\n951:     }\n952:     // Infer kind/model from state log executor records\n953:     const executorRecord = stateRecords.find((r) => r.type === 'event' && r.event === 'executor_start');\n954:     return {\n955:       label,\n956:       lineageDir,\n957:       registry,\n958:       stateRecords,\n959:       kind: executorRecord?.kind ?? orchestrationSummary?.[label]?.kind ?? 'unknown',\n960:       model: executorRecord?.model ?? orchestrationSummary?.[label]?.model ?? 'unknown',\n961:     };\n962:   });\n963: \n964:   const lineagesWithRegistry = lineageData.filter((d) => d.registry !== null);\n965: \n966:   let mergedRegistry;\n967:   if (loopType === 'review') {\n968:     mergedRegistry = mergeReviewRegistries(lineagesWithRegistry, resolveMergeOptions(args));\n969:   } else {\n970:     mergedRegistry = mergeResearchRegistries(lineagesWithRegistry, resolveMergeOptions(args));\n971:   }\n972: \n973:   // Write merged registry to base artifact dir (replacing single-executor path).\n974:   // Atomic temp+fsync+rename so a mid-write kill never hands synthesis a\n975:   // truncated registry — readers see the prior file or the complete new one.\n976:   const mergedRegistryPath = path.join(artifactDir, registryName);\n977:   writeStateAtomic(mergedRegistryPath, mergedRegistry);\n978: \n979:   // Write attribution markdown atomically (same torn-write guarantee; text, not JSON).\n980:   const attributionPath = path.join(artifactDir, 'fanout-attribution.md');\n981:   writeTextAtomic(attributionPath, buildAttributionMd(lineageData, loopType));\n982: \n983:   jsonOut({\n984:     status: 'ok',\n985:     loop_type: loopType,\n986:     merged_lineages: lineagesWithRegistry.length,\n987:     skipped_no_registry: lineageData.length - lineagesWithRegistry.length,\n988:     merged_registry_path: mergedRegistryPath,\n989:     attribution_path: attributionPath,\n990:     ...(loopType === 'review'\n991:       ? { merged_verdict: mergedRegistry.mergedVerdict, active_p0: mergedRegistry.activeP0, active_p1: mergedRegistry.activeP1 }\n992:       : { key_findings: mergedRegistry.keyFindings?.length ?? 0 }),\n993:   });\n994: }\n995: \n996: // Exports for unit testing\n997: module.exports = { mergeResearchRegistries, mergeReviewRegistries, buildAttributionMd, reconstructReviewRegistryFromState, reconstructResearchRegistryFromState, normalizeRegistrySchema };\n998: \n999: if (require.main === module) {\n1000:   main().catch((err) => {\n1001:     const code = err && err.code === 'INPUT_VALIDATION' ? 3 : 1;\n1002:     jsonOut({\n1003:       status: 'error',\n1004:       error: err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err),\n1005:       code: err && err.code ? err.code : 'SCRIPT_ERROR',\n1006:     });\n1007:     if (code === 1) {\n1008:       process.stderr.write(\n1009:         JSON.stringify({ error: err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err), stack: err && err.stack }) + '\\n',\n1010:       );\n1011:     }\n1012:     process.exit(code);\n1013:   });\n1014: }\n\n(End of file - total 1014 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ Deep-Loop Runtime — Fan-Out Cross-Lineage Merge                          ║\n// ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n// ║ Input:  CLI args (--loop-type, --artifact-dir).                          ║\n// ║ Output: JSON to stdout.                                                  ║\n// ║ Exit:   0=ok, 1=script error, 3=input validation error.                 ║\n// ║                                                                          ║\n// ║ Reads every {artifact-dir}/lineages/{label}/ sub-packet and produces:   ║\n// ║   research: deduplicated deep-research-findings-registry.json +          ║\n// ║             fanout-attribution.md                                        ║\n// ║   review:   severity-rollup deep-review-findings-registry.json           ║\n// ║             (strongest-restriction: any lineage P0 → merged FAIL) +     ║\n// ║             fanout-attribution.md                                        ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\n'use strict';\n\nconst crypto = require('node:crypto');\nconst fs = require('node:fs');\nconst path = require('node:path');","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs","text":"// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ Deep-Loop Runtime — Fan-Out Cross-Lineage Merge                          ║\n// ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n// ║ Input:  CLI args (--loop-type, --artifact-dir).                          ║\n// ║ Output: JSON to stdout.                                                  ║\n// ║ Exit:   0=ok, 1=script error, 3=input validation error.                 ║\n// ║                                                                          ║\n// ║ Reads every {artifact-dir}/lineages/{label}/ sub-packet and produces:   ║\n// ║   research: deduplicated deep-research-findings-registry.json +          ║\n// ║             fanout-attribution.md                                        ║\n// ║   review:   severity-rollup deep-review-findings-registry.json           ║\n// ║             (strongest-restriction: any lineage P0 → merged FAIL) +     ║\n// ║             fanout-attribution.md                                        ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\n'use strict';\n\nconst crypto = require('node:crypto');\nconst fs = require('node:fs');\nconst path = require('node:path');\nconst { spawnSync } = require('node:child_process');\n\nconst SEVERITY_RANK = { P0: 3, P1: 2, P2: 1 };\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 1. TSX BOOTSTRAP\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst TSX_LOADER = require.resolve('tsx');\n\n// The merged registry and attribution share the runtime's atomic-state helpers,\n// which are TypeScript ESM. Re-exec once under the tsx loader so the dynamic\n// import below resolves them; mirrors convergence.cjs. Only the CLI entrypoint\n// re-execs — module consumers (unit tests) import the pure helpers directly.\nif (require.main === module && process.env.DEEP_LOOP_TSX_LOADED !== '1') {\n  const child = spawnSync(\n    process.execPath,\n    ['--import', TSX_LOADER, __filename, ...process.argv.slice(2)],\n    {\n      cwd: process.cwd(),\n      env: { ...process.env, DEEP_LOOP_TSX_LOADED: '1' },\n      encoding: 'utf8',\n    },\n  );\n  if (child.stdout) process.stdout.write(child.stdout);\n  if (child.stderr) process.stderr.write(child.stderr);\n  process.exit(child.status === null ? 1 : child.status);\n}\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 2. HELPERS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nfunction inputError(message) {\n  const err = new Error(message);\n  err.code = 'INPUT_VALIDATION';\n  return err;\n}\n\nfunction jsonOut(payload) {\n  process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(payload)}\\n`);\n}\n\nfunction parseArgs(argv = process.argv.slice(2)) {\n  const args = {};\n  for (let i = 0; i < argv.length; i += 1) {\n    const token = argv[i];\n    if (!token.startsWith('--')) {\n      throw inputError(`Unexpected positional argument: ${token}`);\n    }\n    const key = token.slice(2).replace(/-([a-z])/g, (_, c) => c.toUpperCase());\n    const next = argv[i + 1];\n    if (next === undefined || next.startsWith('--')) {\n      args[key] = true;\n    } else {\n      args[key] = next;\n      i += 1;\n    }\n  }\n  return args;\n}\n\nfunction ensureString(args, key) {\n  if (!args[key] || typeof args[key] !== 'string') {\n    throw inputError(`${key} is required`);\n  }\n  return args[key];\n}\n\nfunction tryReadJson(filePath) {\n  if (!fs.existsSync(filePath)) return null;\n  try {\n    return JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8'));\n  } catch {\n    return null;\n  }\n}\n\nfunction readStateLog(stateLogPath) {\n  if (!fs.existsSync(stateLogPath)) return [];\n  const lines = fs.readFileSync(stateLogPath, 'utf8').trim().split('\\n').filter(Boolean);\n  return lines.flatMap((line) => {\n    try {\n      return [JSON.parse(line)];\n    } catch {\n      return [];\n    }\n  });\n}\n\nfunction stableValue(value) {\n  if (Array.isArray(value)) {\n    return value.map(stableValue);\n  }\n  if (value && typeof value === 'object') {\n    const sorted = {};\n    for (const key of Object.keys(value).sort()) {\n      sorted[key] = stableValue(value[key]);\n    }\n    return sorted;\n  }\n  return value;\n}\n\nfunction stableStringify(value) {\n  return JSON.stringify(stableValue(value));\n}\n\nfunction normalizeSortText(value) {\n  return typeof value === 'string' ? value.trim().toLowerCase().replace(/\\s+/g, ' ') : '';\n}\n\nfunction contentSortKey(record) {\n  const durableText = [\n    record.title,\n    record.summary,\n    record.description,\n    record.finding,\n    record.question,\n    record.direction,\n    record.severity,\n    record.status,\n  ].map(normalizeSortText).filter(Boolean).join('\\u0001');\n  return durableText || stableStringify({ ...record, _lineages: undefined });\n}\n\nfunction contentIdentityKey(record) {\n  const durableText = [\n    record.title,\n    record.summary,\n    record.description,\n    record.finding,\n    record.question,\n    record.direction,\n  ].map(normalizeSortText).filter(Boolean).join('\\u0001');\n  return durableText || stableStringify({\n    ...record,\n    _conflictOf: undefined,\n    _conflict_id: undefined,\n    _conflicts: undefined,\n    _lineages: undefined,\n    severity: undefined,\n    status: undefined,\n  });\n}\n\nfunction nearDuplicateContentKey(record) {\n  const durableText = [\n    record.summary,\n    record.description,\n    record.finding,\n    record.question,\n    record.direction,\n  ].map(normalizeSortText).filter(Boolean).join('\\u0001');\n  return durableText || contentIdentityKey(record);\n}\n\n// Stopwords stripped before comparing titles so the overlap signal keys on the content\n// nouns/verbs that distinguish one finding from another, not on filler.\nconst TITLE_STOPWORDS = new Set([\n  'a', 'an', 'the', 'in', 'on', 'at', 'to', 'of', 'for', 'and', 'or', 'with', 'without',\n  'is', 'are', 'was', 'were', 'be', 'no', 'not', 'so', 'that', 'this', 'it', 'its', 'as',\n  'by', 'from', 'into', 'after', 'before', 'when', 'where', 'which', 'has', 'have',\n]);\n\nfunction titleContentTokens(record) {\n  const raw = typeof record.title === 'string' ? record.title : '';\n  return new Set(\n    normalizeSortText(raw)\n      .split(/[^a-z0-9]+/)\n      .filter((tok) => tok && !TITLE_STOPWORDS.has(tok)),\n  );\n}\n\n// Jaccard overlap of two title token sets. 1 when both are empty (no title signal to\n// distinguish on → fall back to body-only collapse, the original contract for title-less\n// findings).\nfunction titleOverlap(aTokens, bTokens) {\n  if (aTokens.size === 0 && bTokens.size === 0) return 1;\n  if (aTokens.size === 0 || bTokens.size === 0) return 0;\n  let shared = 0;\n  for (const tok of aTokens) if (bTokens.has(tok)) shared += 1;\n  const union = aTokens.size + bTokens.size - shared;\n  return union === 0 ? 1 : shared / union;\n}\n\n// Below this title overlap two same-body findings are treated as DISTINCT (their titles\n// name substantively different things — e.g. a generic \"missing auth check\" body whose\n// titles name two different endpoints with no shared subject). At or above it the titles\n// are paraphrases of one point that share their subject noun, and the same-body findings\n// collapse, preserving the designed-for restatement collapse. The threshold is low because\n// legitimate restatement titles often share only the one key subject noun (\"cache\",\n// \"retry\") while genuinely-distinct titles share no content token at all.\nconst TITLE_DISTINCT_OVERLAP_THRESHOLD = 0.15;\n\n// Title-aware near-dup match (deep-review P2-15 fix): two findings are near-duplicates\n// only if their body-content key matches AND their titles are not substantively divergent.\n// This closes the title blind spot — genuinely-distinct findings that share an identical\n// body but carry different distinguishing titles no longer collapse — without breaking the\n// designed-for collapse of restatements that share a body and paraphrase the same title.\nfunction nearDuplicateMatches(a, b) {\n  if (nearDuplicateContentKey(a) !== nearDuplicateContentKey(b)) return false;\n  return titleOverlap(titleContentTokens(a), titleContentTokens(b)) >= TITLE_DISTINCT_OVERLAP_THRESHOLD;\n}\n\nfunction contentDigest(record) {\n  return crypto.createHash('sha256').update(contentIdentityKey(record)).digest('hex').slice(0, 12);\n}\n\nfunction compareByContentThenId(left, right, idKeys) {\n  const leftContent = contentSortKey(left);\n  const rightContent = contentSortKey(right);\n  if (leftContent < rightContent) return -1;\n  if (leftContent > rightContent) return 1;\n\n  const leftId = normalizeSortText(idKeys.map((key) => left[key]).find(Boolean));\n  const rightId = normalizeSortText(idKeys.map((key) => right[key]).find(Boolean));\n  if (leftId < rightId) return -1;\n  if (leftId > rightId) return 1;\n\n  const leftFull = stableStringify(left);\n  const rightFull = stableStringify(right);\n  if (leftFull < rightFull) return -1;\n  if (leftFull > rightFull) return 1;\n  return 0;\n}\n\nfunction sortByContentThenId(records, idKeys) {\n  return [...records].sort((left, right) => compareByContentThenId(left, right, idKeys));\n}\n\nfunction addLineage(existing, label) {\n  if (!existing._lineages) existing._lineages = [];\n  if (!existing._lineages.includes(label)) existing._lineages.push(label);\n  existing._lineages.sort();\n}\n\nfunction mergeLineageLabels(existing, incoming, label) {\n  const lineages = new Set([...(existing._lineages || []), ...(incoming._lineages || []), label].filter(Boolean));\n  return [...lineages].sort();\n}\n\nfunction comparableRecord(record) {\n  const copy = { ...record };\n  delete copy._conflictOf;\n  delete copy._conflict_id;\n  delete copy._conflicts;\n  delete copy._lineages;\n  return copy;\n}\n\nfunction replaceRecord(target, source, lineages) {\n  const next = { ...source, _lineages: lineages };\n  for (const key of Object.keys(target)) {\n    delete target[key];\n  }\n  Object.assign(target, next);\n}\n\nfunction chooseCanonicalRecord(existing, incoming, idKeys) {\n  return compareByContentThenId(comparableRecord(incoming), comparableRecord(existing), idKeys) < 0\n    ? incoming\n    : existing;\n}\n\nfunction chooseReviewCanonicalRecord(existing, incoming, idKeys) {\n  const incomingRank = SEVERITY_RANK[incoming.severity] ?? 0;\n  const existingRank = SEVERITY_RANK[existing.severity] ?? 0;\n  if (incomingRank > existingRank) return incoming;\n  if (incomingRank < existingRank) return existing;\n  return chooseCanonicalRecord(existing, incoming, idKeys);\n}\n\nfunction conflictSafeRecord(record, baseId, idKey) {\n  const conflictId = `${baseId}--${contentDigest(record)}`;\n  return {\n    ...record,\n    [idKey]: conflictId,\n    _conflictOf: baseId,\n    _conflict_id: conflictId,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction attachConflictMarkers(records, baseId, idKey) {\n  if (records.length < 2) return records;\n  return records.map((record) => ({\n    ...record,\n    _conflicts: records\n      .filter((other) => other !== record)\n      .map((other) => ({\n        relation: 'CONTRADICTS',\n        originalId: baseId,\n        peerId: other[idKey],\n        peerLineages: other._lineages || [],\n        basis: 'same-id-different-content',\n      })),\n  }));\n}\n\nfunction parseBooleanOption(value) {\n  if (value === true) return true;\n  if (typeof value !== 'string') return false;\n  return ['1', 'true', 'yes', 'on'].includes(value.trim().toLowerCase());\n}\n\nfunction resolveMergeOptions(options = {}) {\n  return {\n    enableNearDuplicateDedup: parseBooleanOption(\n      options.enableNearDuplicateDedup ?? process.env.SPECKIT_FANOUT_NEAR_DUP_DEDUP,\n    ),\n  };\n}\n\nfunction createFindingBucketIndex() {\n  return {\n    buckets: [],\n    byContent: new Map(),\n    byId: new Map(),\n  };\n}\n\nfunction getFindingBucket(index, id, finding, enableNearDuplicateDedup) {\n  const contentKey = enableNearDuplicateDedup ? nearDuplicateContentKey(finding) : '';\n  const exactBucket = index.byId.get(id);\n  if (exactBucket) {\n    return exactBucket;\n  }\n\n  // Title-aware bucketing (deep-review P2-15 fix): a content key can host MORE than one\n  // bucket when several genuinely-distinct findings share an identical body but carry\n  // divergent titles. byContent maps a content key to the LIST of buckets seen for it; a\n  // same-body finding joins the bucket whose records its title actually matches, and\n  // otherwise opens a new bucket. Without this a distinct finding would share a bucket with\n  // a different finding and be mis-tagged as a same-id conflict variant by\n  // flattenFindingBucketIndex.\n  const candidateBuckets = contentKey ? index.byContent.get(contentKey) : undefined;\n  if (candidateBuckets) {\n    const titleMatch = enableNearDuplicateDedup\n      ? candidateBuckets.find((b) => b.records.some((entry) => nearDuplicateMatches(entry, finding)))\n      : candidateBuckets[0];\n    if (titleMatch) {\n      index.byId.set(id, titleMatch);\n      return titleMatch;\n    }\n  }\n\n  const bucket = { baseId: id, records: [] };\n  index.buckets.push(bucket);\n  index.byId.set(id, bucket);\n  if (contentKey) {\n    if (candidateBuckets) candidateBuckets.push(bucket);\n    else index.byContent.set(contentKey, [bucket]);\n  }\n  return bucket;\n}\n\nfunction flattenFindingBucketIndex(index, idKey, sortKeys) {\n  const records = [];\n  for (const { baseId, records: bucket } of index.buckets) {\n    const variants = sortByContentThenId(bucket, sortKeys);\n    if (variants.length === 1) {\n      records.push(variants[0]);\n      continue;\n    }\n    records.push(...attachConflictMarkers(\n      variants.map((variant) => conflictSafeRecord(variant, baseId, idKey)),\n      baseId,\n      idKey,\n    ));\n  }\n  return sortByContentThenId(records, sortKeys);\n}\n\nfunction addResearchFinding(bucket, finding, label, options = {}) {\n  const matches = options.enableNearDuplicateDedup\n    ? (entry) => nearDuplicateMatches(entry, finding)\n    : (entry) => contentIdentityKey(entry) === contentIdentityKey(finding);\n  const existing = bucket.find(matches);\n  if (existing) {\n    if (options.enableNearDuplicateDedup) {\n      replaceRecord(existing, chooseCanonicalRecord(existing, finding, ['id', 'title']), mergeLineageLabels(existing, finding, label));\n      return;\n    }\n    addLineage(existing, label);\n    return;\n  }\n  bucket.push({ ...finding, _lineages: [label] });\n}\n\nfunction addReviewFinding(bucket, finding, label, options = {}) {\n  const matches = options.enableNearDuplicateDedup\n    ? (entry) => nearDuplicateMatches(entry, finding)\n    : (entry) => contentIdentityKey(entry) === contentIdentityKey(finding);\n  const existing = bucket.find(matches);\n  if (!existing) {\n    bucket.push({ ...finding, _lineages: [label] });\n    return;\n  }\n\n  if (options.enableNearDuplicateDedup) {\n    replaceRecord(\n      existing,\n      chooseReviewCanonicalRecord(existing, finding, ['findingId', 'title']),\n      mergeLineageLabels(existing, finding, label),\n    );\n    return;\n  }\n\n  const incomingRank = SEVERITY_RANK[finding.severity] ?? 0;\n  const existingRank = SEVERITY_RANK[existing.severity] ?? 0;\n  if (incomingRank > existingRank) {\n    Object.assign(existing, {\n      ...finding,\n      _lineages: mergeLineageLabels(existing, finding, label),\n    });\n    return;\n  }\n  addLineage(existing, label);\n}\n\nfunction flattenFindingBuckets(findingById, idKey, sortKeys) {\n  const records = [];\n  for (const [baseId, bucket] of findingById) {\n    const variants = sortByContentThenId(bucket, sortKeys);\n    if (variants.length === 1) {\n      records.push(variants[0]);\n      continue;\n    }\n    records.push(...attachConflictMarkers(\n      variants.map((variant) => conflictSafeRecord(variant, baseId, idKey)),\n      baseId,\n      idKey,\n    ));\n  }\n  return sortByContentThenId(records, sortKeys);\n}\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 2b. SCHEMA NORMALIZATION\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/**\n * Normalize a registry object so that the canonical findings key is populated,\n * tolerating known aliases (e.g. `findings` → `keyFindings` for research,\n * `findings` → `openFindings` for review).\n *\n * Returns { registry, warnings } where warnings is an array of structured\n * schema_mismatch events for every alias hit or unusable-registry skip.\n *\n * @param {object|null} registry\n * @param {{ canonicalKey: string, aliases: Record<string, string>, lineage: string }} opts\n * @returns {{ registry: object|null, warnings: object[] }}\n */\nfunction normalizeRegistrySchema(registry, { canonicalKey, aliases, lineage }) {\n  if (!registry) return { registry, warnings: [] };\n  const warnings = [];\n\n  // If canonical key is already present and an array, nothing to do.\n  if (Array.isArray(registry[canonicalKey])) {\n    return { registry, warnings };\n  }\n\n  // Try each alias in priority order.\n  for (const [aliasKey, targetKey] of Object.entries(aliases)) {\n    if (Array.isArray(registry[aliasKey])) {\n      // Alias found — coerce to canonical key.\n      registry[targetKey] = registry[aliasKey];\n      warnings.push({\n        type: 'schema_mismatch',\n        severity: 'warn',\n        lineage,\n        message: `Registry uses non-canonical key \"${aliasKey}\" instead of \"${targetKey}\"; coerced ${registry[aliasKey].length} entries.`,\n        aliasKey,\n        canonicalKey: targetKey,\n        coercedCount: registry[aliasKey].length,\n      });\n      return { registry, warnings };\n    }\n  }\n\n  // No usable findings array found — registry will be skipped.\n  // We cannot count entries that don't exist, but report the skip.\n  warnings.push({\n    type: 'schema_mismatch',\n    severity: 'warn',\n    lineage,\n    message: `Registry has no usable \"${canonicalKey}\" array (checked aliases: ${Object.keys(aliases).join(', ')}); lineage findings will be skipped.`,\n    aliasKey: null,\n    canonicalKey,\n    coercedCount: 0,\n  });\n\n  return { registry, warnings };\n}\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 3. RESEARCH MERGE\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/**\n * Merge research findings registries from all lineages.\n * Deduplicates by findingId; cross-model attribution via lineage labels.\n * Returns the merged registry object.\n */\nfunction mergeResearchRegistries(lineageData, options = {}) {\n  const mergeOptions = resolveMergeOptions(options);\n  const findingById = mergeOptions.enableNearDuplicateDedup ? createFindingBucketIndex() : new Map();\n  const schemaWarnings = [];\n\n  for (const { label, registry: rawRegistry } of lineageData) {\n    const { registry, warnings } = normalizeRegistrySchema(rawRegistry, {\n      canonicalKey: 'keyFindings',\n      aliases: { findings: 'keyFindings' },\n      lineage: label,\n    });\n    for (const w of warnings) {\n      schemaWarnings.push(w);\n      process.stderr.write(JSON.stringify(w) + '\\n');\n    }\n    if (!registry || !Array.isArray(registry.keyFindings)) continue;\n    for (const finding of registry.keyFindings) {\n      const id = finding.id || finding.title;\n      if (!id) continue;\n      if (mergeOptions.enableNearDuplicateDedup) {\n        addResearchFinding(getFindingBucket(findingById, id, finding, true).records, finding, label, mergeOptions);\n      } else {\n        if (!findingById.has(id)) findingById.set(id, []);\n        addResearchFinding(findingById.get(id), finding, label, mergeOptions);\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  const mergedFindings = mergeOptions.enableNearDuplicateDedup\n    ? flattenFindingBucketIndex(findingById, 'id', ['id', 'title'])\n    : flattenFindingBuckets(findingById, 'id', ['id', 'title']);\n  const openQuestionsById = new Map();\n  const resolvedQuestionsById = new Map();\n  const ruledOutById = new Map();\n\n  for (const { label, registry } of lineageData) {\n    if (!registry) continue;\n    for (const q of registry.openQuestions ?? []) {\n      const id = q.id || q.question || q.text;\n      if (!id) continue;\n      if (!openQuestionsById.has(id)) openQuestionsById.set(id, { ...q, _lineages: [label] });\n      else {\n        const existing = openQuestionsById.get(id);\n        addLineage(existing, label);\n      }\n    }\n    // Resolved questions are produced per-lineage by the research reducer but\n    // were previously dropped here, under-reporting answered coverage in the\n    // merged registry. Collect them with the same id/_lineages discipline.\n    for (const q of registry.resolvedQuestions ?? []) {\n      const id = q.id || q.question || q.text;\n      if (!id) continue;\n      if (!resolvedQuestionsById.has(id)) resolvedQuestionsById.set(id, { ...q, _lineages: [label] });\n      else {\n        const existing = resolvedQuestionsById.get(id);\n        addLineage(existing, label);\n      }\n    }\n    for (const d of registry.ruledOutDirections ?? []) {\n      const id = d.id || d.direction;\n      if (!id) continue;\n      if (!ruledOutById.has(id)) ruledOutById.set(id, { ...d, _lineages: [label] });\n    }\n  }\n\n  const totalIters = lineageData.reduce((sum, { registry }) => {\n    return sum + (registry?.metrics?.iterationsCompleted ?? 0);\n  }, 0);\n\n  const avgConvergence =\n    lineageData.length > 0\n      ? lineageData.reduce((sum, { registry }) => sum + (registry?.metrics?.convergenceScore ?? 0), 0) /\n        lineageData.length\n      : 0;\n\n  return {\n    mergedFrom: lineageData.map(({ label }) => label).sort(),\n    openQuestions: sortByContentThenId([...openQuestionsById.values()], ['id', 'question', 'text']),\n    resolvedQuestions: sortByContentThenId([...resolvedQuestionsById.values()], ['id', 'question', 'text']),\n    keyFindings: mergedFindings,\n    ruledOutDirections: sortByContentThenId([...ruledOutById.values()], ['id', 'direction']),\n    metrics: {\n      iterationsCompleted: totalIters,\n      openQuestions: openQuestionsById.size,\n      resolvedQuestions: resolvedQuestionsById.size,\n      keyFindings: mergedFindings.length,\n      convergenceScore: Math.round(avgConvergence * 1000) / 1000,\n      coverageBySources: {},\n    },\n    ...(schemaWarnings.length > 0 ? { schema_mismatch: schemaWarnings } : {}),\n  };\n}\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 4. REVIEW MERGE  (strongest-restriction)\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/**\n * Merge review findings registries with strongest-restriction severity rollup.\n * Any lineage with an active P0 finding causes the merged result to be FAIL.\n * Deduplication is by findingId; cross-lineage P0 wins if any lineage reports it.\n */\nfunction mergeReviewRegistries(lineageData, options = {}) {\n  const mergeOptions = resolveMergeOptions(options);\n  const findingById = mergeOptions.enableNearDuplicateDedup ? createFindingBucketIndex() : new Map();\n  const schemaWarnings = [];\n\n  for (const { label, registry: rawRegistry } of lineageData) {\n    const { registry, warnings } = normalizeRegistrySchema(rawRegistry, {\n      canonicalKey: 'openFindings',\n      aliases: { findings: 'openFindings' },\n      lineage: label,\n    });\n    for (const w of warnings) {\n      schemaWarnings.push(w);\n      process.stderr.write(JSON.stringify(w) + '\\n');\n    }\n    if (!registry || !Array.isArray(registry.openFindings)) continue;\n    for (const finding of registry.openFindings) {\n      if (finding.status !== 'active') continue;\n      const id = finding.findingId || finding.title;\n      if (!id) continue;\n      if (mergeOptions.enableNearDuplicateDedup) {\n        addReviewFinding(getFindingBucket(findingById, id, finding, true).records, finding, label, mergeOptions);\n      } else {\n        if (!findingById.has(id)) findingById.set(id, []);\n        addReviewFinding(findingById.get(id), finding, label, mergeOptions);\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Resolved findings are tracked separately per lineage and were previously\n  // dropped here, zeroing the merged resolved coverage. Collect them by id with\n  // _lineages attribution, without touching open-finding/verdict semantics.\n  const resolvedFindingById = mergeOptions.enableNearDuplicateDedup ? createFindingBucketIndex() : new Map();\n  for (const { label, registry } of lineageData) {\n    if (!registry || !Array.isArray(registry.resolvedFindings)) continue;\n    for (const finding of registry.resolvedFindings) {\n      const id = finding.findingId || finding.title;\n      if (!id) continue;\n      if (mergeOptions.enableNearDuplicateDedup) {\n        addReviewFinding(getFindingBucket(resolvedFindingById, id, finding, true).records, finding, label, mergeOptions);\n      } else if (resolvedFindingById.has(id)) {\n        addLineage(resolvedFindingById.get(id), label);\n      } else {\n        resolvedFindingById.set(id, { ...finding, _lineages: [label] });\n      }\n    }\n  }\n  const mergedResolvedFindings = mergeOptions.enableNearDuplicateDedup\n    ? flattenFindingBucketIndex(resolvedFindingById, 'findingId', ['findingId', 'title'])\n    : sortByContentThenId([...resolvedFindingById.values()], ['findingId', 'title']);\n\n  const mergedFindings = mergeOptions.enableNearDuplicateDedup\n    ? flattenFindingBucketIndex(findingById, 'findingId', ['findingId', 'title'])\n    : flattenFindingBuckets(findingById, 'findingId', ['findingId', 'title']);\n  const activeP0 = mergedFindings.filter((f) => f.severity === 'P0' && f.status === 'active').length;\n  const activeP1 = mergedFindings.filter((f) => f.severity === 'P1' && f.status === 'active').length;\n  const activeP2 = mergedFindings.filter((f) => f.severity === 'P2' && f.status === 'active').length;\n\n  // Strongest-restriction verdict\n  let mergedVerdict;\n  if (activeP0 > 0) {\n    mergedVerdict = 'FAIL';\n  } else if (activeP1 > 0) {\n    mergedVerdict = 'CONDITIONAL';\n  } else {\n    mergedVerdict = 'PASS';\n  }\n\n  return {\n    mergedFrom: lineageData.map(({ label }) => label).sort(),\n    mergedVerdict,\n    openFindings: mergedFindings,\n    resolvedFindings: mergedResolvedFindings,\n    findingsBySeverity: { P0: activeP0, P1: activeP1, P2: activeP2 },\n    openFindingsCount: mergedFindings.length,\n    resolvedFindingsCount: mergedResolvedFindings.length,\n    activeP0,\n    activeP1,\n    activeP2,\n    ...(schemaWarnings.length > 0 ? { schema_mismatch: schemaWarnings } : {}),\n  };\n}\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 5. ATTRIBUTION\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/**\n * Build fanout-attribution.md summarizing per-lineage convergence, iters, salvage, model.\n */\nfunction buildAttributionMd(lineageData, loopType) {\n  const lines = [\n    `# Fan-Out Attribution`,\n    ``,\n    `Loop type: **${loopType}**  |  Lineage count: **${lineageData.length}**`,\n    ``,\n    `| Label | Kind | Model | Iterations | Convergence | Salvaged | Verdict |`,\n    `|-------|------|-------|-----------|-------------|----------|---------|`,\n  ];\n\n  for (const { label, registry, stateRecords, kind, model } of lineageData) {\n    const iters = stateRecords.filter((r) => r.type === 'iteration').length;\n    const salvage = stateRecords.filter((r) => r.type === 'event' && r.event === 'salvaged_from_stdout').length;\n    const convergenceScore = registry?.metrics?.convergenceScore ?? registry?.convergenceScore ?? 'n/a';\n    const verdict =\n      loopType === 'review'\n        ? registry?.findingsBySeverity?.P0 > 0\n          ? 'FAIL'\n          : registry?.findingsBySeverity?.P1 > 0\n          ? 'CONDITIONAL'\n          : 'PASS'\n        : 'n/a';\n    lines.push(`| ${label} | ${kind ?? 'unknown'} | ${model ?? 'default'} | ${iters} | ${convergenceScore} | ${salvage} | ${verdict} |`);\n  }\n\n  lines.push('');\n  return lines.join('\\n');\n}\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 6. MAIN\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/**\n * Reconstruct a minimal review findings registry from a lineage state log.\n *\n * Leaf-only review lineages may carry active findings only in their state log\n * iteration records (`findingDetails`), with no registry file on disk. This maps\n * those findingDetails into the openFindings shape mergeReviewRegistries consumes,\n * so registry-absent lineages are not silently dropped from merge/synthesis.\n *\n * @param {Array<Object>} stateRecords - Parsed JSONL state records.\n * @param {string} label - Lineage label, for attribution.\n * @returns {{openFindings:Array,Object}|null} Reconstructed registry, or null when no findings exist.\n */\nfunction reconstructReviewRegistryFromState(stateRecords, label) {\n  if (!Array.isArray(stateRecords)) return null;\n  const openFindings = [];\n  const resolvedFindings = [];\n  for (const record of stateRecords) {\n    if (!record || record.type !== 'iteration' || !Array.isArray(record.findingDetails)) continue;\n    for (const detail of record.findingDetails) {\n      if (!detail || typeof detail !== 'object') continue;\n      const id = detail.id || detail.findingId || detail.title;\n      if (!id) continue;\n      const isActive = (detail.disposition || detail.status || 'active') === 'active';\n      const mapped = {\n        findingId: id,\n        title: detail.title || id,\n        severity: detail.severity || 'P2',\n        status: isActive ? 'active' : 'resolved',\n        ...(detail.dimension ? { dimension: detail.dimension } : {}),\n        ...(detail.file ? { file: detail.file } : {}),\n        ...(detail.recommendation ? { recommendation: detail.recommendation } : {}),\n        _lineages: [label],\n        _reconstructed_from_state: true,\n      };\n      if (isActive) openFindings.push(mapped);\n      else resolvedFindings.push(mapped);\n    }\n  }\n  if (openFindings.length === 0 && resolvedFindings.length === 0) return null;\n  const bySeverity = {\n    P0: openFindings.filter((f) => f.severity === 'P0').length,\n    P1: openFindings.filter((f) => f.severity === 'P1').length,\n    P2: openFindings.filter((f) => f.severity === 'P2').length,\n  };\n  return { openFindings, resolvedFindings, findingsBySeverity: bySeverity, _reconstructed: true };\n}\n\nfunction firstNonEmptyString(values) {\n  for (const value of values) {\n    if (typeof value === 'string' && value.trim() !== '') return value.trim();\n    if (value && typeof value === 'object' && !Array.isArray(value)) {\n      const objectText = firstNonEmptyString([value.title, value.summary, value.text, value.finding, value.description]);\n      if (objectText) return objectText;\n    }\n  }\n  return '';\n}\n\nfunction normalizeResearchFindingCandidate(candidate, record, index) {\n  const run = Number.isFinite(Number(record.run ?? record.iteration)) ? Math.floor(Number(record.run ?? record.iteration)) : 0;\n  if (typeof candidate === 'string') {\n    const text = candidate.trim();\n    if (!text) return null;\n    return {\n      id: `state-finding-${run}-${index + 1}-${crypto.createHash('sha256').update(text).digest('hex').slice(0, 12)}`,\n      title: text,\n      text,\n      addedAtIteration: run,\n      _reconstructed_from_state: true,\n    };\n  }\n  if (!candidate || typeof candidate !== 'object' || Array.isArray(candidate)) return null;\n  const text = firstNonEmptyString([candidate.title, candidate.summary, candidate.text, candidate.finding, candidate.description]);\n  if (!text) return null;\n  return {\n    id: candidate.id || candidate.findingId || `state-finding-${run}-${index + 1}-${crypto.createHash('sha256').update(text).digest('hex').slice(0, 12)}`,\n    title: candidate.title || text,\n    ...(candidate.summary ? { summary: candidate.summary } : {}),\n    ...(candidate.text ? { text: candidate.text } : { text }),\n    ...(candidate.confidence ? { confidence: candidate.confidence } : {}),\n    addedAtIteration: candidate.addedAtIteration ?? run,\n    _reconstructed_from_state: true,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction researchCandidatesFromIteration(record) {\n  if (!record || record.type !== 'iteration') return [];\n  const structured = [record.keyFindings, record.findings, record.findingDetails]\n    .find((value) => Array.isArray(value) && value.length > 0);\n  if (Array.isArray(structured)) {\n    return structured;\n  }\n\n  const findingsCount = Number(record.findingsCount);\n  if (!Number.isFinite(findingsCount) || findingsCount <= 0) return [];\n  const run = Number.isFinite(Number(record.run ?? record.iteration)) ? Math.floor(Number(record.run ?? record.iteration)) : 0;\n  const narrative = firstNonEmptyString([\n    record.summary,\n    record.findingsSummary,\n    record.focus,\n    record.nextFocus,\n    record.reflection,\n  ]);\n  return [{\n    id: `state-finding-${run}-1-${crypto.createHash('sha256').update(narrative || String(run)).digest('hex').slice(0, 12)}`,\n    title: narrative || `Iteration ${run} recorded ${Math.floor(findingsCount)} finding(s)`,\n    summary: narrative || `State log recorded ${Math.floor(findingsCount)} finding(s) but no structured finding text.`,\n    addedAtIteration: run,\n  }];\n}\n\n/**\n * Reconstruct a minimal research findings registry from a lineage state log.\n *\n * Leaf-only research lineages may have substantive iteration records but no\n * registry file on disk. This maps state-log findings into keyFindings so the\n * research merge does not silently drop a registry-absent lineage.\n *\n * @param {Array<Object>} stateRecords - Parsed JSONL state records.\n * @param {string} label - Lineage label, for attribution.\n * @returns {{keyFindings:Array,Object}|null} Reconstructed registry, or null when no findings exist.\n */\nfunction reconstructResearchRegistryFromState(stateRecords, label) {\n  if (!Array.isArray(stateRecords)) return null;\n  const keyFindings = [];\n  for (const record of stateRecords) {\n    const candidates = researchCandidatesFromIteration(record);\n    candidates.forEach((candidate, index) => {\n      const mapped = normalizeResearchFindingCandidate(candidate, record, index);\n      if (!mapped) return;\n      keyFindings.push({ ...mapped, _lineages: [label] });\n    });\n  }\n  if (keyFindings.length === 0) return null;\n  const iterationsCompleted = stateRecords.filter((record) => record?.type === 'iteration').length;\n  const latestIteration = stateRecords.filter((record) => record?.type === 'iteration').at(-1);\n  const convergenceScore = latestIteration?.convergenceSignals?.compositeStop\n    ?? latestIteration?.newInfoRatio\n    ?? 0;\n  return {\n    keyFindings,\n    openQuestions: [],\n    resolvedQuestions: [],\n    ruledOutDirections: [],\n    metrics: {\n      iterationsCompleted,\n      openQuestions: 0,\n      resolvedQuestions: 0,\n      keyFindings: keyFindings.length,\n      convergenceScore,\n      coverageBySources: {},\n    },\n    _reconstructed: true,\n  };\n}\n\nasync function main() {\n  const { writeStateAtomic, writeTextAtomic } = await import('../lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts');\n  const args = parseArgs();\n  const loopType = ensureString(args, 'loopType');\n  if (loopType !== 'research' && loopType !== 'review' && loopType !== 'context') {\n    throw inputError('loopType must be \"research\", \"review\", or \"context\"');\n  }\n  const artifactDir = ensureString(args, 'artifactDir');\n  const lineagesDir = path.join(artifactDir, 'lineages');\n\n  if (!fs.existsSync(lineagesDir)) {\n    jsonOut({ status: 'ok', message: 'no lineages directory — nothing to merge', merged: 0 });\n    return;\n  }\n\n  const labelDirs = fs.readdirSync(lineagesDir)\n    .filter((entry) => fs.statSync(path.join(lineagesDir, entry)).isDirectory())\n    .sort();\n\n  if (labelDirs.length === 0) {\n    jsonOut({ status: 'ok', message: 'no lineage subdirs found', merged: 0 });\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Load per-lineage data\n  const registryName =\n    loopType === 'review' ? 'deep-review-findings-registry.json' : 'deep-research-findings-registry.json';\n  const stateLogName = loopType === 'review' ? 'deep-review-state.jsonl' : 'deep-research-state.jsonl';\n  const summaryPath = path.join(artifactDir, 'orchestration-summary.json');\n  const orchestrationSummary = tryReadJson(summaryPath) ?? {};\n\n  const lineageData = labelDirs.map((label) => {\n    const lineageDir = path.join(lineagesDir, label);\n    let registry = tryReadJson(path.join(lineageDir, registryName));\n    const stateRecords = readStateLog(path.join(lineageDir, stateLogName));\n    // Leaf-only review/research lineages (orchestrator-managed direct-leaf convention) may carry\n    // active findings only in their state log's findingDetails, with no registry file.\n    // Without a registry, such a lineage was silently skipped by the registry-only merge,\n    // dropping its findings from synthesis. Reconstruct a minimal registry from the\n    // state log so leaf-only lineages reach merge without a separate reducer step.\n    if (!registry && loopType === 'review') {\n      registry = reconstructReviewRegistryFromState(stateRecords, label);\n    }\n    if (!registry && loopType === 'research') {\n      registry = reconstructResearchRegistryFromState(stateRecords, label);\n    }\n    // Infer kind/model from state log executor records\n    const executorRecord = stateRecords.find((r) => r.type === 'event' && r.event === 'executor_start');\n    return {\n      label,\n      lineageDir,\n      registry,\n      stateRecords,\n      kind: executorRecord?.kind ?? orchestrationSummary?.[label]?.kind ?? 'unknown',\n      model: executorRecord?.model ?? orchestrationSummary?.[label]?.model ?? 'unknown',\n    };\n  });\n\n  const lineagesWithRegistry = lineageData.filter((d) => d.registry !== null);\n\n  let mergedRegistry;\n  if (loopType === 'review') {\n    mergedRegistry = mergeReviewRegistries(lineagesWithRegistry, resolveMergeOptions(args));\n  } else {\n    mergedRegistry = mergeResearchRegistries(lineagesWithRegistry, resolveMergeOptions(args));\n  }\n\n  // Write merged registry to base artifact dir (replacing single-executor path).\n  // Atomic temp+fsync+rename so a mid-write kill never hands synthesis a\n  // truncated registry — readers see the prior file or the complete new one.\n  const mergedRegistryPath = path.join(artifactDir, registryName);\n  writeStateAtomic(mergedRegistryPath, mergedRegistry);\n\n  // Write attribution markdown atomically (same torn-write guarantee; text, not JSON).\n  const attributionPath = path.join(artifactDir, 'fanout-attribution.md');\n  writeTextAtomic(attributionPath, buildAttributionMd(lineageData, loopType));\n\n  jsonOut({\n    status: 'ok',\n    loop_type: loopType,\n    merged_lineages: lineagesWithRegistry.length,\n    skipped_no_registry: lineageData.length - lineagesWithRegistry.length,\n    merged_registry_path: mergedRegistryPath,\n    attribution_path: attributionPath,\n    ...(loopType === 'review'\n      ? { merged_verdict: mergedRegistry.mergedVerdict, active_p0: mergedRegistry.activeP0, active_p1: mergedRegistry.activeP1 }\n      : { key_findings: mergedRegistry.keyFindings?.length ?? 0 }),\n  });\n}\n\n// Exports for unit testing\nmodule.exports = { mergeResearchRegistries, mergeReviewRegistries, buildAttributionMd, reconstructReviewRegistryFromState, reconstructResearchRegistryFromState, normalizeRegistrySchema };\n\nif (require.main === module) {\n  main().catch((err) => {\n    const code = err && err.code === 'INPUT_VALIDATION' ? 3 : 1;\n    jsonOut({\n      status: 'error',\n      error: err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err),\n      code: err && err.code ? err.code : 'SCRIPT_ERROR',\n    });\n    if (code === 1) {\n      process.stderr.write(\n        JSON.stringify({ error: err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err), stack: err && err.stack }) + '\\n',\n      );\n    }\n    process.exit(code);\n  });\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":1014,"totalLines":1014,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs","time":{"start":1784691892234,"end":1784691892259}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0c2ff4dd619f1f4b016a603cb4272081918e7a0bd735531a98"}},"id":"prt_f87ed20050011AtIMfJsXix1p0","sessionID":"ses_07813ae6bffeXSfNUcMKmjadEz","messageID":"msg_f87ecf9df001hwbObtyOL00KA7"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784691892280,"sessionID":"ses_07813ae6bffeXSfNUcMKmjadEz","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_RtswKGOrkhruKQb02q6KpS3t","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs","offset":1,"limit":2400},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: #!/usr/bin/env node\n2: \n3: // ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n4: // ║ Deep-Loop Runtime — Fan-Out CLI Lineage Pool Runner                      ║\n5: // ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n6: // ║ Input:  CLI args (--spec-folder, --loop-type, --fanout-config-json,      ║\n7: // ║         --base-artifact-dir).                                            ║\n8: // ║ Output: JSON to stdout.                                                  ║\n9: // ║ Exit:   0=all ok, 1=script error, 2=some failed, 3=all failed.          ║\n10: // ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n11: \n12: 'use strict';\n13: \n14: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n15: // 1. IMPORTS\n16: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n17: \n18: const fs = require('node:fs');\n19: const os = require('node:os');\n20: const path = require('node:path');\n21: const { spawn, spawnSync } = require('node:child_process');\n22: const { createHash } = require('node:crypto');\n23: \n24: const {\n25:   classifyExitCode,\n26:   maybeThrowTestFault,\n27:   validateNamespaceValue,\n28: } = require('./lib/cli-guards.cjs');\n29: \n30: const {\n31:   runCappedPool,\n32:   appendStatusLedger,\n33:   markOrphanedLineages,\n34:   readRetryCountsFromLedger,\n35:   createWavePlannerInterface,\n36:   writeOrchestrationSummary,\n37: } = require('./fanout-pool.cjs');\n38: \n39: const {\n40:   runSalvageSweep,\n41:   extractTextFromOpencodeJson,\n42: } = require('./fanout-salvage.cjs');\n43: \n44: const {\n45:   appendObservabilityEvent,\n46: } = require('../lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs');\n47: \n48: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n49: // 2. TSX BOOTSTRAP\n50: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n51: \n52: const TSX_LOADER = require.resolve('tsx');\n53: const isTsxLoaded = process.env.DEEP_LOOP_TSX_LOADED === '1';\n54: \n55: function runTsxBootstrap() {\n56:   const child = spawn(\n57:     process.execPath,\n58:     ['--import', TSX_LOADER, __filename, ...process.argv.slice(2)],\n59:     {\n60:       cwd: process.cwd(),\n61:       env: { ...process.env, DEEP_LOOP_TSX_LOADED: '1' },\n62:       stdio: [process.stdin.isTTY ? 'ignore' : 'pipe', 'pipe', 'pipe'],\n63:     },\n64:   );\n65: \n66:   if (!process.stdin.isTTY && child.stdin) {\n67:     child.stdin.on('error', () => {});\n68:     process.stdin.pipe(child.stdin);\n69:   }\n70: \n71:   child.stdout?.pipe(process.stdout);\n72:   child.stderr?.pipe(process.stderr);\n73: \n74:   for (const signal of ['SIGINT', 'SIGTERM']) {\n75:     process.once(signal, () => {\n76:       child.kill(signal);\n77:     });\n78:   }\n79: \n80:   child.on('close', (status, signal) => {\n81:     if (status !== null) {\n82:       process.exit(status);\n83:     }\n84:     process.exit(signal === 'SIGINT' ? 130 : signal === 'SIGTERM' ? 143 : 1);\n85:   });\n86: }\n87: \n88: if (require.main === module && !isTsxLoaded) {\n89:   runTsxBootstrap();\n90: }\n91: \n92: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n93: // 3. HELPERS\n94: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n95: \n96: function parseArgs(argv = process.argv.slice(2)) {\n97:   const args = {};\n98:   for (let i = 0; i < argv.length; i += 1) {\n99:     const token = argv[i];\n100:     if (!token.startsWith('--')) {\n101:       throw inputError(`Unexpected positional argument: ${token}`);\n102:     }\n103:     const key = token.slice(2).replace(/-([a-z])/g, (_, c) => c.toUpperCase());\n104:     const next = argv[i + 1];\n105:     if (next === undefined || next.startsWith('--')) {\n106:       args[key] = true;\n107:     } else {\n108:       args[key] = next;\n109:       i += 1;\n110:     }\n111:   }\n112:   return args;\n113: }\n114: \n115: function inputError(message) {\n116:   const err = new Error(message);\n117:   err.code = 'INPUT_VALIDATION';\n118:   return err;\n119: }\n120: \n121: function ensureString(args, key) {\n122:   if (!args[key] || typeof args[key] !== 'string') {\n123:     throw inputError(`${key} is required`);\n124:   }\n125:   return args[key];\n126: }\n127: \n128: function parseOptionalNumber(args, key) {\n129:   const raw = args[key];\n130:   if (raw === undefined || raw === false || raw === null || raw === '') {\n131:     return null;\n132:   }\n133:   if (raw === true || typeof raw !== 'string') {\n134:     throw inputError(`${key} must be a number`);\n135:   }\n136:   const value = Number(raw);\n137:   if (!Number.isFinite(value) || value < 0) {\n138:     throw inputError(`${key} must be a non-negative number`);\n139:   }\n140:   return value;\n141: }\n142: \n143: function readRawConfigNumber(rawConfig, names, fieldName) {\n144:   if (!isRecord(rawConfig)) return null;\n145:   for (const name of names) {\n146:     if (!Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(rawConfig, name)) continue;\n147:     const raw = rawConfig[name];\n148:     if (raw === undefined || raw === null || raw === '') return null;\n149:     if (raw === true || raw === false) {\n150:       throw inputError(`${fieldName} must be a non-negative number`);\n151:     }\n152:     const value = Number(raw);\n153:     if (!Number.isFinite(value) || value < 0) {\n154:       throw inputError(`${fieldName} must be a non-negative number`);\n155:     }\n156:     return Math.floor(value);\n157:   }\n158:   return null;\n159: }\n160: \n161: function readPositiveRawConfigNumber(rawConfig, names, fieldName, fallback) {\n162:   const value = readRawConfigNumber(rawConfig, names, fieldName);\n163:   if (value === null) return fallback;\n164:   if (value <= 0) {\n165:     throw inputError(`${fieldName} must be greater than 0`);\n166:   }\n167:   return value;\n168: }\n169: \n170: function rawConfigWithCliBudgetOverrides(rawConfig, args) {\n171:   const merged = { ...(isRecord(rawConfig) ? rawConfig : {}) };\n172:   const mappings = [\n173:     ['stallWatchdogMs', 'stallWatchdogMs'],\n174:     ['maxCostUnitsPerLineage', 'maxCostUnitsPerLineage'],\n175:     ['maxAggregateCostUnits', 'maxAggregateCostUnits'],\n176:     ['maxTokensPerLineage', 'maxTokensPerLineage'],\n177:     ['maxTokenBudget', 'maxTokenBudget'],\n178:     ['maxTokenBudgetPerLineage', 'maxTokenBudgetPerLineage'],\n179:     ['costUnitsPerIteration', 'costUnitsPerIteration'],\n180:     ['estimatedTokensPerIteration', 'estimatedTokensPerIteration'],\n181:   ];\n182:   for (const [targetKey, argKey] of mappings) {\n183:     if (Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(args, argKey)) {\n184:       merged[targetKey] = args[argKey];\n185:     }\n186:   }\n187:   return merged;\n188: }\n189: \n190: function normalizeStopPolicy(raw) {\n191:   if (raw === undefined || raw === false || raw === null || raw === '') {\n192:     return 'convergence';\n193:   }\n194:   if (raw === true || typeof raw !== 'string') {\n195:     throw inputError('stopPolicy must be convergence or max-iterations');\n196:   }\n197:   if (raw !== 'convergence' && raw !== 'max-iterations') {\n198:     throw inputError('stopPolicy must be convergence or max-iterations');\n199:   }\n200:   return raw;\n201: }\n202: \n203: function jsonOut(payload) {\n204:   process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(payload)}\\n`);\n205: }\n206: \n207: function signalExitCode(signal) {\n208:   return signal === 'SIGINT' ? 130 : 143;\n209: }\n210: \n211: let fanoutSignalHandlersInstalled = false;\n212: \n213: function installFanoutSignalHandlers(onStop) {\n214:   if (fanoutSignalHandlersInstalled) return;\n215:   fanoutSignalHandlersInstalled = true;\n216: \n217:   for (const signal of ['SIGINT', 'SIGTERM']) {\n218:     process.once(signal, () => {\n219:       try {\n220:         onStop(signal);\n221:       } finally {\n222:         process.exit(signalExitCode(signal));\n223:       }\n224:     });\n225:   }\n226: }\n227: \n228: function updateLineageSnapshot(snapshots, event) {\n229:   if (!event || typeof event.label !== 'string') return;\n230:   const existing = snapshots.get(event.label) || { label: event.label };\n231: \n232:   if (event.event === 'started') {\n233:     snapshots.set(event.label, { ...existing, status: 'running', started_at_iso: event.at });\n234:     return;\n235:   }\n236:   if (event.event === 'completed') {\n237:     snapshots.set(event.label, {\n238:       ...existing,\n239:       status: 'fulfilled',\n240:       completed_at_iso: event.at,\n241:       duration_ms: event.duration_ms,\n242:     });\n243:     return;\n244:   }\n245:   if (event.event === 'failed') {\n246:     snapshots.set(event.label, {\n247:       ...existing,\n248:       status: event.terminal === false ? 'retrying' : 'rejected',\n249:       completed_at_iso: event.at,\n250:       duration_ms: event.duration_ms,\n251:       error: event.error,\n252:     });\n253:     return;\n254:   }\n255:   if (event.event === 'retry_scheduled' || event.event === 'orphan_requeued') {\n256:     snapshots.set(event.label, { ...existing, status: 'requeued', updated_at_iso: event.at });\n257:     return;\n258:   }\n259:   if (event.event === 'progress') {\n260:     snapshots.set(event.label, {\n261:       ...existing,\n262:       status: 'running',\n263:       updated_at_iso: event.at,\n264:       duration_ms: event.duration_ms,\n265:     });\n266:   }\n267: }\n268: \n269: function buildLineageSnapshots(lineages, snapshots) {\n270:   return lineages.map((lineage) => snapshots.get(lineage.label) || { label: lineage.label, status: 'pending' });\n271: }\n272: \n273: function summarizeSnapshots(lineages, snapshots) {\n274:   const results = buildLineageSnapshots(lineages, snapshots);\n275:   const succeeded = results.filter((result) => result.status === 'fulfilled').length;\n276:   const failed = results.filter((result) => result.status === 'rejected').length;\n277:   return {\n278:     results,\n279:     summary: {\n280:       total: lineages.length,\n281:       succeeded,\n282:       failed,\n283:       all_failed: lineages.length > 0 && failed === lineages.length,\n284:     },\n285:   };\n286: }\n287: \n288: function observabilityPathForLedger(ledgerPath) {\n289:   return path.join(path.dirname(ledgerPath), OBSERVABILITY_EVENTS_FILENAME);\n290: }\n291: \n292: function statusForLedgerEvent(entry) {\n293:   if (entry && typeof entry.status === 'string' && entry.status.trim() !== '') {\n294:     return entry.status;\n295:   }\n296:   if (!entry || typeof entry.event !== 'string') return 'unknown';\n297:   if (entry.event === 'started' || entry.event === 'progress' || entry.event === 'resume_waiting') return 'running';\n298:   if (entry.event === 'completed' || entry.event === 'resume_waiting_complete') return 'completed';\n299:   if (entry.event === 'failed') return entry.terminal === false ? 'retrying' : 'failed';\n300:   if (entry.event === 'stopped') return 'stopped';\n301:   if (entry.event === 'retry_scheduled' || entry.event === 'orphan_requeued') return 'retrying';\n302:   // Lag-ceiling signals from the pool: a stall warning while work remains pending, or a\n303:   // forced abort of the stalled attempt. Map both to typed statuses instead of 'unknown'.\n304:   if (entry.event === 'lag_ceiling_exceeded') return entry.action === 'abort' ? 'failed' : 'warning';\n305:   if (entry.event === 'lag_ceiling_abort') return 'failed';\n306:   if (entry.event === 'stall_detected') return 'warning';\n307:   if (entry.event === 'budget_cap_exceeded') return 'failed';\n308:   if (entry.event === 'aggregate_budget_cap_exceeded') return 'failed';\n309:   return 'unknown';\n310: }\n311: \n312: function appendFanoutStatusLedger(ledgerPath, entry) {\n313:   appendStatusLedger(ledgerPath, entry);\n314:   try {\n315:     appendObservabilityEvent(observabilityPathForLedger(ledgerPath), entry, {\n316:       producer: 'fanout-run',\n317:       stream: 'orchestration-status',\n318:       subject: {\n319:         run_id: entry.run_id ?? null,\n320:         label: entry.label ?? null,\n321:         loop_type: entry.loop_type ?? null,\n322:         spec_folder: entry.spec_folder ?? null,\n323:       },\n324:       event: entry.event,\n325:       status: statusForLedgerEvent(entry),\n326:     });\n327:   } catch {\n328:     // Observability must not make the primary orchestration ledger fail.\n329:   }\n330: }\n331: \n332: const FLAT_POOL_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL = 'flat_pool';\n333: const WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL = 'wave';\n334: const WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL_REJECTION = 'REJECTED: wave assignment_model requires conflict-safety substrate';\n335: const WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_METADATA_REJECTION = 'REJECTED: wave assignment metadata requires conflict-safety substrate';\n336: const STATE_LOG_BY_LOOP_TYPE = {\n337:   research: 'deep-research-state.jsonl',\n338:   review: 'deep-review-state.jsonl',\n339: };\n340: const ACTIVE_FANOUT_LOOP_TYPES = new Set(['research', 'review']);\n341: const DEPRECATED_CONTEXT_FANOUT_MESSAGE = 'loopType must be \"research\" or \"review\"; context fan-out is deprecated. Use @context for one-shot retrieval, /deep:research or /deep:review bounded snapshots for iterative work, or /speckit:plan for implementation planning.';\n342: \n343: function assertActiveFanoutLoopType(loopType) {\n344:   if (!ACTIVE_FANOUT_LOOP_TYPES.has(loopType)) {\n345:     throw inputError(DEPRECATED_CONTEXT_FANOUT_MESSAGE);\n346:   }\n347: }\n348: \n349: function hasNonEmptyArrayField(value) {\n350:   return Array.isArray(value) && value.length > 0;\n351: }\n352: \n353: function collectFlatPoolGuardRejections(fanoutConfig) {\n354:   const rejections = [];\n355:   if (fanoutConfig.assignment_model === WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL) {\n356:     rejections.push({\n357:       scope: 'fanout',\n358:       label: null,\n359:       field: 'assignment_model',\n360:       message: WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL_REJECTION,\n361:     });\n362:   }\n363: \n364:   for (const lineage of fanoutConfig.executors) {\n365:     if (lineage.assignment_model === WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL) {\n366:       rejections.push({\n367:         scope: 'lineage',\n368:         label: lineage.label,\n369:         field: 'assignment_model',\n370:         message: WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL_REJECTION,\n371:       });\n372:     }\n373: \n374:     const reservedFields = [];\n375:     if (hasNonEmptyArrayField(lineage.depends_on)) {\n376:       reservedFields.push('depends_on');\n377:     }\n378:     if (hasNonEmptyArrayField(lineage.touches)) {\n379:       reservedFields.push('touches');\n380:     }\n381:     if (reservedFields.length > 0) {\n382:       rejections.push({\n383:         scope: 'lineage',\n384:         label: lineage.label,\n385:         field: reservedFields.join(','),\n386:         message: WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_METADATA_REJECTION,\n387:       });\n388:     }\n389:   }\n390: \n391:   return rejections;\n392: }\n393: \n394: /**\n395:  * Force fan-out execution onto the existing flat pool while wave planning is gated.\n396:  *\n397:  * @param {Object} fanoutConfig - Parsed fan-out config.\n398:  * @returns {{ config: Object, rejections: Array<Object> }} Guarded config and rejection records.\n399:  */\n400: function applyFlatPoolAssignmentGuard(fanoutConfig) {\n401:   const rejections = collectFlatPoolGuardRejections(fanoutConfig);\n402:   return {\n403:     config: {\n404:       ...fanoutConfig,\n405:       assignment_model: FLAT_POOL_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL,\n406:       executors: fanoutConfig.executors.map((lineage) => ({\n407:         ...lineage,\n408:         assignment_model: FLAT_POOL_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL,\n409:       })),\n410:     },\n411:     rejections,\n412:   };\n413: }\n414: \n415: function logFlatPoolGuardRejections({ rejections, ledgerPath, runId, loopType, specFolder }) {\n416:   if (rejections.length === 0) {\n417:     return;\n418:   }\n419:   const wavePlanner = createWavePlannerInterface();\n420:   for (const rejection of rejections) {\n421:     const labelSuffix = rejection.label ? ` lineage=${rejection.label}` : '';\n422:     process.stderr.write(`[fanout-run] ${rejection.message}${labelSuffix}\\n`);\n423:     appendFanoutStatusLedger(ledgerPath, {\n424:       event: 'assignment_model_rejected',\n425:       severity: 'warning',\n426:       at: new Date().toISOString(),\n427:       run_id: runId,\n428:       loop_type: loopType,\n429:       spec_folder: specFolder,\n430:       planner_status: wavePlanner.status,\n431:       fallback_assignment_model: FLAT_POOL_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL,\n432:       ...rejection,\n433:     });\n434:   }\n435: }\n436: \n437: // Per-kind first state-dir env var (used for lockfile isolation across same-kind replicas).\n438: const SPECKIT_STATE_ENV_BY_KIND = {\n439:   'cli-codex': 'SPECKIT_CODEX_STATE_DIR',\n440:   'cli-claude-code': 'SPECKIT_CLAUDE_CODE_STATE_DIR',\n441:   'cli-opencode': 'SPECKIT_OPENCODE_STATE_DIR',\n442: };\n443: \n444: const activeLineageProcesses = new Set();\n445: const WAIT_CHECKPOINT_FILENAME = 'orchestration-wait-checkpoint.json';\n446: const WAIT_CHECKPOINT_SCHEMA_VERSION = 1;\n447: const WAIT_SLEEP_CHUNK_MS = 200;\n448: const OBSERVABILITY_EVENTS_FILENAME = 'observability-events.jsonl';\n449: const DEFAULT_POST_EXIT_GRACE_MS = 5 * 60 * 1000;\n450: \n451: function stopActiveLineageProcesses(signal) {\n452:   for (const child of activeLineageProcesses) {\n453:     terminateLineageProcess(child, signal);\n454:   }\n455: }\n456: \n457: function expandHomeDir(inputPath) {\n458:   if (inputPath === '~') {\n459:     return os.homedir();\n460:   }\n461:   if (typeof inputPath === 'string' && inputPath.startsWith('~/')) {\n462:     return path.join(os.homedir(), inputPath.slice(2));\n463:   }\n464:   return inputPath;\n465: }\n466: \n467: function isPathInside(childPath, parentPath) {\n468:   const relative = path.relative(parentPath, childPath);\n469:   return relative === '' || (!relative.startsWith('..') && !path.isAbsolute(relative));\n470: }\n471: \n472: function physicalPathForValidation(targetPath) {\n473:   try {\n474:     return fs.realpathSync.native(targetPath);\n475:   } catch {\n476:     const parentPath = path.dirname(targetPath);\n477:     try {\n478:       return path.join(fs.realpathSync.native(parentPath), path.basename(targetPath));\n479:     } catch {\n480:       return targetPath;\n481:     }\n482:   }\n483: }\n484: \n485: function validateBaseArtifactDir(baseArtifactDir, specFolder, loopType) {\n486:   if (baseArtifactDir.includes('\\0')) {\n487:     throw inputError('baseArtifactDir must not contain null bytes');\n488:   }\n489:   if (baseArtifactDir.split(/[\\\\/]+/).includes('..')) {\n490:     throw inputError('baseArtifactDir must not contain \"..\" path segments');\n491:   }\n492:   const resolvedBase = physicalPathForValidation(path.resolve(process.cwd(), baseArtifactDir));\n493:   const resolvedSpecFolder = physicalPathForValidation(path.resolve(process.cwd(), specFolder));\n494:   const expectedRoot = path.join(resolvedSpecFolder, loopType);\n495:   if (!isPathInside(resolvedBase, expectedRoot)) {\n496:     throw inputError(`baseArtifactDir must resolve inside the spec folder's ${loopType} artifact tree`);\n497:   }\n498:   return baseArtifactDir;\n499: }\n500: \n501: function validateClaudeConfigDir(configDir) {\n502:   if (typeof configDir !== 'string' || configDir.trim() === '') {\n503:     throw inputError('configDir must be a non-empty string when set');\n504:   }\n505:   validateNamespaceValue(configDir, 'configDir', inputError);\n506: \n507:   const expanded = expandHomeDir(configDir);\n508:   const resolved = path.resolve(process.cwd(), expanded);\n509:   const homeDir = path.resolve(os.homedir());\n510:   const cwd = path.resolve(process.cwd());\n511:   const homeRelative = path.relative(homeDir, resolved);\n512:   const cwdRelative = path.relative(cwd, resolved);\n513:   const homeTop = homeRelative.split(path.sep)[0] || '';\n514:   const cwdTop = cwdRelative.split(path.sep)[0] || '';\n515:   const allowedConfigRoot = (segment) => segment === '.claude' || segment.startsWith('.claude-');\n516: \n517:   if (isPathInside(resolved, homeDir) && allowedConfigRoot(homeTop)) {\n518:     return resolved;\n519:   }\n520:   if (isPathInside(resolved, cwd) && allowedConfigRoot(cwdTop)) {\n521:     return resolved;\n522:   }\n523:   throw inputError('configDir must resolve under ~/.claude*, or a repo-local .claude* directory');\n524: }\n525: \n526: function terminateLineageProcess(child, signal) {\n527:   if (!child || child.killed) return;\n528:   if (process.platform !== 'win32' && child.pid) {\n529:     try {\n530:       process.kill(-child.pid, signal);\n531:       return;\n532:     } catch (error) {\n533:       if (error && error.code !== 'ESRCH') {\n534:         try {\n535:           child.kill(signal);\n536:         } catch {\n537:           // The process may have already exited between the group and direct kill attempts.\n538:         }\n539:       }\n540:       return;\n541:     }\n542:   }\n543:   try {\n544:     child.kill(signal);\n545:   } catch {\n546:     // The process may have already exited.\n547:   }\n548: }\n549: \n550: function expectedLineageArtifactPaths(loopType, lineageDir) {\n551:   assertActiveFanoutLoopType(loopType);\n552:   if (loopType === 'review') return [path.join(lineageDir, 'review-report.md')];\n553:   return [path.join(lineageDir, 'research.md')];\n554: }\n555: \n556: function hasNonEmptyFile(filePath) {\n557:   try {\n558:     return fs.statSync(filePath).isFile() && fs.statSync(filePath).size > 0;\n559:   } catch {\n560:     return false;\n561:   }\n562: }\n563: \n564: function findMissingLineageArtifacts(loopType, lineageDir) {\n565:   return expectedLineageArtifactPaths(loopType, lineageDir)\n566:     .filter((artifactPath) => !hasNonEmptyFile(artifactPath));\n567: }\n568: \n569: function parseJsonlRecords(filePath) {\n570:   const text = fs.readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8');\n571:   return text\n572:     .split(/\\r?\\n/)\n573:     .filter((line) => line.trim() !== '')\n574:     .map((line) => JSON.parse(line));\n575: }\n576: \n577: function lineageStateLogName(loopType) {\n578:   return STATE_LOG_BY_LOOP_TYPE[loopType] || null;\n579: }\n580: \n581: function readLineageStateRecords(loopType, lineageDir) {\n582:   const stateLogName = lineageStateLogName(loopType);\n583:   if (!stateLogName) {\n584:     return { statePath: null, records: [], missing: true, parseError: null };\n585:   }\n586:   const statePath = path.join(lineageDir, stateLogName);\n587:   if (!hasNonEmptyFile(statePath)) {\n588:     return { statePath, records: [], missing: true, parseError: null };\n589:   }\n590:   try {\n591:     return { statePath, records: parseJsonlRecords(statePath), missing: false, parseError: null };\n592:   } catch (error) {\n593:     return {\n594:       statePath,\n595:       records: [],\n596:       missing: false,\n597:       parseError: error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error),\n598:     };\n599:   }\n600: }\n601: \n602: // A lineage's synthesis stopReason is written by its model and cannot be held to an exact\n603: // spelling. The iteration-count check above already proves the lineage ran every iteration,\n604: // so this only needs to confirm the reason belongs to the max-iterations family (e.g.\n605: // \"maxIterationsReached\", \"max-iterations (10/10)\") and is not a genuinely different outcome\n606: // such as convergence, a manual stop, or an error.\n607: function isMaxIterationsStopReason(stopReason) {\n608:   if (typeof stopReason !== 'string') return false;\n609:   return stopReason.toLowerCase().replace(/[^a-z]/g, '').startsWith('maxiteration');\n610: }\n611: \n612: function findMaxIterationsPolicyViolation({ loopType, stateRead, lineage, stopPolicy }) {\n613:   if (loopType !== 'review' || stopPolicy !== 'max-iterations') return null;\n614:   if (typeof lineage.iterations !== 'number' || lineage.iterations <= 0) {\n615:     return 'stopPolicy=max-iterations requires a positive lineage iteration cap';\n616:   }\n617: \n618:   if (!stateRead || stateRead.missing) {\n619:     return 'missing deep-review-state.jsonl for max-iterations stop-policy validation';\n620:   }\n621:   if (stateRead.parseError) {\n622:     return `could not parse deep-review-state.jsonl: ${stateRead.parseError}`;\n623:   }\n624: \n625:   const records = stateRead.records;\n626:   const iterationCount = records.filter((record) => record && record.type === 'iteration').length;\n627:   const synthesis = [...records]\n628:     .reverse()\n629:     .find((record) => record && record.type === 'event' && record.event === 'synthesis_complete');\n630:   if (!synthesis) {\n631:     return 'missing synthesis_complete event for max-iterations stop-policy validation';\n632:   }\n633: \n634:   const totalIterations = Number.isFinite(Number(synthesis.totalIterations))\n635:     ? Number(synthesis.totalIterations)\n636:     : iterationCount;\n637:   if (totalIterations !== lineage.iterations) {\n638:     return `expected ${lineage.iterations} iterations, got ${totalIterations}`;\n639:   }\n640:   if (!isMaxIterationsStopReason(synthesis.stopReason)) {\n641:     return `expected stopReason=maxIterationsReached, got ${synthesis.stopReason || 'unknown'}`;\n642:   }\n643:   return null;\n644: }\n645: \n646: function isRecord(value) {\n647:   return value !== null && typeof value === 'object' && !Array.isArray(value);\n648: }\n649: \n650: function normalizeStallWatchdogMs(rawConfig) {\n651:   // Defaults ON (mirrors the fan-out lagCeilingMs default): without a watchdog a stalled\n652:   // lineage hangs silently until the hours-scale timeout. Read through the raw alias set\n653:   // because this knob is intentionally outside fanoutConfigSchema. Non-disableable while\n654:   // running autonomously: an explicit 0 no longer opts out, it is rejected.\n655:   const value = readRawConfigNumber(rawConfig, [\n656:     'stallWatchdogMs',\n657:     'stall_watchdog_ms',\n658:     'stallWatchdogMillis',\n659:     'stall_watchdog_millis',\n660:   ], 'stallWatchdogMs');\n661:   if (value === 0) {\n662:     throw inputError('stallWatchdogMs must be greater than 0; stall detection cannot be disabled for autonomous fan-out runs');\n663:   }\n664:   return value ?? 300000;\n665: }\n666: \n667: const DEFAULT_MAX_COST_UNITS_PER_LINEAGE = 72;\n668: \n669: function normalizeLineageBudgetGuards(rawConfig = {}) {\n670:   return {\n671:     max_cost_units_per_lineage: readRawConfigNumber(rawConfig, [\n672:       'maxCostUnitsPerLineage',\n673:       'max_cost_units_per_lineage',\n674:       'maxLineageCostUnits',\n675:       'max_lineage_cost_units',\n676:       'maxTokensPerLineage',\n677:       'max_tokens_per_lineage',\n678:       'maxTokenBudget',\n679:       'max_token_budget',\n680:       'maxTokenBudgetPerLineage',\n681:       'max_token_budget_per_lineage',\n682:     ], 'maxCostUnitsPerLineage') ?? DEFAULT_MAX_COST_UNITS_PER_LINEAGE,\n683:     cost_units_per_iteration: readPositiveRawConfigNumber(rawConfig, [\n684:       'costUnitsPerIteration',\n685:       'cost_units_per_iteration',\n686:       'estimatedTokensPerIteration',\n687:       'estimated_tokens_per_iteration',\n688:     ], 'costUnitsPerIteration', 1),\n689:   };\n690: }\n691: \n692: function computeLineageBudgetUpperBound(lineage, guardsInput = {}, maxRetries = 0) {\n693:   const guards = normalizeLineageBudgetGuards(guardsInput);\n694:   const rawIterations = Number(lineage && lineage.iterations);\n695:   const iterations = Number.isFinite(rawIterations) && rawIterations > 0 ? Math.floor(rawIterations) : 12;\n696:   const normalizedRetries = Number.isFinite(Number(maxRetries)) && Number(maxRetries) >= 0\n697:     ? Math.floor(Number(maxRetries))\n698:     : 0;\n699:   const totalAttempts = normalizedRetries + 1;\n700:   return {\n701:     ...guards,\n702:     iterations,\n703:     total_attempts: totalAttempts,\n704:     estimated_cost_units: iterations * guards.cost_units_per_iteration * totalAttempts,\n705:   };\n706: }\n707: \n708: function evaluateLineageBudgetCap(input = {}) {\n709:   const upperBound = computeLineageBudgetUpperBound(\n710:     input.lineage || {},\n711:     input.guards || input,\n712:     input.maxRetries,\n713:   );\n714:   const exceeded = upperBound.max_cost_units_per_lineage > 0\n715:     && upperBound.estimated_cost_units > upperBound.max_cost_units_per_lineage;\n716:   return {\n717:     continue_allowed: !exceeded,\n718:     stop_reasons: exceeded ? ['max_cost_units_per_lineage'] : [],\n719:     upper_bound: upperBound,\n720:   };\n721: }\n722: \n723: // Aggregate budget across every expanded lineage in a run. This is a SEPARATE ceiling\n724: // from DEFAULT_MAX_COST_UNITS_PER_LINEAGE above: the per-lineage cap bounds any single\n725: // lineage, this bounds the whole fan-out submission, and both are enforced independently\n726: // (a run may pass one and still fail the other).\n727: const DEFAULT_MAX_AGGREGATE_COST_UNITS = 288;\n728: \n729: function normalizeAggregateBudgetGuards(rawConfig = {}) {\n730:   return {\n731:     max_aggregate_cost_units: readRawConfigNumber(rawConfig, [\n732:       'maxAggregateCostUnits',\n733:       'max_aggregate_cost_units',\n734:       'maxTotalCostUnits',\n735:       'max_total_cost_units',\n736:     ], 'maxAggregateCostUnits') ?? DEFAULT_MAX_AGGREGATE_COST_UNITS,\n737:   };\n738: }\n739: \n740: function computeAggregateBudgetUpperBound(lineages, guardsInput = {}, maxRetries = 0) {\n741:   const aggregateGuards = normalizeAggregateBudgetGuards(guardsInput);\n742:   const lineageGuards = normalizeLineageBudgetGuards(guardsInput);\n743:   const perLineage = (lineages || []).map((lineage) => {\n744:     const upperBound = computeLineageBudgetUpperBound(lineage, lineageGuards, maxRetries);\n745:     return { label: lineage && lineage.label, estimated_cost_units: upperBound.estimated_cost_units };\n746:   });\n747:   const estimatedCostUnits = perLineage.reduce((sum, entry) => sum + entry.estimated_cost_units, 0);\n748:   return {\n749:     max_aggregate_cost_units: aggregateGuards.max_aggregate_cost_units,\n750:     estimated_cost_units: estimatedCostUnits,\n751:     lineage_count: perLineage.length,\n752:     per_lineage: perLineage,\n753:   };\n754: }\n755: \n756: function evaluateAggregateBudgetCap(input = {}) {\n757:   const upperBound = computeAggregateBudgetUpperBound(\n758:     input.lineages || [],\n759:     input.guards || input,\n760:     input.maxRetries,\n761:   );\n762:   const exceeded = upperBound.max_aggregate_cost_units > 0\n763:     && upperBound.estimated_cost_units > upperBound.max_aggregate_cost_units;\n764:   return {\n765:     continue_allowed: !exceeded,\n766:     stop_reasons: exceeded ? ['max_aggregate_cost_units'] : [],\n767:     upper_bound: upperBound,\n768:   };\n769: }\n770: \n771: function buildTimestampAnomalyCounts(check) {\n772:   return {\n773:     anomalous: check.anomalous,\n774:     untimestamped: check.untimestamped,\n775:     unparseable: check.unparseable,\n776:     total: check.total,\n777:   };\n778: }\n779: \n780: function buildTimestampAnomalyPayload({ lineage, statePath, check }) {\n781:   return {\n782:     label: lineage.label,\n783:     state_log: statePath,\n784:     window: {\n785:       start_at_iso: check.windowStart,\n786:       end_at_iso: check.windowEnd,\n787:       tolerance_ms: check.toleranceMs,\n788:     },\n789:     counts: buildTimestampAnomalyCounts(check),\n790:     sample: check.sample,\n791:   };\n792: }\n793: \n794: function collectTimestampAnomalies(results) {\n795:   return results\n796:     .filter((result) => result && result.status === 'fulfilled' && result.output && result.output.timestamp_anomaly)\n797:     .map((result) => result.output.timestamp_anomaly);\n798: }\n799: \n800: function normalizeNonNegativeDelayMs(value) {\n801:   if (value === undefined || value === null) return null;\n802:   const n = Number(value);\n803:   if (!Number.isFinite(n) || n < 0) return null;\n804:   return Math.floor(n);\n805: }\n806: \n807: function normalizeWaitDurationMs(value) {\n808:   return normalizeNonNegativeDelayMs(value) ?? 0;\n809: }\n810: \n811: function waitCheckpointPath(baseArtifactDir) {\n812:   return path.join(baseArtifactDir, WAIT_CHECKPOINT_FILENAME);\n813: }\n814: \n815: function atomicWriteJson(filePath, payload) {\n816:   fs.mkdirSync(path.dirname(filePath), { recursive: true });\n817:   const tmpPath = `${filePath}.${process.pid}.${Date.now()}.tmp`;\n818:   fs.writeFileSync(tmpPath, `${JSON.stringify(payload, null, 2)}\\n`, 'utf8');\n819:   fs.renameSync(tmpPath, filePath);\n820: }\n821: \n822: function buildWaitCheckpoint({ waitMs, runId, loopType, specFolder, nowMs = Date.now() }) {\n823:   const durationMs = normalizeWaitDurationMs(waitMs);\n824:   const updatedAt = new Date(nowMs).toISOString();\n825:   if (durationMs <= 0) {\n826:     return {\n827:       schemaVersion: WAIT_CHECKPOINT_SCHEMA_VERSION,\n828:       status: 'idle',\n829:       nextRunAt: null,\n830:       remainingDelayMs: null,\n831:       updatedAt,\n832:       runId,\n833:       loopType,\n834:       specFolder,\n835:     };\n836:   }\n837: \n838:   return {\n839:     schemaVersion: WAIT_CHECKPOINT_SCHEMA_VERSION,\n840:     status: 'waiting',\n841:     nextRunAt: new Date(nowMs + durationMs).toISOString(),\n842:     remainingDelayMs: durationMs,\n843:     updatedAt,\n844:     runId,\n845:     loopType,\n846:     specFolder,\n847:   };\n848: }\n849: \n850: function normalizeWaitCheckpoint(raw, context) {\n851:   if (!isRecord(raw)) {\n852:     throw inputError('wait checkpoint must be a JSON object');\n853:   }\n854: \n855:   const nowMs = Number.isFinite(Number(context.nowMs)) ? Number(context.nowMs) : Date.now();\n856:   const hasNextRunAt = Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(raw, 'nextRunAt');\n857:   const hasRemainingDelayMs = Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(raw, 'remainingDelayMs');\n858:   const nextRunAt = typeof raw.nextRunAt === 'string' && raw.nextRunAt.trim() !== ''\n859:     ? raw.nextRunAt\n860:     : null;\n861:   const nextRunAtMs = nextRunAt === null ? NaN : Date.parse(nextRunAt);\n862:   const waiting = Number.isFinite(nextRunAtMs) && nextRunAtMs > nowMs;\n863:   const remainingDelayMs = waiting ? Math.max(0, Math.ceil(nextRunAtMs - nowMs)) : null;\n864:   const base = {\n865:     runId: typeof raw.runId === 'string' && raw.runId ? raw.runId : context.runId,\n866:     loopType: typeof raw.loopType === 'string' && raw.loopType ? raw.loopType : context.loopType,\n867:     specFolder: typeof raw.specFolder === 'string' && raw.specFolder ? raw.specFolder : context.specFolder,\n868:   };\n869: \n870:   const checkpoint = waiting\n871:     ? {\n872:         schemaVersion: WAIT_CHECKPOINT_SCHEMA_VERSION,\n873:         status: 'waiting',\n874:         nextRunAt,\n875:         remainingDelayMs,\n876:         updatedAt: new Date(nowMs).toISOString(),\n877:         ...base,\n878:       }\n879:     : buildWaitCheckpoint({ waitMs: 0, nowMs, ...base });\n880:   const staleWaitingFields = !waiting\n881:     && (raw.nextRunAt !== null || raw.remainingDelayMs !== null || raw.status === 'waiting');\n882:   const staleRemainingDelay = waiting && Number(raw.remainingDelayMs) !== remainingDelayMs;\n883: \n884:   return {\n885:     checkpoint,\n886:     migrated: !hasNextRunAt || !hasRemainingDelayMs || staleWaitingFields || staleRemainingDelay,\n887:   };\n888: }\n889: \n890: function readWaitCheckpoint(checkpointPath, context) {\n891:   if (!fs.existsSync(checkpointPath)) {\n892:     return { exists: false, checkpoint: null, migrated: false };\n893:   }\n894: \n895:   let raw;\n896:   try {\n897:     raw = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(checkpointPath, 'utf8'));\n898:   } catch (error) {\n899:     throw inputError(\n900:       `wait checkpoint is not valid JSON: ${error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error)}`,\n901:     );\n902:   }\n903: \n904:   const normalized = normalizeWaitCheckpoint(raw, context);\n905:   if (normalized.migrated) {\n906:     atomicWriteJson(checkpointPath, normalized.checkpoint);\n907:   }\n908:   return { exists: true, ...normalized };\n909: }\n910: \n911: function sleepWaitChunk(ms) {\n912:   return new Promise((resolvePromise) => setTimeout(resolvePromise, ms));\n913: }\n914: \n915: async function waitUntilCheckpointExpires({ checkpointPath, checkpoint, context, sleep = sleepWaitChunk }) {\n916:   const nextRunAtMs = Date.parse(checkpoint.nextRunAt);\n917:   let remainingDelayMs = Math.max(0, Math.ceil(nextRunAtMs - Date.now()));\n918: \n919:   while (remainingDelayMs > 0) {\n920:     atomicWriteJson(checkpointPath, {\n921:       ...checkpoint,\n922:       remainingDelayMs,\n923:       updatedAt: new Date().toISOString(),\n924:     });\n925:     await sleep(Math.min(remainingDelayMs, WAIT_SLEEP_CHUNK_MS));\n926:     remainingDelayMs = Math.max(0, Math.ceil(nextRunAtMs - Date.now()));\n927:   }\n928: \n929:   atomicWriteJson(checkpointPath, buildWaitCheckpoint({ waitMs: 0, ...context }));\n930: }\n931: \n932: async function resumeWaitingCheckpoint({ checkpointPath, ledgerPath, runId, loopType, specFolder }) {\n933:   const context = { runId, loopType, specFolder, nowMs: Date.now() };\n934:   const loaded = readWaitCheckpoint(checkpointPath, context);\n935:   if (!loaded.checkpoint || loaded.checkpoint.status !== 'waiting') {\n936:     return { didWait: false, migrated: loaded.migrated };\n937:   }\n938: \n939:   appendFanoutStatusLedger(ledgerPath, {\n940:     event: 'resume_waiting',\n941:     at: new Date().toISOString(),\n942:     run_id: runId,\n943:     loop_type: loopType,\n944:     spec_folder: specFolder,\n945:     nextRunAt: loaded.checkpoint.nextRunAt,\n946:     remainingDelayMs: loaded.checkpoint.remainingDelayMs,\n947:   });\n948: \n949:   await waitUntilCheckpointExpires({\n950:     checkpointPath,\n951:     checkpoint: loaded.checkpoint,\n952:     context: { runId, loopType, specFolder },\n953:   });\n954: \n955:   appendFanoutStatusLedger(ledgerPath, {\n956:     event: 'resume_waiting_complete',\n957:     at: new Date().toISOString(),\n958:     run_id: runId,\n959:     loop_type: loopType,\n960:     spec_folder: specFolder,\n961:   });\n962: \n963:   return { didWait: true, migrated: loaded.migrated };\n964: }\n965: \n966: async function persistPreDispatchWait({ checkpointPath, ledgerPath, runId, loopType, specFolder, waitMs }) {\n967:   const durationMs = normalizeWaitDurationMs(waitMs);\n968:   if (durationMs <= 0) {\n969:     return { didWait: false };\n970:   }\n971: \n972:   const checkpoint = buildWaitCheckpoint({ waitMs: durationMs, runId, loopType, specFolder });\n973:   atomicWriteJson(checkpointPath, checkpoint);\n974:   appendFanoutStatusLedger(ledgerPath, {\n975:     event: 'wait_checkpoint_persisted',\n976:     at: checkpoint.updatedAt,\n977:     run_id: runId,\n978:     loop_type: loopType,\n979:     spec_folder: specFolder,\n980:     nextRunAt: checkpoint.nextRunAt,\n981:     remainingDelayMs: checkpoint.remainingDelayMs,\n982:   });\n983: \n984:   await waitUntilCheckpointExpires({\n985:     checkpointPath,\n986:     checkpoint,\n987:     context: { runId, loopType, specFolder },\n988:   });\n989: \n990:   appendFanoutStatusLedger(ledgerPath, {\n991:     event: 'wait_checkpoint_cleared',\n992:     at: new Date().toISOString(),\n993:     run_id: runId,\n994:     loop_type: loopType,\n995:     spec_folder: specFolder,\n996:   });\n997: \n998:   return { didWait: true };\n999: }\n1000: \n1001: /**\n1002:  * Build the \"run the full loop\" prompt text for a CLI lineage subprocess.\n1003:  * The subprocess reads this, loads the skill, and runs the requested stop policy\n1004:  * with config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir overriding step_resolve_artifact_root.\n1005:  */\n1006: function buildLoopPrompt(loopType, specFolder, lineageDir, sessionId, lineage, researchTopic, options = {}) {\n1007:   assertActiveFanoutLoopType(loopType);\n1008:   const skillFile =\n1009:     loopType === 'review'\n1010:       ? '.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/SKILL.md'\n1011:       : '.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md';\n1012:   const agentName = loopType === 'review' ? 'deep-review' : 'deep-research';\n1013:   const detachedIntro = lineage.kind === 'cli-opencode'\n1014:     ? [\n1015:         `This is an explicit parallel-detached OpenCode lineage, not a self-invocation of the parent session.`,\n1016:         `Use the separate lineage directory and session id below as the detached state boundary.`,\n1017:         ``,\n1018:       ]\n1019:     : lineage.kind === 'native'\n1020:       ? [\n1021:           `This is an explicit native fan-out adapter running through the command host's OpenCode CLI surface.`,\n1022:           `Use the separate lineage directory and session id below as the detached state boundary.`,\n1023:           ``,\n1024:         ]\n1025:       : [];\n1026:   const hasIterationCap = typeof lineage.iterations === 'number' && lineage.iterations > 0;\n1027:   const stopPolicy = options.stopPolicy || 'convergence';\n1028:   const stopClause = hasIterationCap && stopPolicy === 'max-iterations'\n1029:     ? 'until config.maxIterations is reached; treat convergence before that as telemetry only and broaden review angles instead of synthesizing early'\n1030:     : hasIterationCap\n1031:       ? 'to legal convergence OR config.maxIterations, whichever comes first'\n1032:       : 'to legal convergence';\n1033:   const params = [\n1034:     `  spec_folder: ${specFolder}`,\n1035:     `  config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: ${lineageDir}`,\n1036:     `  session_id: ${sessionId}`,\n1037:     `  executor: ${lineage.kind} model=${lineage.model || 'default'}`,\n1038:     `  loop_type: ${loopType}`,\n1039:     `  config.stopPolicy: ${stopPolicy}`,\n1040:   ];\n1041:   if (researchTopic) {\n1042:     // A research lineage's phase_init binds research_topic from this line. Without it a\n1043:     // fan-out research loop has no question to investigate and degrades to an empty topic.\n1044:     // Review loops scope by spec_folder and intentionally pass no topic.\n1045:     params.push(`  research_topic: ${researchTopic}`);\n1046:   }\n1047:   if (hasIterationCap) {\n1048:     params.push(`  config.maxIterations: ${lineage.iterations}`);\n1049:   }\n1050:   if (options.convergenceThreshold !== null && options.convergenceThreshold !== undefined) {\n1051:     params.push(`  config.convergenceThreshold: ${options.convergenceThreshold}`);\n1052:   }\n1053:   // Review lineages scope by spec_folder but the auto-workflow preflight\n1054:   // still requires the same review setup bindings the native command path pre-binds.\n1055:   // Without these, a detached CLI lineage can fail first-run initialization or infer a\n1056:   // different setup contract than native lineages.\n1057:   const setupBindings =\n1058:     loopType === 'review'\n1059:       ? [\n1060:           ``,\n1061:           `Review setup bindings (emit before any writes, same as native PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS):`,\n1062:           `review_target: ${specFolder}`,\n1063:           `review_target_type: spec-folder`,\n1064:           `review_dimensions: all`,\n1065:           `spec_folder: ${specFolder}`,\n1066:           `execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS`,\n1067:           `lineage_mode: auto`,\n1068:           ``,\n1069:         ]\n1070:       : [];\n1071:   return [\n1072:     `You are orchestrating the ${agentName} workflow YAML as a detached fan-out lineage.`,\n1073:     ...detachedIntro,\n1074:     ``,\n1075:     `Read ${skillFile} and execute the ${loopType} loop with these parameters:`,\n1076:     ...params,\n1077:     ...setupBindings,\n1078:     `The step_resolve_artifact_root step will bind artifact_dir to ${lineageDir} via the`,\n1079:     `config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir override — do NOT run the resolveArtifactRoot node`,\n1080:     `command; bind artifact_dir directly to the override value.`,\n1081:     ``,\n1082:     `Run phase_init, phase_main_loop (${stopClause}), and phase_synthesis.`,\n1083:     `Write all outputs to ${lineageDir}. Do not touch any path outside ${lineageDir}.`,\n1084:     ``,\n1085:     `When complete, output a single line: FANOUT_LINEAGE_COMPLETE:${lineage.label}`,\n1086:   ].join('\\n');\n1087: }\n1088: \n1089: function buildNativeCommandInput(loopType, specFolder, lineageDir, lineage, options = {}) {\n1090:   assertActiveFanoutLoopType(loopType);\n1091:   const maxIterations = lineage.iterations || 12;\n1092:   const convergenceThreshold = options.convergenceThreshold ?? (loopType === 'research' ? 0.05 : 0.1);\n1093:   const stopPolicy = options.stopPolicy || 'convergence';\n1094:   const sessionId = options.sessionId || '';\n1095:   const args = [\n1096:     ':auto',\n1097:     JSON.stringify(specFolder),\n1098:     `--spec-folder=${specFolder}`,\n1099:     `--max-iterations=${maxIterations}`,\n1100:     `--convergence=${convergenceThreshold}`,\n1101:     `--stop-policy=${stopPolicy}`,\n1102:     `--fanout-lineage-artifact-dir=${lineageDir}`,\n1103:     '--lineage-mode=auto',\n1104:   ];\n1105:   if (loopType === 'research' && options.researchTopic) {\n1106:     args.push(`--research-topic=${JSON.stringify(options.researchTopic)}`);\n1107:   }\n1108: \n1109:   return [\n1110:     args.join(' '),\n1111:     '',\n1112:     'PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:',\n1113:     `review_target: ${specFolder}`,\n1114:     'review_target_type: spec-folder',\n1115:     'review_dimensions: all',\n1116:     `spec_folder: ${specFolder}`,\n1117:     ...(sessionId ? [`session_id: ${sessionId}`] : []),\n1118:     'execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS',\n1119:     'lineage_mode: auto',\n1120:     `maxIterations: ${maxIterations}`,\n1121:     `convergenceThreshold: ${convergenceThreshold}`,\n1122:     `stop_policy: ${stopPolicy}`,\n1123:     `config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: ${lineageDir}`,\n1124:   ].join('\\n');\n1125: }\n1126: \n1127: // Full-lineage lifetime is non-disableable in autonomous mode: 4 hours is the hard\n1128: // ceiling and a positive override may only narrow it, never widen past it.\n1129: const LINEAGE_LIFETIME_HARD_MAX_HOURS = 4;\n1130: \n1131: function assertLineageTimeoutHoursOverrideWithinCeiling(ceilingHoursOverride) {\n1132:   if (Number.isFinite(ceilingHoursOverride) && ceilingHoursOverride > LINEAGE_LIFETIME_HARD_MAX_HOURS) {\n1133:     throw inputError(\n1134:       `lineageTimeoutHours override (${ceilingHoursOverride}) exceeds the hard maximum of `\n1135:         + `${LINEAGE_LIFETIME_HARD_MAX_HOURS} hours`,\n1136:     );\n1137:   }\n1138: }\n1139: \n1140: /**\n1141:  * Compute a generous timeout for a full lineage loop run.\n1142:  * A single iteration is timeoutSeconds; a full loop is up to iterations * timeoutSeconds.\n1143:  * We double it for safety and cap at 4 hours. A caller-provided ceiling override may only\n1144:  * narrow this hard ceiling, never widen it — full-lineage lifetime is non-disableable.\n1145:  */\n1146: function computeLineageTimeoutMs(lineage, ceilingHoursOverride) {\n1147:   assertLineageTimeoutHoursOverrideWithinCeiling(ceilingHoursOverride);\n1148:   const iters = lineage.iterations || 12;\n1149:   const perIterSecs = lineage.timeoutSeconds || 900;\n1150:   const ceilingMs = Number.isFinite(ceilingHoursOverride) && ceilingHoursOverride > 0\n1151:     ? ceilingHoursOverride * 60 * 60 * 1000\n1152:     : LINEAGE_LIFETIME_HARD_MAX_HOURS * 60 * 60 * 1000;\n1153:   return Math.min(iters * perIterSecs * 2 * 1000, ceilingMs);\n1154: }\n1155: \n1156: function normalizeProgressHeartbeatMs(seconds) {\n1157:   const value = Number(seconds);\n1158:   if (!Number.isFinite(value) || value <= 0) return 0;\n1159:   return Math.max(1, Math.floor(value * 1000));\n1160: }\n1161: \n1162: function normalizePostExitGraceMs(rawConfig, progressHeartbeatMs = 0) {\n1163:   const explicit = readRawConfigNumber(rawConfig, [\n1164:     'postExitGraceMs',\n1165:     'post_exit_grace_ms',\n1166:     'postSubprocessExitGraceMs',\n1167:     'post_subprocess_exit_grace_ms',\n1168:     'orchestratorPostExitGraceMs',\n1169:     'orchestrator_post_exit_grace_ms',\n1170:   ], 'postExitGraceMs');\n1171:   if (explicit !== null) return explicit;\n1172: \n1173:   const heartbeatDerived = Number.isFinite(progressHeartbeatMs) && progressHeartbeatMs > 0\n1174:     ? progressHeartbeatMs * 2\n1175:     : 0;\n1176:   return Math.max(DEFAULT_POST_EXIT_GRACE_MS, heartbeatDerived);\n1177: }\n1178: \n1179: function slotDurationMsFromHrtime(hrStart) {\n1180:   const [seconds, nanoseconds] = process.hrtime(hrStart);\n1181:   return Math.max(0, (seconds * 1000) + (nanoseconds / 1e6));\n1182: }\n1183: \n1184: function computeSkippedCount(slotDurationMs, intervalMs) {\n1185:   const elapsed = Number(slotDurationMs);\n1186:   const interval = Number(intervalMs);\n1187:   if (!Number.isFinite(elapsed) || !Number.isFinite(interval) || interval <= 0) {\n1188:     return 0;\n1189:   }\n1190:   return Math.max(0, Math.floor(elapsed / interval) - 1);\n1191: }\n1192: \n1193: function buildSlotAccounting(hrStart, intervalMs) {\n1194:   const slotDurationMs = slotDurationMsFromHrtime(hrStart);\n1195:   return {\n1196:     slotDurationMs,\n1197:     skippedCount: computeSkippedCount(slotDurationMs, intervalMs),\n1198:   };\n1199: }\n1200: \n1201: function decorateSlotAccountingEvent(event, accountingByLabel) {\n1202:   if (!event || typeof event.label !== 'string') return event;\n1203:   if (event.event !== 'completed' && event.event !== 'failed') return event;\n1204: \n1205:   const accounting = accountingByLabel.get(event.label);\n1206:   if (!accounting) return event;\n1207:   return {\n1208:     ...event,\n1209:     skippedCount: accounting.skippedCount,\n1210:     slotDurationMs: accounting.slotDurationMs,\n1211:   };\n1212: }\n1213: \n1214: function startLineageProgressHeartbeat({ cadenceMs, label, ledgerPath, getGauges, onProgress }) {\n1215:   if (!Number.isFinite(cadenceMs) || cadenceMs <= 0) {\n1216:     return () => {};\n1217:   }\n1218:   const startedAtMs = Date.now();\n1219:   const timer = setInterval(() => {\n1220:     appendFanoutStatusLedger(ledgerPath, {\n1221:       event: 'progress',\n1222:       label,\n1223:       at: new Date().toISOString(),\n1224:       duration_ms: Math.max(0, Date.now() - startedAtMs),\n1225:         gauges: getGauges(),\n1226:       });\n1227:       if (typeof onProgress === 'function') onProgress();\n1228:     }, cadenceMs);\n1229:   timer.unref?.();\n1230:   return () => clearInterval(timer);\n1231: }\n1232: \n1233: function startLineageStallWatchdog({ thresholdMs, label, ledgerPath, getLastEventAtMs, getGauges }) {\n1234:   if (!Number.isFinite(thresholdMs) || thresholdMs <= 0) {\n1235:     return () => {};\n1236:   }\n1237: \n1238:   let timer = null;\n1239:   let fired = false;\n1240:   const schedule = () => {\n1241:     if (fired) return;\n1242:     const quietMs = Math.max(0, Date.now() - getLastEventAtMs());\n1243:     const delayMs = Math.max(1, thresholdMs - quietMs);\n1244:     timer = setTimeout(() => {\n1245:       timer = null;\n1246:       const latestQuietMs = Math.max(0, Date.now() - getLastEventAtMs());\n1247:       if (latestQuietMs >= thresholdMs) {\n1248:         fired = true;\n1249:         appendFanoutStatusLedger(ledgerPath, {\n1250:           event: 'stall_detected',\n1251:           label,\n1252:           at: new Date().toISOString(),\n1253:           severity: 'warning',\n1254:           metric: 'time_since_last_lineage_event',\n1255:           stall_watchdog_ms: thresholdMs,\n1256:           quiet_ms: Math.floor(latestQuietMs),\n1257:           gauges: getGauges(),\n1258:         });\n1259:         return;\n1260:       }\n1261:       schedule();\n1262:     }, delayMs);\n1263:     timer.unref?.();\n1264:   };\n1265: \n1266:   schedule();\n1267:   return () => {\n1268:     fired = true;\n1269:     if (timer) clearTimeout(timer);\n1270:   };\n1271: }\n1272: \n1273: /**\n1274:  * Run a lineage subprocess without blocking the Node event loop.\n1275:  *\n1276:  * Resolves a spawnSync-shaped result ({ status, signal, stdout, error }) so the\n1277:  * pool's K-in-flight cap actually overlaps lineages. spawnSync blocked the single\n1278:  * thread until each child exited, serializing every lineage regardless of the\n1279:  * concurrency cap; an awaited async spawn yields to the loop so K run at once.\n1280:  *\n1281:  * On timeout the child is killed with SIGTERM and result.signal is set to\n1282:  * 'SIGTERM', preserving the timeout-as-failure signal the caller relies on.\n1283:  *\n1284:  * @param {string} command - Executable to run.\n1285:  * @param {string[]} cmdArgs - Arguments for the executable.\n1286:  * @param {Object} opts - { cwd, env, timeoutMs, maxBuffer, input? }.\n1287:  * @returns {Promise<{status:number|null, signal:string|null, stdout:string, error?:Error}>}\n1288:  */\n1289: function runLineageProcess(command, cmdArgs, opts) {\n1290:   const { cwd, env, timeoutMs, maxBuffer } = opts;\n1291:   const hasInput = typeof opts.input === 'string';\n1292: \n1293:   return new Promise((resolvePromise) => {\n1294:     let child;\n1295:     try {\n1296:       child = spawn(command, cmdArgs, {\n1297:         cwd,\n1298:         env,\n1299:         stdio: [hasInput ? 'pipe' : 'ignore', 'pipe', 'pipe'],\n1300:         detached: process.platform !== 'win32',\n1301:       });\n1302:     } catch (error) {\n1303:       resolvePromise({ status: null, signal: null, stdout: '', error });\n1304:       return;\n1305:     }\n1306:     activeLineageProcesses.add(child);\n1307:     if (typeof opts.onSpawn === 'function') {\n1308:       opts.onSpawn({ pid: child.pid });\n1309:     }\n1310: \n1311:     let stdout = '';\n1312:     let stdoutBytes = 0;\n1313:     let truncated = false;\n1314:     let timedOut = false;\n1315:     let settled = false;\n1316:     let spawnError;\n1317: \n1318:     const timer = setTimeout(() => {\n1319:       timedOut = true;\n1320:       terminateLineageProcess(child, 'SIGTERM');\n1321:     }, timeoutMs);\n1322:     timer.unref?.();\n1323: \n1324:     const abortHandler = () => {\n1325:       terminateLineageProcess(child, 'SIGTERM');\n1326:     };\n1327:     if (opts.abortSignal) {\n1328:       if (opts.abortSignal.aborted) {\n1329:         abortHandler();\n1330:       } else {\n1331:         opts.abortSignal.addEventListener('abort', abortHandler, { once: true });\n1332:       }\n1333:     }\n1334: \n1335:     child.stdout?.setEncoding('utf8');\n1336:     child.stdout?.on('data', (chunk) => {\n1337:       if (typeof opts.onOutput === 'function') opts.onOutput();\n1338:       if (truncated) return;\n1339:       stdoutBytes += Buffer.byteLength(chunk, 'utf8');\n1340:       if (stdoutBytes > maxBuffer) {\n1341:         truncated = true;\n1342:         terminateLineageProcess(child, 'SIGTERM');\n1343:         return;\n1344:       }\n1345:       stdout += chunk;\n1346:     });\n1347:     // Drain stderr so the child never blocks on a full pipe; we do not capture it.\n1348:     child.stderr?.resume();\n1349: \n1350:     child.on('error', (error) => {\n1351:       spawnError = error;\n1352:     });\n1353: \n1354:     child.on('close', (code, signal) => {\n1355:       if (settled) return;\n1356:       settled = true;\n1357:       activeLineageProcesses.delete(child);\n1358:       clearTimeout(timer);\n1359:       opts.abortSignal?.removeEventListener?.('abort', abortHandler);\n1360:       const effectiveSignal = timedOut ? 'SIGTERM' : signal;\n1361:       if (typeof opts.onExit === 'function') {\n1362:         opts.onExit({ status: timedOut ? null : code, signal: effectiveSignal, pid: child.pid, exitedAtMs: Date.now() });\n1363:       }\n1364:       resolvePromise({\n1365:         status: timedOut ? null : code,\n1366:         signal: effectiveSignal,\n1367:         stdout,\n1368:         ...(spawnError ? { error: spawnError } : {}),\n1369:       });\n1370:     });\n1371: \n1372:     if (hasInput) {\n1373:       child.stdin?.on('error', () => {});\n1374:       child.stdin?.end(opts.input);\n1375:     }\n1376:   });\n1377: }\n1378: \n1379: function digestText(value) {\n1380:   return createHash('sha256').update(String(value)).digest('hex');\n1381: }\n1382: \n1383: const executableIdentityCache = new Map();\n1384: \n1385: function resolveExecutableVersion(command, options = {}) {\n1386:   if (typeof options.executableVersion === 'string' && options.executableVersion.trim()) {\n1387:     return options.executableVersion.trim();\n1388:   }\n1389:   const env = options.env || process.env;\n1390:   const pathEntries = String(env.PATH || '').split(path.delimiter).filter(Boolean);\n1391:   for (const entry of pathEntries) {\n1392:     const candidate = path.join(entry, command);\n1393:     try {\n1394:       const executablePath = fs.realpathSync(candidate);\n1395:       const stat = fs.statSync(executablePath);\n1396:       if (!stat.isFile()) continue;\n1397:       const cacheKey = `${executablePath}:${stat.size}:${stat.mtimeMs}`;\n1398:       const cached = executableIdentityCache.get(cacheKey);\n1399:       if (cached) return cached;\n1400:       const identity = `sha256:${createHash('sha256').update(fs.readFileSync(executablePath)).digest('hex')}`;\n1401:       executableIdentityCache.set(cacheKey, identity);\n1402:       return identity;\n1403:     } catch {}\n1404:   }\n1405:   return 'unknown';\n1406: }\n1407: \n1408: function effectiveWebSearchPolicy(lineage) {\n1409:   return lineage.liveTools?.webSearch || 'inherit';\n1410: }\n1411: \n1412: /**\n1413:  * Build the allowlisted fingerprint payload without raw prompts or environment maps.\n1414:  *\n1415:  * @param {Object} input - Resolved invocation fields.\n1416:  * @returns {Object} Canonical JSON-safe payload.\n1417:  */\n1418: function buildInvocationFingerprintPayload(input) {\n1419:   const promptDigest = digestText(input.prompt);\n1420:   const promptArgIndexes = new Set(input.promptArgIndexes || []);\n1421:   const argv = input.args.map((arg, index) => (\n1422:     promptArgIndexes.has(index) ? `<prompt:${promptDigest}>` : arg\n1423:   ));\n1424:   return {\n1425:     kind: input.kind,\n1426:     executable: input.command,\n1427:     executableVersion: input.executableVersion || 'unknown',\n1428:     model: input.model,\n1429:     effort: input.reasoningEffort,\n1430:     tier: input.serviceTier,\n1431:     sandboxPosture: {\n1432:       sandboxMode: input.resolvedSandbox,\n1433:       permissionMode: input.resolvedPermission,\n1434:     },\n1435:     webSearch: input.webSearch,\n1436:     argv,\n1437:     promptDigest,\n1438:   };\n1439: }\n1440: \n1441: function finalizeLineageCommand(input) {\n1442:   const effectiveConfig = {\n1443:     kind: input.kind,\n1444:     executable: input.command,\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 1-1444. Use offset=1445 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n\n// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ Deep-Loop Runtime — Fan-Out CLI Lineage Pool Runner                      ║\n// ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n// ║ Input:  CLI args (--spec-folder, --loop-type, --fanout-config-json,      ║\n// ║         --base-artifact-dir).                                            ║\n// ║ Output: JSON to stdout.                                                  ║\n// ║ Exit:   0=all ok, 1=script error, 2=some failed, 3=all failed.          ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\n'use strict';\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 1. IMPORTS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst fs = require('node:fs');\nconst os = require('node:os');\nconst path = require('node:path');","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs","text":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n\n// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ Deep-Loop Runtime — Fan-Out CLI Lineage Pool Runner                      ║\n// ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n// ║ Input:  CLI args (--spec-folder, --loop-type, --fanout-config-json,      ║\n// ║         --base-artifact-dir).                                            ║\n// ║ Output: JSON to stdout.                                                  ║\n// ║ Exit:   0=all ok, 1=script error, 2=some failed, 3=all failed.          ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\n'use strict';\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 1. IMPORTS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst fs = require('node:fs');\nconst os = require('node:os');\nconst path = require('node:path');\nconst { spawn, spawnSync } = require('node:child_process');\nconst { createHash } = require('node:crypto');\n\nconst {\n  classifyExitCode,\n  maybeThrowTestFault,\n  validateNamespaceValue,\n} = require('./lib/cli-guards.cjs');\n\nconst {\n  runCappedPool,\n  appendStatusLedger,\n  markOrphanedLineages,\n  readRetryCountsFromLedger,\n  createWavePlannerInterface,\n  writeOrchestrationSummary,\n} = require('./fanout-pool.cjs');\n\nconst {\n  runSalvageSweep,\n  extractTextFromOpencodeJson,\n} = require('./fanout-salvage.cjs');\n\nconst {\n  appendObservabilityEvent,\n} = require('../lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs');\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 2. TSX BOOTSTRAP\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst TSX_LOADER = require.resolve('tsx');\nconst isTsxLoaded = process.env.DEEP_LOOP_TSX_LOADED === '1';\n\nfunction runTsxBootstrap() {\n  const child = spawn(\n    process.execPath,\n    ['--import', TSX_LOADER, __filename, ...process.argv.slice(2)],\n    {\n      cwd: process.cwd(),\n      env: { ...process.env, DEEP_LOOP_TSX_LOADED: '1' },\n      stdio: [process.stdin.isTTY ? 'ignore' : 'pipe', 'pipe', 'pipe'],\n    },\n  );\n\n  if (!process.stdin.isTTY && child.stdin) {\n    child.stdin.on('error', () => {});\n    process.stdin.pipe(child.stdin);\n  }\n\n  child.stdout?.pipe(process.stdout);\n  child.stderr?.pipe(process.stderr);\n\n  for (const signal of ['SIGINT', 'SIGTERM']) {\n    process.once(signal, () => {\n      child.kill(signal);\n    });\n  }\n\n  child.on('close', (status, signal) => {\n    if (status !== null) {\n      process.exit(status);\n    }\n    process.exit(signal === 'SIGINT' ? 130 : signal === 'SIGTERM' ? 143 : 1);\n  });\n}\n\nif (require.main === module && !isTsxLoaded) {\n  runTsxBootstrap();\n}\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 3. HELPERS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nfunction parseArgs(argv = process.argv.slice(2)) {\n  const args = {};\n  for (let i = 0; i < argv.length; i += 1) {\n    const token = argv[i];\n    if (!token.startsWith('--')) {\n      throw inputError(`Unexpected positional argument: ${token}`);\n    }\n    const key = token.slice(2).replace(/-([a-z])/g, (_, c) => c.toUpperCase());\n    const next = argv[i + 1];\n    if (next === undefined || next.startsWith('--')) {\n      args[key] = true;\n    } else {\n      args[key] = next;\n      i += 1;\n    }\n  }\n  return args;\n}\n\nfunction inputError(message) {\n  const err = new Error(message);\n  err.code = 'INPUT_VALIDATION';\n  return err;\n}\n\nfunction ensureString(args, key) {\n  if (!args[key] || typeof args[key] !== 'string') {\n    throw inputError(`${key} is required`);\n  }\n  return args[key];\n}\n\nfunction parseOptionalNumber(args, key) {\n  const raw = args[key];\n  if (raw === undefined || raw === false || raw === null || raw === '') {\n    return null;\n  }\n  if (raw === true || typeof raw !== 'string') {\n    throw inputError(`${key} must be a number`);\n  }\n  const value = Number(raw);\n  if (!Number.isFinite(value) || value < 0) {\n    throw inputError(`${key} must be a non-negative number`);\n  }\n  return value;\n}\n\nfunction readRawConfigNumber(rawConfig, names, fieldName) {\n  if (!isRecord(rawConfig)) return null;\n  for (const name of names) {\n    if (!Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(rawConfig, name)) continue;\n    const raw = rawConfig[name];\n    if (raw === undefined || raw === null || raw === '') return null;\n    if (raw === true || raw === false) {\n      throw inputError(`${fieldName} must be a non-negative number`);\n    }\n    const value = Number(raw);\n    if (!Number.isFinite(value) || value < 0) {\n      throw inputError(`${fieldName} must be a non-negative number`);\n    }\n    return Math.floor(value);\n  }\n  return null;\n}\n\nfunction readPositiveRawConfigNumber(rawConfig, names, fieldName, fallback) {\n  const value = readRawConfigNumber(rawConfig, names, fieldName);\n  if (value === null) return fallback;\n  if (value <= 0) {\n    throw inputError(`${fieldName} must be greater than 0`);\n  }\n  return value;\n}\n\nfunction rawConfigWithCliBudgetOverrides(rawConfig, args) {\n  const merged = { ...(isRecord(rawConfig) ? rawConfig : {}) };\n  const mappings = [\n    ['stallWatchdogMs', 'stallWatchdogMs'],\n    ['maxCostUnitsPerLineage', 'maxCostUnitsPerLineage'],\n    ['maxAggregateCostUnits', 'maxAggregateCostUnits'],\n    ['maxTokensPerLineage', 'maxTokensPerLineage'],\n    ['maxTokenBudget', 'maxTokenBudget'],\n    ['maxTokenBudgetPerLineage', 'maxTokenBudgetPerLineage'],\n    ['costUnitsPerIteration', 'costUnitsPerIteration'],\n    ['estimatedTokensPerIteration', 'estimatedTokensPerIteration'],\n  ];\n  for (const [targetKey, argKey] of mappings) {\n    if (Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(args, argKey)) {\n      merged[targetKey] = args[argKey];\n    }\n  }\n  return merged;\n}\n\nfunction normalizeStopPolicy(raw) {\n  if (raw === undefined || raw === false || raw === null || raw === '') {\n    return 'convergence';\n  }\n  if (raw === true || typeof raw !== 'string') {\n    throw inputError('stopPolicy must be convergence or max-iterations');\n  }\n  if (raw !== 'convergence' && raw !== 'max-iterations') {\n    throw inputError('stopPolicy must be convergence or max-iterations');\n  }\n  return raw;\n}\n\nfunction jsonOut(payload) {\n  process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(payload)}\\n`);\n}\n\nfunction signalExitCode(signal) {\n  return signal === 'SIGINT' ? 130 : 143;\n}\n\nlet fanoutSignalHandlersInstalled = false;\n\nfunction installFanoutSignalHandlers(onStop) {\n  if (fanoutSignalHandlersInstalled) return;\n  fanoutSignalHandlersInstalled = true;\n\n  for (const signal of ['SIGINT', 'SIGTERM']) {\n    process.once(signal, () => {\n      try {\n        onStop(signal);\n      } finally {\n        process.exit(signalExitCode(signal));\n      }\n    });\n  }\n}\n\nfunction updateLineageSnapshot(snapshots, event) {\n  if (!event || typeof event.label !== 'string') return;\n  const existing = snapshots.get(event.label) || { label: event.label };\n\n  if (event.event === 'started') {\n    snapshots.set(event.label, { ...existing, status: 'running', started_at_iso: event.at });\n    return;\n  }\n  if (event.event === 'completed') {\n    snapshots.set(event.label, {\n      ...existing,\n      status: 'fulfilled',\n      completed_at_iso: event.at,\n      duration_ms: event.duration_ms,\n    });\n    return;\n  }\n  if (event.event === 'failed') {\n    snapshots.set(event.label, {\n      ...existing,\n      status: event.terminal === false ? 'retrying' : 'rejected',\n      completed_at_iso: event.at,\n      duration_ms: event.duration_ms,\n      error: event.error,\n    });\n    return;\n  }\n  if (event.event === 'retry_scheduled' || event.event === 'orphan_requeued') {\n    snapshots.set(event.label, { ...existing, status: 'requeued', updated_at_iso: event.at });\n    return;\n  }\n  if (event.event === 'progress') {\n    snapshots.set(event.label, {\n      ...existing,\n      status: 'running',\n      updated_at_iso: event.at,\n      duration_ms: event.duration_ms,\n    });\n  }\n}\n\nfunction buildLineageSnapshots(lineages, snapshots) {\n  return lineages.map((lineage) => snapshots.get(lineage.label) || { label: lineage.label, status: 'pending' });\n}\n\nfunction summarizeSnapshots(lineages, snapshots) {\n  const results = buildLineageSnapshots(lineages, snapshots);\n  const succeeded = results.filter((result) => result.status === 'fulfilled').length;\n  const failed = results.filter((result) => result.status === 'rejected').length;\n  return {\n    results,\n    summary: {\n      total: lineages.length,\n      succeeded,\n      failed,\n      all_failed: lineages.length > 0 && failed === lineages.length,\n    },\n  };\n}\n\nfunction observabilityPathForLedger(ledgerPath) {\n  return path.join(path.dirname(ledgerPath), OBSERVABILITY_EVENTS_FILENAME);\n}\n\nfunction statusForLedgerEvent(entry) {\n  if (entry && typeof entry.status === 'string' && entry.status.trim() !== '') {\n    return entry.status;\n  }\n  if (!entry || typeof entry.event !== 'string') return 'unknown';\n  if (entry.event === 'started' || entry.event === 'progress' || entry.event === 'resume_waiting') return 'running';\n  if (entry.event === 'completed' || entry.event === 'resume_waiting_complete') return 'completed';\n  if (entry.event === 'failed') return entry.terminal === false ? 'retrying' : 'failed';\n  if (entry.event === 'stopped') return 'stopped';\n  if (entry.event === 'retry_scheduled' || entry.event === 'orphan_requeued') return 'retrying';\n  // Lag-ceiling signals from the pool: a stall warning while work remains pending, or a\n  // forced abort of the stalled attempt. Map both to typed statuses instead of 'unknown'.\n  if (entry.event === 'lag_ceiling_exceeded') return entry.action === 'abort' ? 'failed' : 'warning';\n  if (entry.event === 'lag_ceiling_abort') return 'failed';\n  if (entry.event === 'stall_detected') return 'warning';\n  if (entry.event === 'budget_cap_exceeded') return 'failed';\n  if (entry.event === 'aggregate_budget_cap_exceeded') return 'failed';\n  return 'unknown';\n}\n\nfunction appendFanoutStatusLedger(ledgerPath, entry) {\n  appendStatusLedger(ledgerPath, entry);\n  try {\n    appendObservabilityEvent(observabilityPathForLedger(ledgerPath), entry, {\n      producer: 'fanout-run',\n      stream: 'orchestration-status',\n      subject: {\n        run_id: entry.run_id ?? null,\n        label: entry.label ?? null,\n        loop_type: entry.loop_type ?? null,\n        spec_folder: entry.spec_folder ?? null,\n      },\n      event: entry.event,\n      status: statusForLedgerEvent(entry),\n    });\n  } catch {\n    // Observability must not make the primary orchestration ledger fail.\n  }\n}\n\nconst FLAT_POOL_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL = 'flat_pool';\nconst WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL = 'wave';\nconst WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL_REJECTION = 'REJECTED: wave assignment_model requires conflict-safety substrate';\nconst WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_METADATA_REJECTION = 'REJECTED: wave assignment metadata requires conflict-safety substrate';\nconst STATE_LOG_BY_LOOP_TYPE = {\n  research: 'deep-research-state.jsonl',\n  review: 'deep-review-state.jsonl',\n};\nconst ACTIVE_FANOUT_LOOP_TYPES = new Set(['research', 'review']);\nconst DEPRECATED_CONTEXT_FANOUT_MESSAGE = 'loopType must be \"research\" or \"review\"; context fan-out is deprecated. Use @context for one-shot retrieval, /deep:research or /deep:review bounded snapshots for iterative work, or /speckit:plan for implementation planning.';\n\nfunction assertActiveFanoutLoopType(loopType) {\n  if (!ACTIVE_FANOUT_LOOP_TYPES.has(loopType)) {\n    throw inputError(DEPRECATED_CONTEXT_FANOUT_MESSAGE);\n  }\n}\n\nfunction hasNonEmptyArrayField(value) {\n  return Array.isArray(value) && value.length > 0;\n}\n\nfunction collectFlatPoolGuardRejections(fanoutConfig) {\n  const rejections = [];\n  if (fanoutConfig.assignment_model === WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL) {\n    rejections.push({\n      scope: 'fanout',\n      label: null,\n      field: 'assignment_model',\n      message: WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL_REJECTION,\n    });\n  }\n\n  for (const lineage of fanoutConfig.executors) {\n    if (lineage.assignment_model === WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL) {\n      rejections.push({\n        scope: 'lineage',\n        label: lineage.label,\n        field: 'assignment_model',\n        message: WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL_REJECTION,\n      });\n    }\n\n    const reservedFields = [];\n    if (hasNonEmptyArrayField(lineage.depends_on)) {\n      reservedFields.push('depends_on');\n    }\n    if (hasNonEmptyArrayField(lineage.touches)) {\n      reservedFields.push('touches');\n    }\n    if (reservedFields.length > 0) {\n      rejections.push({\n        scope: 'lineage',\n        label: lineage.label,\n        field: reservedFields.join(','),\n        message: WAVE_ASSIGNMENT_METADATA_REJECTION,\n      });\n    }\n  }\n\n  return rejections;\n}\n\n/**\n * Force fan-out execution onto the existing flat pool while wave planning is gated.\n *\n * @param {Object} fanoutConfig - Parsed fan-out config.\n * @returns {{ config: Object, rejections: Array<Object> }} Guarded config and rejection records.\n */\nfunction applyFlatPoolAssignmentGuard(fanoutConfig) {\n  const rejections = collectFlatPoolGuardRejections(fanoutConfig);\n  return {\n    config: {\n      ...fanoutConfig,\n      assignment_model: FLAT_POOL_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL,\n      executors: fanoutConfig.executors.map((lineage) => ({\n        ...lineage,\n        assignment_model: FLAT_POOL_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL,\n      })),\n    },\n    rejections,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction logFlatPoolGuardRejections({ rejections, ledgerPath, runId, loopType, specFolder }) {\n  if (rejections.length === 0) {\n    return;\n  }\n  const wavePlanner = createWavePlannerInterface();\n  for (const rejection of rejections) {\n    const labelSuffix = rejection.label ? ` lineage=${rejection.label}` : '';\n    process.stderr.write(`[fanout-run] ${rejection.message}${labelSuffix}\\n`);\n    appendFanoutStatusLedger(ledgerPath, {\n      event: 'assignment_model_rejected',\n      severity: 'warning',\n      at: new Date().toISOString(),\n      run_id: runId,\n      loop_type: loopType,\n      spec_folder: specFolder,\n      planner_status: wavePlanner.status,\n      fallback_assignment_model: FLAT_POOL_ASSIGNMENT_MODEL,\n      ...rejection,\n    });\n  }\n}\n\n// Per-kind first state-dir env var (used for lockfile isolation across same-kind replicas).\nconst SPECKIT_STATE_ENV_BY_KIND = {\n  'cli-codex': 'SPECKIT_CODEX_STATE_DIR',\n  'cli-claude-code': 'SPECKIT_CLAUDE_CODE_STATE_DIR',\n  'cli-opencode': 'SPECKIT_OPENCODE_STATE_DIR',\n};\n\nconst activeLineageProcesses = new Set();\nconst WAIT_CHECKPOINT_FILENAME = 'orchestration-wait-checkpoint.json';\nconst WAIT_CHECKPOINT_SCHEMA_VERSION = 1;\nconst WAIT_SLEEP_CHUNK_MS = 200;\nconst OBSERVABILITY_EVENTS_FILENAME = 'observability-events.jsonl';\nconst DEFAULT_POST_EXIT_GRACE_MS = 5 * 60 * 1000;\n\nfunction stopActiveLineageProcesses(signal) {\n  for (const child of activeLineageProcesses) {\n    terminateLineageProcess(child, signal);\n  }\n}\n\nfunction expandHomeDir(inputPath) {\n  if (inputPath === '~') {\n    return os.homedir();\n  }\n  if (typeof inputPath === 'string' && inputPath.startsWith('~/')) {\n    return path.join(os.homedir(), inputPath.slice(2));\n  }\n  return inputPath;\n}\n\nfunction isPathInside(childPath, parentPath) {\n  const relative = path.relative(parentPath, childPath);\n  return relative === '' || (!relative.startsWith('..') && !path.isAbsolute(relative));\n}\n\nfunction physicalPathForValidation(targetPath) {\n  try {\n    return fs.realpathSync.native(targetPath);\n  } catch {\n    const parentPath = path.dirname(targetPath);\n    try {\n      return path.join(fs.realpathSync.native(parentPath), path.basename(targetPath));\n    } catch {\n      return targetPath;\n    }\n  }\n}\n\nfunction validateBaseArtifactDir(baseArtifactDir, specFolder, loopType) {\n  if (baseArtifactDir.includes('\\0')) {\n    throw inputError('baseArtifactDir must not contain null bytes');\n  }\n  if (baseArtifactDir.split(/[\\\\/]+/).includes('..')) {\n    throw inputError('baseArtifactDir must not contain \"..\" path segments');\n  }\n  const resolvedBase = physicalPathForValidation(path.resolve(process.cwd(), baseArtifactDir));\n  const resolvedSpecFolder = physicalPathForValidation(path.resolve(process.cwd(), specFolder));\n  const expectedRoot = path.join(resolvedSpecFolder, loopType);\n  if (!isPathInside(resolvedBase, expectedRoot)) {\n    throw inputError(`baseArtifactDir must resolve inside the spec folder's ${loopType} artifact tree`);\n  }\n  return baseArtifactDir;\n}\n\nfunction validateClaudeConfigDir(configDir) {\n  if (typeof configDir !== 'string' || configDir.trim() === '') {\n    throw inputError('configDir must be a non-empty string when set');\n  }\n  validateNamespaceValue(configDir, 'configDir', inputError);\n\n  const expanded = expandHomeDir(configDir);\n  const resolved = path.resolve(process.cwd(), expanded);\n  const homeDir = path.resolve(os.homedir());\n  const cwd = path.resolve(process.cwd());\n  const homeRelative = path.relative(homeDir, resolved);\n  const cwdRelative = path.relative(cwd, resolved);\n  const homeTop = homeRelative.split(path.sep)[0] || '';\n  const cwdTop = cwdRelative.split(path.sep)[0] || '';\n  const allowedConfigRoot = (segment) => segment === '.claude' || segment.startsWith('.claude-');\n\n  if (isPathInside(resolved, homeDir) && allowedConfigRoot(homeTop)) {\n    return resolved;\n  }\n  if (isPathInside(resolved, cwd) && allowedConfigRoot(cwdTop)) {\n    return resolved;\n  }\n  throw inputError('configDir must resolve under ~/.claude*, or a repo-local .claude* directory');\n}\n\nfunction terminateLineageProcess(child, signal) {\n  if (!child || child.killed) return;\n  if (process.platform !== 'win32' && child.pid) {\n    try {\n      process.kill(-child.pid, signal);\n      return;\n    } catch (error) {\n      if (error && error.code !== 'ESRCH') {\n        try {\n          child.kill(signal);\n        } catch {\n          // The process may have already exited between the group and direct kill attempts.\n        }\n      }\n      return;\n    }\n  }\n  try {\n    child.kill(signal);\n  } catch {\n    // The process may have already exited.\n  }\n}\n\nfunction expectedLineageArtifactPaths(loopType, lineageDir) {\n  assertActiveFanoutLoopType(loopType);\n  if (loopType === 'review') return [path.join(lineageDir, 'review-report.md')];\n  return [path.join(lineageDir, 'research.md')];\n}\n\nfunction hasNonEmptyFile(filePath) {\n  try {\n    return fs.statSync(filePath).isFile() && fs.statSync(filePath).size > 0;\n  } catch {\n    return false;\n  }\n}\n\nfunction findMissingLineageArtifacts(loopType, lineageDir) {\n  return expectedLineageArtifactPaths(loopType, lineageDir)\n    .filter((artifactPath) => !hasNonEmptyFile(artifactPath));\n}\n\nfunction parseJsonlRecords(filePath) {\n  const text = fs.readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8');\n  return text\n    .split(/\\r?\\n/)\n    .filter((line) => line.trim() !== '')\n    .map((line) => JSON.parse(line));\n}\n\nfunction lineageStateLogName(loopType) {\n  return STATE_LOG_BY_LOOP_TYPE[loopType] || null;\n}\n\nfunction readLineageStateRecords(loopType, lineageDir) {\n  const stateLogName = lineageStateLogName(loopType);\n  if (!stateLogName) {\n    return { statePath: null, records: [], missing: true, parseError: null };\n  }\n  const statePath = path.join(lineageDir, stateLogName);\n  if (!hasNonEmptyFile(statePath)) {\n    return { statePath, records: [], missing: true, parseError: null };\n  }\n  try {\n    return { statePath, records: parseJsonlRecords(statePath), missing: false, parseError: null };\n  } catch (error) {\n    return {\n      statePath,\n      records: [],\n      missing: false,\n      parseError: error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error),\n    };\n  }\n}\n\n// A lineage's synthesis stopReason is written by its model and cannot be held to an exact\n// spelling. The iteration-count check above already proves the lineage ran every iteration,\n// so this only needs to confirm the reason belongs to the max-iterations family (e.g.\n// \"maxIterationsReached\", \"max-iterations (10/10)\") and is not a genuinely different outcome\n// such as convergence, a manual stop, or an error.\nfunction isMaxIterationsStopReason(stopReason) {\n  if (typeof stopReason !== 'string') return false;\n  return stopReason.toLowerCase().replace(/[^a-z]/g, '').startsWith('maxiteration');\n}\n\nfunction findMaxIterationsPolicyViolation({ loopType, stateRead, lineage, stopPolicy }) {\n  if (loopType !== 'review' || stopPolicy !== 'max-iterations') return null;\n  if (typeof lineage.iterations !== 'number' || lineage.iterations <= 0) {\n    return 'stopPolicy=max-iterations requires a positive lineage iteration cap';\n  }\n\n  if (!stateRead || stateRead.missing) {\n    return 'missing deep-review-state.jsonl for max-iterations stop-policy validation';\n  }\n  if (stateRead.parseError) {\n    return `could not parse deep-review-state.jsonl: ${stateRead.parseError}`;\n  }\n\n  const records = stateRead.records;\n  const iterationCount = records.filter((record) => record && record.type === 'iteration').length;\n  const synthesis = [...records]\n    .reverse()\n    .find((record) => record && record.type === 'event' && record.event === 'synthesis_complete');\n  if (!synthesis) {\n    return 'missing synthesis_complete event for max-iterations stop-policy validation';\n  }\n\n  const totalIterations = Number.isFinite(Number(synthesis.totalIterations))\n    ? Number(synthesis.totalIterations)\n    : iterationCount;\n  if (totalIterations !== lineage.iterations) {\n    return `expected ${lineage.iterations} iterations, got ${totalIterations}`;\n  }\n  if (!isMaxIterationsStopReason(synthesis.stopReason)) {\n    return `expected stopReason=maxIterationsReached, got ${synthesis.stopReason || 'unknown'}`;\n  }\n  return null;\n}\n\nfunction isRecord(value) {\n  return value !== null && typeof value === 'object' && !Array.isArray(value);\n}\n\nfunction normalizeStallWatchdogMs(rawConfig) {\n  // Defaults ON (mirrors the fan-out lagCeilingMs default): without a watchdog a stalled\n  // lineage hangs silently until the hours-scale timeout. Read through the raw alias set\n  // because this knob is intentionally outside fanoutConfigSchema. Non-disableable while\n  // running autonomously: an explicit 0 no longer opts out, it is rejected.\n  const value = readRawConfigNumber(rawConfig, [\n    'stallWatchdogMs',\n    'stall_watchdog_ms',\n    'stallWatchdogMillis',\n    'stall_watchdog_millis',\n  ], 'stallWatchdogMs');\n  if (value === 0) {\n    throw inputError('stallWatchdogMs must be greater than 0; stall detection cannot be disabled for autonomous fan-out runs');\n  }\n  return value ?? 300000;\n}\n\nconst DEFAULT_MAX_COST_UNITS_PER_LINEAGE = 72;\n\nfunction normalizeLineageBudgetGuards(rawConfig = {}) {\n  return {\n    max_cost_units_per_lineage: readRawConfigNumber(rawConfig, [\n      'maxCostUnitsPerLineage',\n      'max_cost_units_per_lineage',\n      'maxLineageCostUnits',\n      'max_lineage_cost_units',\n      'maxTokensPerLineage',\n      'max_tokens_per_lineage',\n      'maxTokenBudget',\n      'max_token_budget',\n      'maxTokenBudgetPerLineage',\n      'max_token_budget_per_lineage',\n    ], 'maxCostUnitsPerLineage') ?? DEFAULT_MAX_COST_UNITS_PER_LINEAGE,\n    cost_units_per_iteration: readPositiveRawConfigNumber(rawConfig, [\n      'costUnitsPerIteration',\n      'cost_units_per_iteration',\n      'estimatedTokensPerIteration',\n      'estimated_tokens_per_iteration',\n    ], 'costUnitsPerIteration', 1),\n  };\n}\n\nfunction computeLineageBudgetUpperBound(lineage, guardsInput = {}, maxRetries = 0) {\n  const guards = normalizeLineageBudgetGuards(guardsInput);\n  const rawIterations = Number(lineage && lineage.iterations);\n  const iterations = Number.isFinite(rawIterations) && rawIterations > 0 ? Math.floor(rawIterations) : 12;\n  const normalizedRetries = Number.isFinite(Number(maxRetries)) && Number(maxRetries) >= 0\n    ? Math.floor(Number(maxRetries))\n    : 0;\n  const totalAttempts = normalizedRetries + 1;\n  return {\n    ...guards,\n    iterations,\n    total_attempts: totalAttempts,\n    estimated_cost_units: iterations * guards.cost_units_per_iteration * totalAttempts,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction evaluateLineageBudgetCap(input = {}) {\n  const upperBound = computeLineageBudgetUpperBound(\n    input.lineage || {},\n    input.guards || input,\n    input.maxRetries,\n  );\n  const exceeded = upperBound.max_cost_units_per_lineage > 0\n    && upperBound.estimated_cost_units > upperBound.max_cost_units_per_lineage;\n  return {\n    continue_allowed: !exceeded,\n    stop_reasons: exceeded ? ['max_cost_units_per_lineage'] : [],\n    upper_bound: upperBound,\n  };\n}\n\n// Aggregate budget across every expanded lineage in a run. This is a SEPARATE ceiling\n// from DEFAULT_MAX_COST_UNITS_PER_LINEAGE above: the per-lineage cap bounds any single\n// lineage, this bounds the whole fan-out submission, and both are enforced independently\n// (a run may pass one and still fail the other).\nconst DEFAULT_MAX_AGGREGATE_COST_UNITS = 288;\n\nfunction normalizeAggregateBudgetGuards(rawConfig = {}) {\n  return {\n    max_aggregate_cost_units: readRawConfigNumber(rawConfig, [\n      'maxAggregateCostUnits',\n      'max_aggregate_cost_units',\n      'maxTotalCostUnits',\n      'max_total_cost_units',\n    ], 'maxAggregateCostUnits') ?? DEFAULT_MAX_AGGREGATE_COST_UNITS,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction computeAggregateBudgetUpperBound(lineages, guardsInput = {}, maxRetries = 0) {\n  const aggregateGuards = normalizeAggregateBudgetGuards(guardsInput);\n  const lineageGuards = normalizeLineageBudgetGuards(guardsInput);\n  const perLineage = (lineages || []).map((lineage) => {\n    const upperBound = computeLineageBudgetUpperBound(lineage, lineageGuards, maxRetries);\n    return { label: lineage && lineage.label, estimated_cost_units: upperBound.estimated_cost_units };\n  });\n  const estimatedCostUnits = perLineage.reduce((sum, entry) => sum + entry.estimated_cost_units, 0);\n  return {\n    max_aggregate_cost_units: aggregateGuards.max_aggregate_cost_units,\n    estimated_cost_units: estimatedCostUnits,\n    lineage_count: perLineage.length,\n    per_lineage: perLineage,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction evaluateAggregateBudgetCap(input = {}) {\n  const upperBound = computeAggregateBudgetUpperBound(\n    input.lineages || [],\n    input.guards || input,\n    input.maxRetries,\n  );\n  const exceeded = upperBound.max_aggregate_cost_units > 0\n    && upperBound.estimated_cost_units > upperBound.max_aggregate_cost_units;\n  return {\n    continue_allowed: !exceeded,\n    stop_reasons: exceeded ? ['max_aggregate_cost_units'] : [],\n    upper_bound: upperBound,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction buildTimestampAnomalyCounts(check) {\n  return {\n    anomalous: check.anomalous,\n    untimestamped: check.untimestamped,\n    unparseable: check.unparseable,\n    total: check.total,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction buildTimestampAnomalyPayload({ lineage, statePath, check }) {\n  return {\n    label: lineage.label,\n    state_log: statePath,\n    window: {\n      start_at_iso: check.windowStart,\n      end_at_iso: check.windowEnd,\n      tolerance_ms: check.toleranceMs,\n    },\n    counts: buildTimestampAnomalyCounts(check),\n    sample: check.sample,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction collectTimestampAnomalies(results) {\n  return results\n    .filter((result) => result && result.status === 'fulfilled' && result.output && result.output.timestamp_anomaly)\n    .map((result) => result.output.timestamp_anomaly);\n}\n\nfunction normalizeNonNegativeDelayMs(value) {\n  if (value === undefined || value === null) return null;\n  const n = Number(value);\n  if (!Number.isFinite(n) || n < 0) return null;\n  return Math.floor(n);\n}\n\nfunction normalizeWaitDurationMs(value) {\n  return normalizeNonNegativeDelayMs(value) ?? 0;\n}\n\nfunction waitCheckpointPath(baseArtifactDir) {\n  return path.join(baseArtifactDir, WAIT_CHECKPOINT_FILENAME);\n}\n\nfunction atomicWriteJson(filePath, payload) {\n  fs.mkdirSync(path.dirname(filePath), { recursive: true });\n  const tmpPath = `${filePath}.${process.pid}.${Date.now()}.tmp`;\n  fs.writeFileSync(tmpPath, `${JSON.stringify(payload, null, 2)}\\n`, 'utf8');\n  fs.renameSync(tmpPath, filePath);\n}\n\nfunction buildWaitCheckpoint({ waitMs, runId, loopType, specFolder, nowMs = Date.now() }) {\n  const durationMs = normalizeWaitDurationMs(waitMs);\n  const updatedAt = new Date(nowMs).toISOString();\n  if (durationMs <= 0) {\n    return {\n      schemaVersion: WAIT_CHECKPOINT_SCHEMA_VERSION,\n      status: 'idle',\n      nextRunAt: null,\n      remainingDelayMs: null,\n      updatedAt,\n      runId,\n      loopType,\n      specFolder,\n    };\n  }\n\n  return {\n    schemaVersion: WAIT_CHECKPOINT_SCHEMA_VERSION,\n    status: 'waiting',\n    nextRunAt: new Date(nowMs + durationMs).toISOString(),\n    remainingDelayMs: durationMs,\n    updatedAt,\n    runId,\n    loopType,\n    specFolder,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction normalizeWaitCheckpoint(raw, context) {\n  if (!isRecord(raw)) {\n    throw inputError('wait checkpoint must be a JSON object');\n  }\n\n  const nowMs = Number.isFinite(Number(context.nowMs)) ? Number(context.nowMs) : Date.now();\n  const hasNextRunAt = Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(raw, 'nextRunAt');\n  const hasRemainingDelayMs = Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(raw, 'remainingDelayMs');\n  const nextRunAt = typeof raw.nextRunAt === 'string' && raw.nextRunAt.trim() !== ''\n    ? raw.nextRunAt\n    : null;\n  const nextRunAtMs = nextRunAt === null ? NaN : Date.parse(nextRunAt);\n  const waiting = Number.isFinite(nextRunAtMs) && nextRunAtMs > nowMs;\n  const remainingDelayMs = waiting ? Math.max(0, Math.ceil(nextRunAtMs - nowMs)) : null;\n  const base = {\n    runId: typeof raw.runId === 'string' && raw.runId ? raw.runId : context.runId,\n    loopType: typeof raw.loopType === 'string' && raw.loopType ? raw.loopType : context.loopType,\n    specFolder: typeof raw.specFolder === 'string' && raw.specFolder ? raw.specFolder : context.specFolder,\n  };\n\n  const checkpoint = waiting\n    ? {\n        schemaVersion: WAIT_CHECKPOINT_SCHEMA_VERSION,\n        status: 'waiting',\n        nextRunAt,\n        remainingDelayMs,\n        updatedAt: new Date(nowMs).toISOString(),\n        ...base,\n      }\n    : buildWaitCheckpoint({ waitMs: 0, nowMs, ...base });\n  const staleWaitingFields = !waiting\n    && (raw.nextRunAt !== null || raw.remainingDelayMs !== null || raw.status === 'waiting');\n  const staleRemainingDelay = waiting && Number(raw.remainingDelayMs) !== remainingDelayMs;\n\n  return {\n    checkpoint,\n    migrated: !hasNextRunAt || !hasRemainingDelayMs || staleWaitingFields || staleRemainingDelay,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction readWaitCheckpoint(checkpointPath, context) {\n  if (!fs.existsSync(checkpointPath)) {\n    return { exists: false, checkpoint: null, migrated: false };\n  }\n\n  let raw;\n  try {\n    raw = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(checkpointPath, 'utf8'));\n  } catch (error) {\n    throw inputError(\n      `wait checkpoint is not valid JSON: ${error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error)}`,\n    );\n  }\n\n  const normalized = normalizeWaitCheckpoint(raw, context);\n  if (normalized.migrated) {\n    atomicWriteJson(checkpointPath, normalized.checkpoint);\n  }\n  return { exists: true, ...normalized };\n}\n\nfunction sleepWaitChunk(ms) {\n  return new Promise((resolvePromise) => setTimeout(resolvePromise, ms));\n}\n\nasync function waitUntilCheckpointExpires({ checkpointPath, checkpoint, context, sleep = sleepWaitChunk }) {\n  const nextRunAtMs = Date.parse(checkpoint.nextRunAt);\n  let remainingDelayMs = Math.max(0, Math.ceil(nextRunAtMs - Date.now()));\n\n  while (remainingDelayMs > 0) {\n    atomicWriteJson(checkpointPath, {\n      ...checkpoint,\n      remainingDelayMs,\n      updatedAt: new Date().toISOString(),\n    });\n    await sleep(Math.min(remainingDelayMs, WAIT_SLEEP_CHUNK_MS));\n    remainingDelayMs = Math.max(0, Math.ceil(nextRunAtMs - Date.now()));\n  }\n\n  atomicWriteJson(checkpointPath, buildWaitCheckpoint({ waitMs: 0, ...context }));\n}\n\nasync function resumeWaitingCheckpoint({ checkpointPath, ledgerPath, runId, loopType, specFolder }) {\n  const context = { runId, loopType, specFolder, nowMs: Date.now() };\n  const loaded = readWaitCheckpoint(checkpointPath, context);\n  if (!loaded.checkpoint || loaded.checkpoint.status !== 'waiting') {\n    return { didWait: false, migrated: loaded.migrated };\n  }\n\n  appendFanoutStatusLedger(ledgerPath, {\n    event: 'resume_waiting',\n    at: new Date().toISOString(),\n    run_id: runId,\n    loop_type: loopType,\n    spec_folder: specFolder,\n    nextRunAt: loaded.checkpoint.nextRunAt,\n    remainingDelayMs: loaded.checkpoint.remainingDelayMs,\n  });\n\n  await waitUntilCheckpointExpires({\n    checkpointPath,\n    checkpoint: loaded.checkpoint,\n    context: { runId, loopType, specFolder },\n  });\n\n  appendFanoutStatusLedger(ledgerPath, {\n    event: 'resume_waiting_complete',\n    at: new Date().toISOString(),\n    run_id: runId,\n    loop_type: loopType,\n    spec_folder: specFolder,\n  });\n\n  return { didWait: true, migrated: loaded.migrated };\n}\n\nasync function persistPreDispatchWait({ checkpointPath, ledgerPath, runId, loopType, specFolder, waitMs }) {\n  const durationMs = normalizeWaitDurationMs(waitMs);\n  if (durationMs <= 0) {\n    return { didWait: false };\n  }\n\n  const checkpoint = buildWaitCheckpoint({ waitMs: durationMs, runId, loopType, specFolder });\n  atomicWriteJson(checkpointPath, checkpoint);\n  appendFanoutStatusLedger(ledgerPath, {\n    event: 'wait_checkpoint_persisted',\n    at: checkpoint.updatedAt,\n    run_id: runId,\n    loop_type: loopType,\n    spec_folder: specFolder,\n    nextRunAt: checkpoint.nextRunAt,\n    remainingDelayMs: checkpoint.remainingDelayMs,\n  });\n\n  await waitUntilCheckpointExpires({\n    checkpointPath,\n    checkpoint,\n    context: { runId, loopType, specFolder },\n  });\n\n  appendFanoutStatusLedger(ledgerPath, {\n    event: 'wait_checkpoint_cleared',\n    at: new Date().toISOString(),\n    run_id: runId,\n    loop_type: loopType,\n    spec_folder: specFolder,\n  });\n\n  return { didWait: true };\n}\n\n/**\n * Build the \"run the full loop\" prompt text for a CLI lineage subprocess.\n * The subprocess reads this, loads the skill, and runs the requested stop policy\n * with config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir overriding step_resolve_artifact_root.\n */\nfunction buildLoopPrompt(loopType, specFolder, lineageDir, sessionId, lineage, researchTopic, options = {}) {\n  assertActiveFanoutLoopType(loopType);\n  const skillFile =\n    loopType === 'review'\n      ? '.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/SKILL.md'\n      : '.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md';\n  const agentName = loopType === 'review' ? 'deep-review' : 'deep-research';\n  const detachedIntro = lineage.kind === 'cli-opencode'\n    ? [\n        `This is an explicit parallel-detached OpenCode lineage, not a self-invocation of the parent session.`,\n        `Use the separate lineage directory and session id below as the detached state boundary.`,\n        ``,\n      ]\n    : lineage.kind === 'native'\n      ? [\n          `This is an explicit native fan-out adapter running through the command host's OpenCode CLI surface.`,\n          `Use the separate lineage directory and session id below as the detached state boundary.`,\n          ``,\n        ]\n      : [];\n  const hasIterationCap = typeof lineage.iterations === 'number' && lineage.iterations > 0;\n  const stopPolicy = options.stopPolicy || 'convergence';\n  const stopClause = hasIterationCap && stopPolicy === 'max-iterations'\n    ? 'until config.maxIterations is reached; treat convergence before that as telemetry only and broaden review angles instead of synthesizing early'\n    : hasIterationCap\n      ? 'to legal convergence OR config.maxIterations, whichever comes first'\n      : 'to legal convergence';\n  const params = [\n    `  spec_folder: ${specFolder}`,\n    `  config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: ${lineageDir}`,\n    `  session_id: ${sessionId}`,\n    `  executor: ${lineage.kind} model=${lineage.model || 'default'}`,\n    `  loop_type: ${loopType}`,\n    `  config.stopPolicy: ${stopPolicy}`,\n  ];\n  if (researchTopic) {\n    // A research lineage's phase_init binds research_topic from this line. Without it a\n    // fan-out research loop has no question to investigate and degrades to an empty topic.\n    // Review loops scope by spec_folder and intentionally pass no topic.\n    params.push(`  research_topic: ${researchTopic}`);\n  }\n  if (hasIterationCap) {\n    params.push(`  config.maxIterations: ${lineage.iterations}`);\n  }\n  if (options.convergenceThreshold !== null && options.convergenceThreshold !== undefined) {\n    params.push(`  config.convergenceThreshold: ${options.convergenceThreshold}`);\n  }\n  // Review lineages scope by spec_folder but the auto-workflow preflight\n  // still requires the same review setup bindings the native command path pre-binds.\n  // Without these, a detached CLI lineage can fail first-run initialization or infer a\n  // different setup contract than native lineages.\n  const setupBindings =\n    loopType === 'review'\n      ? [\n          ``,\n          `Review setup bindings (emit before any writes, same as native PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS):`,\n          `review_target: ${specFolder}`,\n          `review_target_type: spec-folder`,\n          `review_dimensions: all`,\n          `spec_folder: ${specFolder}`,\n          `execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS`,\n          `lineage_mode: auto`,\n          ``,\n        ]\n      : [];\n  return [\n    `You are orchestrating the ${agentName} workflow YAML as a detached fan-out lineage.`,\n    ...detachedIntro,\n    ``,\n    `Read ${skillFile} and execute the ${loopType} loop with these parameters:`,\n    ...params,\n    ...setupBindings,\n    `The step_resolve_artifact_root step will bind artifact_dir to ${lineageDir} via the`,\n    `config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir override — do NOT run the resolveArtifactRoot node`,\n    `command; bind artifact_dir directly to the override value.`,\n    ``,\n    `Run phase_init, phase_main_loop (${stopClause}), and phase_synthesis.`,\n    `Write all outputs to ${lineageDir}. Do not touch any path outside ${lineageDir}.`,\n    ``,\n    `When complete, output a single line: FANOUT_LINEAGE_COMPLETE:${lineage.label}`,\n  ].join('\\n');\n}\n\nfunction buildNativeCommandInput(loopType, specFolder, lineageDir, lineage, options = {}) {\n  assertActiveFanoutLoopType(loopType);\n  const maxIterations = lineage.iterations || 12;\n  const convergenceThreshold = options.convergenceThreshold ?? (loopType === 'research' ? 0.05 : 0.1);\n  const stopPolicy = options.stopPolicy || 'convergence';\n  const sessionId = options.sessionId || '';\n  const args = [\n    ':auto',\n    JSON.stringify(specFolder),\n    `--spec-folder=${specFolder}`,\n    `--max-iterations=${maxIterations}`,\n    `--convergence=${convergenceThreshold}`,\n    `--stop-policy=${stopPolicy}`,\n    `--fanout-lineage-artifact-dir=${lineageDir}`,\n    '--lineage-mode=auto',\n  ];\n  if (loopType === 'research' && options.researchTopic) {\n    args.push(`--research-topic=${JSON.stringify(options.researchTopic)}`);\n  }\n\n  return [\n    args.join(' '),\n    '',\n    'PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:',\n    `review_target: ${specFolder}`,\n    'review_target_type: spec-folder',\n    'review_dimensions: all',\n    `spec_folder: ${specFolder}`,\n    ...(sessionId ? [`session_id: ${sessionId}`] : []),\n    'execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS',\n    'lineage_mode: auto',\n    `maxIterations: ${maxIterations}`,\n    `convergenceThreshold: ${convergenceThreshold}`,\n    `stop_policy: ${stopPolicy}`,\n    `config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: ${lineageDir}`,\n  ].join('\\n');\n}\n\n// Full-lineage lifetime is non-disableable in autonomous mode: 4 hours is the hard\n// ceiling and a positive override may only narrow it, never widen past it.\nconst LINEAGE_LIFETIME_HARD_MAX_HOURS = 4;\n\nfunction assertLineageTimeoutHoursOverrideWithinCeiling(ceilingHoursOverride) {\n  if (Number.isFinite(ceilingHoursOverride) && ceilingHoursOverride > LINEAGE_LIFETIME_HARD_MAX_HOURS) {\n    throw inputError(\n      `lineageTimeoutHours override (${ceilingHoursOverride}) exceeds the hard maximum of `\n        + `${LINEAGE_LIFETIME_HARD_MAX_HOURS} hours`,\n    );\n  }\n}\n\n/**\n * Compute a generous timeout for a full lineage loop run.\n * A single iteration is timeoutSeconds; a full loop is up to iterations * timeoutSeconds.\n * We double it for safety and cap at 4 hours. A caller-provided ceiling override may only\n * narrow this hard ceiling, never widen it — full-lineage lifetime is non-disableable.\n */\nfunction computeLineageTimeoutMs(lineage, ceilingHoursOverride) {\n  assertLineageTimeoutHoursOverrideWithinCeiling(ceilingHoursOverride);\n  const iters = lineage.iterations || 12;\n  const perIterSecs = lineage.timeoutSeconds || 900;\n  const ceilingMs = Number.isFinite(ceilingHoursOverride) && ceilingHoursOverride > 0\n    ? ceilingHoursOverride * 60 * 60 * 1000\n    : LINEAGE_LIFETIME_HARD_MAX_HOURS * 60 * 60 * 1000;\n  return Math.min(iters * perIterSecs * 2 * 1000, ceilingMs);\n}\n\nfunction normalizeProgressHeartbeatMs(seconds) {\n  const value = Number(seconds);\n  if (!Number.isFinite(value) || value <= 0) return 0;\n  return Math.max(1, Math.floor(value * 1000));\n}\n\nfunction normalizePostExitGraceMs(rawConfig, progressHeartbeatMs = 0) {\n  const explicit = readRawConfigNumber(rawConfig, [\n    'postExitGraceMs',\n    'post_exit_grace_ms',\n    'postSubprocessExitGraceMs',\n    'post_subprocess_exit_grace_ms',\n    'orchestratorPostExitGraceMs',\n    'orchestrator_post_exit_grace_ms',\n  ], 'postExitGraceMs');\n  if (explicit !== null) return explicit;\n\n  const heartbeatDerived = Number.isFinite(progressHeartbeatMs) && progressHeartbeatMs > 0\n    ? progressHeartbeatMs * 2\n    : 0;\n  return Math.max(DEFAULT_POST_EXIT_GRACE_MS, heartbeatDerived);\n}\n\nfunction slotDurationMsFromHrtime(hrStart) {\n  const [seconds, nanoseconds] = process.hrtime(hrStart);\n  return Math.max(0, (seconds * 1000) + (nanoseconds / 1e6));\n}\n\nfunction computeSkippedCount(slotDurationMs, intervalMs) {\n  const elapsed = Number(slotDurationMs);\n  const interval = Number(intervalMs);\n  if (!Number.isFinite(elapsed) || !Number.isFinite(interval) || interval <= 0) {\n    return 0;\n  }\n  return Math.max(0, Math.floor(elapsed / interval) - 1);\n}\n\nfunction buildSlotAccounting(hrStart, intervalMs) {\n  const slotDurationMs = slotDurationMsFromHrtime(hrStart);\n  return {\n    slotDurationMs,\n    skippedCount: computeSkippedCount(slotDurationMs, intervalMs),\n  };\n}\n\nfunction decorateSlotAccountingEvent(event, accountingByLabel) {\n  if (!event || typeof event.label !== 'string') return event;\n  if (event.event !== 'completed' && event.event !== 'failed') return event;\n\n  const accounting = accountingByLabel.get(event.label);\n  if (!accounting) return event;\n  return {\n    ...event,\n    skippedCount: accounting.skippedCount,\n    slotDurationMs: accounting.slotDurationMs,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction startLineageProgressHeartbeat({ cadenceMs, label, ledgerPath, getGauges, onProgress }) {\n  if (!Number.isFinite(cadenceMs) || cadenceMs <= 0) {\n    return () => {};\n  }\n  const startedAtMs = Date.now();\n  const timer = setInterval(() => {\n    appendFanoutStatusLedger(ledgerPath, {\n      event: 'progress',\n      label,\n      at: new Date().toISOString(),\n      duration_ms: Math.max(0, Date.now() - startedAtMs),\n        gauges: getGauges(),\n      });\n      if (typeof onProgress === 'function') onProgress();\n    }, cadenceMs);\n  timer.unref?.();\n  return () => clearInterval(timer);\n}\n\nfunction startLineageStallWatchdog({ thresholdMs, label, ledgerPath, getLastEventAtMs, getGauges }) {\n  if (!Number.isFinite(thresholdMs) || thresholdMs <= 0) {\n    return () => {};\n  }\n\n  let timer = null;\n  let fired = false;\n  const schedule = () => {\n    if (fired) return;\n    const quietMs = Math.max(0, Date.now() - getLastEventAtMs());\n    const delayMs = Math.max(1, thresholdMs - quietMs);\n    timer = setTimeout(() => {\n      timer = null;\n      const latestQuietMs = Math.max(0, Date.now() - getLastEventAtMs());\n      if (latestQuietMs >= thresholdMs) {\n        fired = true;\n        appendFanoutStatusLedger(ledgerPath, {\n          event: 'stall_detected',\n          label,\n          at: new Date().toISOString(),\n          severity: 'warning',\n          metric: 'time_since_last_lineage_event',\n          stall_watchdog_ms: thresholdMs,\n          quiet_ms: Math.floor(latestQuietMs),\n          gauges: getGauges(),\n        });\n        return;\n      }\n      schedule();\n    }, delayMs);\n    timer.unref?.();\n  };\n\n  schedule();\n  return () => {\n    fired = true;\n    if (timer) clearTimeout(timer);\n  };\n}\n\n/**\n * Run a lineage subprocess without blocking the Node event loop.\n *\n * Resolves a spawnSync-shaped result ({ status, signal, stdout, error }) so the\n * pool's K-in-flight cap actually overlaps lineages. spawnSync blocked the single\n * thread until each child exited, serializing every lineage regardless of the\n * concurrency cap; an awaited async spawn yields to the loop so K run at once.\n *\n * On timeout the child is killed with SIGTERM and result.signal is set to\n * 'SIGTERM', preserving the timeout-as-failure signal the caller relies on.\n *\n * @param {string} command - Executable to run.\n * @param {string[]} cmdArgs - Arguments for the executable.\n * @param {Object} opts - { cwd, env, timeoutMs, maxBuffer, input? }.\n * @returns {Promise<{status:number|null, signal:string|null, stdout:string, error?:Error}>}\n */\nfunction runLineageProcess(command, cmdArgs, opts) {\n  const { cwd, env, timeoutMs, maxBuffer } = opts;\n  const hasInput = typeof opts.input === 'string';\n\n  return new Promise((resolvePromise) => {\n    let child;\n    try {\n      child = spawn(command, cmdArgs, {\n        cwd,\n        env,\n        stdio: [hasInput ? 'pipe' : 'ignore', 'pipe', 'pipe'],\n        detached: process.platform !== 'win32',\n      });\n    } catch (error) {\n      resolvePromise({ status: null, signal: null, stdout: '', error });\n      return;\n    }\n    activeLineageProcesses.add(child);\n    if (typeof opts.onSpawn === 'function') {\n      opts.onSpawn({ pid: child.pid });\n    }\n\n    let stdout = '';\n    let stdoutBytes = 0;\n    let truncated = false;\n    let timedOut = false;\n    let settled = false;\n    let spawnError;\n\n    const timer = setTimeout(() => {\n      timedOut = true;\n      terminateLineageProcess(child, 'SIGTERM');\n    }, timeoutMs);\n    timer.unref?.();\n\n    const abortHandler = () => {\n      terminateLineageProcess(child, 'SIGTERM');\n    };\n    if (opts.abortSignal) {\n      if (opts.abortSignal.aborted) {\n        abortHandler();\n      } else {\n        opts.abortSignal.addEventListener('abort', abortHandler, { once: true });\n      }\n    }\n\n    child.stdout?.setEncoding('utf8');\n    child.stdout?.on('data', (chunk) => {\n      if (typeof opts.onOutput === 'function') opts.onOutput();\n      if (truncated) return;\n      stdoutBytes += Buffer.byteLength(chunk, 'utf8');\n      if (stdoutBytes > maxBuffer) {\n        truncated = true;\n        terminateLineageProcess(child, 'SIGTERM');\n        return;\n      }\n      stdout += chunk;\n    });\n    // Drain stderr so the child never blocks on a full pipe; we do not capture it.\n    child.stderr?.resume();\n\n    child.on('error', (error) => {\n      spawnError = error;\n    });\n\n    child.on('close', (code, signal) => {\n      if (settled) return;\n      settled = true;\n      activeLineageProcesses.delete(child);\n      clearTimeout(timer);\n      opts.abortSignal?.removeEventListener?.('abort', abortHandler);\n      const effectiveSignal = timedOut ? 'SIGTERM' : signal;\n      if (typeof opts.onExit === 'function') {\n        opts.onExit({ status: timedOut ? null : code, signal: effectiveSignal, pid: child.pid, exitedAtMs: Date.now() });\n      }\n      resolvePromise({\n        status: timedOut ? null : code,\n        signal: effectiveSignal,\n        stdout,\n        ...(spawnError ? { error: spawnError } : {}),\n      });\n    });\n\n    if (hasInput) {\n      child.stdin?.on('error', () => {});\n      child.stdin?.end(opts.input);\n    }\n  });\n}\n\nfunction digestText(value) {\n  return createHash('sha256').update(String(value)).digest('hex');\n}\n\nconst executableIdentityCache = new Map();\n\nfunction resolveExecutableVersion(command, options = {}) {\n  if (typeof options.executableVersion === 'string' && options.executableVersion.trim()) {\n    return options.executableVersion.trim();\n  }\n  const env = options.env || process.env;\n  const pathEntries = String(env.PATH || '').split(path.delimiter).filter(Boolean);\n  for (const entry of pathEntries) {\n    const candidate = path.join(entry, command);\n    try {\n      const executablePath = fs.realpathSync(candidate);\n      const stat = fs.statSync(executablePath);\n      if (!stat.isFile()) continue;\n      const cacheKey = `${executablePath}:${stat.size}:${stat.mtimeMs}`;\n      const cached = executableIdentityCache.get(cacheKey);\n      if (cached) return cached;\n      const identity = `sha256:${createHash('sha256').update(fs.readFileSync(executablePath)).digest('hex')}`;\n      executableIdentityCache.set(cacheKey, identity);\n      return identity;\n    } catch {}\n  }\n  return 'unknown';\n}\n\nfunction effectiveWebSearchPolicy(lineage) {\n  return lineage.liveTools?.webSearch || 'inherit';\n}\n\n/**\n * Build the allowlisted fingerprint payload without raw prompts or environment maps.\n *\n * @param {Object} input - Resolved invocation fields.\n * @returns {Object} Canonical JSON-safe payload.\n */\nfunction buildInvocationFingerprintPayload(input) {\n  const promptDigest = digestText(input.prompt);\n  const promptArgIndexes = new Set(input.promptArgIndexes || []);\n  const argv = input.args.map((arg, index) => (\n    promptArgIndexes.has(index) ? `<prompt:${promptDigest}>` : arg\n  ));\n  return {\n    kind: input.kind,\n    executable: input.command,\n    executableVersion: input.executableVersion || 'unknown',\n    model: input.model,\n    effort: input.reasoningEffort,\n    tier: input.serviceTier,\n    sandboxPosture: {\n      sandboxMode: input.resolvedSandbox,\n      permissionMode: input.resolvedPermission,\n    },\n    webSearch: input.webSearch,\n    argv,\n    promptDigest,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction finalizeLineageCommand(input) {\n  const effectiveConfig = {\n    kind: input.kind,\n    executable: input.command,","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":1444,"totalLines":1445,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs","time":{"start":1784691892213,"end":1784691892273}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0c2ff4dd619f1f4b016a603cb426d4819191cda2c56c577770"}},"id":"prt_f87ed1fbc001rVAD1pQtg5EcVp","sessionID":"ses_07813ae6bffeXSfNUcMKmjadEz","messageID":"msg_f87ecf9df001hwbObtyOL00KA7"}}
