{"type":"text","timestamp":1784693374900,"sessionID":"ses_07813ae6bffeXSfNUcMKmjadEz","part":{"id":"prt_f8803b6f2001myPqOOncp9p7Yr","messageID":"msg_f88033fd9001eqFcx057XJdvIV","sessionID":"ses_07813ae6bffeXSfNUcMKmjadEz","type":"text","text":"The maintainability pass passed with one P2 synchronization risk; existing tests currently detect divergence but do not make the cohort single-source. I’m finishing the bounded review with repeated correctness, resilience, integration, adversarial, and final-convergence passes, preserving the three substantive open findings and avoiding any product-code edits.","time":{"start":1784693372658,"end":1784693374895},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_00a2830b48040826016a60427c8dd08191989fbda1f2171d11","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784693547354,"sessionID":"ses_07813ae6bffeXSfNUcMKmjadEz","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_XNAANTqdo3Fukck0kjgUbHsF","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/013-compiled-coverage-buildout/review/lineages/luna-xhigh/prompts/iteration-006.md\n+DEEP-REVIEW\n+\n+Iteration: 6 of 10\n+Focus: correctness adjudication\n+Review angle: refresh generation races, write ordering, manifest identity, and whether F001 is confirmed or downgraded.\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/013-compiled-coverage-buildout/review/lineages/luna-xhigh/iterations/iteration-006.md\n+# Iteration 6: Refresh Correctness Adjudication\n+\n+## Files Reviewed\n+- `.opencode/bin/lib/compiled-route-manifest.cjs:535-595`\n+- `.opencode/bin/tests/compiled-route-manifest.test.cjs:457-472,501-600`\n+- `.opencode/bin/compiled-route-manifest.cjs:63-77`\n+\n+## Findings\n+- F001 remains confirmed P1. `refreshCanonicalManifest` reads the existing generation, compiles outside any lock, and performs a plain overwrite at `.opencode/bin/lib/compiled-route-manifest.cjs:550-588`. Two refresh processes can therefore compile from the same generation and both write, with the later write replacing the earlier policy while returning its own generation.\n+- The concurrent test at `compiled-route-manifest.test.cjs:457-472` covers only mint's atomic create-if-absent path, not refresh's read/compile/overwrite race.\n+- No new P0, P1, or P2 finding was identified. F002, F003, and F004 remain active from prior passes.\n+\n+## Edge Cases\n+- Compile errors return before the write, preserving fail-closed behavior.\n+- Invalid or missing manifests are rejected before compilation.\n+- These safeguards do not serialize two valid refreshes against the same prior generation.\n+\n+## Next Focus\n+- dimension: integration\n+- focus area: parity harness, resolver, sync tooling, and cross-surface behavior\n+- reason: refresh race remains the only implementation P1; check whether integration tests catch or conceal it\n+\n+Review verdict: CONDITIONAL\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/013-compiled-coverage-buildout/review/lineages/luna-xhigh/deltas/iter-006.jsonl\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":6,\"mode\":\"review\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-review\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=review target_agent=deep-review\",\"run\":6,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"correctness adjudication: refresh generation races\",\"dimensions\":[\"correctness\"],\"findingsCount\":4,\"findingsSummary\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":2,\"P2\":2},\"findingsNew\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"findingDetails\":[{\"findingId\":\"F001\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"title\":\"Concurrent refreshes can lose a generation/policy update\",\"file\":\".opencode/bin/lib/compiled-route-manifest.cjs\",\"line\":588,\"description\":\"Refresh reads, compiles, and plain-overwrites without serialization or compare-and-swap.\",\"status\":\"active\"},{\"findingId\":\"F002\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"title\":\"Completion status conflicts with required packet gates\",\"file\":\"checklist.md\",\"line\":58,\"description\":\"Complete status coexists with open P1 checklist rows and planned metadata.\",\"status\":\"active\"},{\"findingId\":\"F003\",\"severity\":\"P2\",\"title\":\"SD-015 limitation and follow-up are stale\",\"file\":\"implementation-summary.md\",\"line\":208,\"description\":\"A dedicated SD-015 lock-in test exists although the summary says it does not.\",\"status\":\"active\"},{\"findingId\":\"F004\",\"severity\":\"P2\",\"title\":\"Default-on cohort is maintained in multiple independently edited sources\",\"file\":\".opencode/bin/lib/compiled-routing/011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs\",\"line\":34,\"description\":\"Runtime, authored, and advisor cohort literals require coordinated updates.\",\"status\":\"active\"}],\"traceabilityChecks\":{\"summary\":{\"required\":3,\"executed\":3,\"pass\":1,\"partial\":2,\"fail\":0,\"blocked\":0,\"notApplicable\":0,\"gatingFailures\":0},\"results\":[{\"name\":\"refresh_identity\",\"status\":\"fail\"},{\"name\":\"compile_error_boundary\",\"status\":\"pass\"},{\"name\":\"manifest_validation\",\"status\":\"pass\"}]},\"newFindingsRatio\":0.0,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Adjudication confirmed F001 with direct source and test evidence; no new finding.\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-luna-xhigh-1784691838667-iv78vk\",\"generation\":1,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-22T04:24:00.000Z\"}\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/013-compiled-coverage-buildout/review/lineages/luna-xhigh/prompts/iteration-007.md\n+DEEP-REVIEW\n+\n+Iteration: 7 of 10\n+Focus: integration\n+Review angle: resolver, parity harness, promoted closure, sync verification, and cross-hub default-on behavior.\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/013-compiled-coverage-buildout/review/lineages/luna-xhigh/iterations/iteration-007.md\n+# Iteration 7: Cross-Surface Integration\n+\n+## Files Reviewed\n+- `.opencode/bin/compiled-routing-foundation.vitest.ts:38-181`\n+- `.opencode/bin/compiled-route-sync.cjs:103-175,300-399`\n+- `.opencode/bin/lib/compiled-routing/011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs:52-122`\n+- `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/compiled-routing-parity.cjs`\n+\n+## Findings\n+- The integration controls are coherent: the resolver fails safe on invalid flags, stale authority, identity mismatch, and engine errors; the promoted closure has a no-specs-read verification path; and the foundation suite cross-checks advisor/runtime cohort equality.\n+- No new finding was confirmed. F001 remains a manifest-refresh correctness issue outside the normal serving request path. F002, F003, and F004 remain active.\n+\n+## Confirmed-Clean Surfaces\n+- The fleet kill-switch and default-on truth table are tested across all seven hubs.\n+- Parity classification retains drift for real route/resource mismatches rather than masking them.\n+- Sync verification exercises all hubs and reports zero spec-tree reads.\n+\n+## Next Focus\n+- dimension: resilience\n+- focus area: malformed inputs, missing artifacts, invalid flags, and recovery behavior\n+- reason: integration surfaces are covered; resilience is the remaining edge-case frontier\n+\n+Review verdict: CONDITIONAL\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/013-compiled-coverage-buildout/review/lineages/luna-xhigh/deltas/iter-007.jsonl\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":7,\"mode\":\"review\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-review\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=review target_agent=deep-review\",\"run\":7,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"integration: resolver, parity, and promoted closure\",\"dimensions\":[\"correctness\",\"security\"],\"findingsCount\":4,\"findingsSummary\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":2,\"P2\":2},\"findingsNew\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"findingDetails\":[{\"findingId\":\"F001\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"title\":\"Concurrent refreshes can lose a generation/policy update\",\"file\":\".opencode/bin/lib/compiled-route-manifest.cjs\",\"line\":588,\"description\":\"R