ting-cutover/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-alignment-presentation.txt:\n  Line 215: Run an iterative loop for conformance auditing: initialize the `alignment/` packet under `{artifact_dir}` (resolved via `resolveArtifactRoot()` — root specs use `{spec_folder}/alignment/`; child phases use a local packet dir inside that target's `alignment/` folder), resolve one or more lanes (`authority` x `artifactClass` x `scope`), discover each lane's corpus through its adapter, dispatch a fresh `@deep-alignment` LEAF agent per lane-slice iteration, evaluate the coverage-AND-stability gate, and synthesize per-lane findings into one `alignment-report.md`. The loop is READ-ONLY by default; remediation is a separate, operator-gated follow-up run.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-skill-benchmark-confirm.yaml:\n  Line 119:         on_fail: \"Report the loop host's own STATUS=FAIL and error verbatim; do not synthesize a verdict.\"\n\n  Line 128:         description: \"Report the loop-host-owned verdict; the report content is owned by the loop host, never synthesized here\"\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-alignment-confirm.yaml:\n  Line 188:           skip_to: phase_synthesis\n\n  Line 415:         if_converged: { proceed_to: phase_synthesis }\n\n  Line 416:         if_stop_max_iterations: { log: \"Max iterations ({max_iterations}) reached without full convergence; proceeding to synthesis with current coverage/stability as recorded evidence.\", proceed_to: phase_synthesis }\n\n  Line 417:         if_nothing_to_converge: { log: \"Zero applicable lanes -- nothing to converge. Proceeding to synthesis.\", proceed_to: phase_synthesis }\n\n  Line 423:   phase_synthesis:\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-skill-benchmark-auto.yaml:\n  Line 96:         on_fail: \"Report the loop host's own STATUS=FAIL and error verbatim; do not synthesize a verdict.\"\n\n  Line 105:         description: \"Report the loop-host-owned verdict; the report content is owned by the loop host, never synthesized here\"\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-skill-benchmark-presentation.txt:\n  Line 87: The JSON report is the machine record (verdict, D1-D5, funnel, ranked bottlenecks, scenario rows); the Markdown report is rendered FROM the JSON (anti-drift). The loop host owns both; this router never synthesizes a verdict.\n\n  Line 93: | Loop host STATUS=FAIL | Report the loop host's error verbatim; do not synthesize a verdict |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/legacy/deep-review.body.md:\n  Line 124: The YAML workflow runs iterative code review by initializing a review packet under `{artifact_dir}`, dispatching fresh deep-review LEAF agents, evaluating convergence across configured review dimensions, and synthesizing findings into `review-report.md` plus optional `resource-map.md`. Convergence uses the review-specific `convergenceThreshold` severity-weighted finding ratio; do not transfer sibling defaults from deep-research or deep-ai-council. Code graph tool IDs remain stable as `code_graph_query` and `code_graph_context`; implementation and docs live under `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/`.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-review-auto.yaml:\n  Line 95:   legacy_root_report: \"{spec_folder}/review-report.md\"\n\n  Line 111:   review_output: \"{artifact_dir}/review-rep