{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784693596453,"sessionID":"ses_07813ae6bffeXSfNUcMKmjadEz","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_UA1QOpbEs58K1L1kdP0lmg70","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-review-auto.yaml","offset":1640,"limit":390},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-review-auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1640:       step_loop_decision:\n1641:         action: \"Return to step_read_state for next iteration\"\n1642:         goto: step_read_state\n1643: \n1644:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1645:   # PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n1646:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1647:   phase_synthesis:\n1648:     purpose: Compile all iteration findings into review/review-report.md\n1649:     steps:\n1650: \n1651:       step_fanout_merge:\n1652:         description: \"Merge N lineage registries with strongest-restriction; bind p0/p1/p2 counts for step_derive_verdict; skip when single-executor\"\n1653:         skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n1654:         command: |\n1655:           node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs \\\n1656:             --loop-type review \\\n1657:             --artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n1658:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1659:         wait_for_completion: true\n1660:         bind_from_output:\n1661:           p0_count: \"active_p0\"\n1662:           p1_count: \"active_p1\"\n1663:           p2_count: \"active_p2\"\n1664: \n1665:       step_hydrate_summary_metrics:\n1666:         action: \"Hydrate summary metrics before synthesis\"\n1667:         read:\n1668:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1669:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1670:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1671:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1672:         extract:\n1673:           - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n1674:           - p0_count: \"Total P0 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n1675:           - p1_count: \"Total P1 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n1676:           - p2_count: \"Total P2 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n1677:           - dimensions_covered: \"List of reviewed dimensions\"\n1678:           - dimension_coverage: \"covered / total\"\n1679:           - ac_coverage_signal: \"For spec-folder targets only: if level is 2+ and checklist.md exists and implementation-summary.md is in-progress or later, surface the AC_COVERAGE advisory status; otherwise mark exempt.\"\n1680:           - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records\"\n1681:           - reason: \"Use the latest stop reason if present, else the frozen default 'converged'. (Must be a member of the STOP_REASONS enum: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused.)\"\n1682: \n1683:       # H-1 verdict derivation: parse findings JSONL, map highest severity to verdict\n1684:       # - PASS: no P0 or P1 findings (P2-only or clean)\n1685:       # - CONDITIONAL: any P1 findings (no P0)\n1686:       # - FAIL: any P0 findings\n1687:       # Final line of iteration-NNN.md MUST be exactly: \"Review verdict: PASS\" / \"Review verdict: CONDITIONAL\" / \"Review verdict: FAIL\"\n1688:       step_derive_verdict:\n1689:         action: \"Derive review verdict from accumulated findings\"\n1690:         algorithm: |\n1691:           if p0_count > 0:\n1692:             verdict = \"FAIL\"\n1693:           elif p1_count > 0:\n1694:             verdict = \"CONDITIONAL\"\n1695:           else:\n1696:             verdict = \"PASS\"\n1697:           has_advisories = (verdict == \"PASS\" and p2_count > 0)\n1698:           ac_coverage_signal is advisory while the validation rule is INFO/default-off; include it in synthesis traceability, but do not change the exact verdict enum from this signal alone.\n1699:         outputs:\n1700:           - verdict: \"PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL\"\n1701:           - has_advisories: \"Boolean true when verdict is PASS and any active P2 findings exist\"\n1702:           - ac_coverage_signal: \"exempt | disabled | pass | advisory-shortfall\"\n1703:         contract: |\n1704:           Every iteration-NNN.md must end with exactly: \"Review verdict: PASS\" (or CONDITIONAL or FAIL).\n1705:           Downstream automation parses this final line via exact string match — do not vary the format.\n1706: \n1707:       step_read_all_iterations:\n1708:         action: \"Read all iteration files and strategy\"\n1709:         read_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n1710:         read_also: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1711: \n1712:       step_build_finding_registry:\n1713:         action: \"Build deduplicated finding registry from all iterations\"\n1714:         algorithm: |\n1715:           1. Extract all findings from iteration JSONL delta files\n1716:           2. Compute content_hash for each finding (emission requirement):\n1717:              content_hash = sha256(file_path + \"\\u001f\" + line_range + \"\\u001f\" + finding_type + \"\\u001f\" + normalized_description_80chars)\n1718:              Normalized description = whitespace-collapsed, lowercased, first 80 chars of the finding description.\n1719:           3. Two-tier dedup:\n1720:              PRIMARY: group by content_hash field\n1721:                - Same content_hash, multiple dimensions → single finding, merged `dimensions: [<all>]` array\n1722:                - Keep highest severity on duplicates\n1723:              FALLBACK (legacy records lacking content_hash): file:line + normalized_title\n1724:                - Same file:line, multiple dimensions → single finding, multiple dimension tags\n1725:                - Keep highest severity on duplicates\n1726:           4. Track finding lifecycle:\n1727:              - status: active | duplicate | upgraded | downgraded | contested | resolved_false_positive\n1728:              - Record first_seen, upgraded_in, previous_severity for severity changes\n1729:              - Record dimensions array reflecting all dimensions that emitted this finding\n1730:           5. Resolve contradictions:\n1731:              - Findings marked contested across iterations → referee pass\n1732:              - Determine final severity and status\n1733:           6. Count only 'active' findings for totals\n1734:         outputs:\n1735:           - finding_registry: \"Deduplicated list of all findings with metadata\"\n1736:           - active_p0: \"Count of active P0 findings\"\n1737:           - active_p1: \"Count of active P1 findings\"\n1738:           - active_p2: \"Count of active P2 findings\"\n1739: \n1740:       step_adversarial_selfcheck:\n1741:         action: \"Final adversarial self-check on all P0 and P1 findings\"\n1742:         algorithm: |\n1743:           For each active P0/P1 finding:\n1744:             1. Hunter: Re-verify finding against source code (re-read file:line)\n1745:             2. Skeptic: Challenge severity — is this really P0/P1? Could it be P2?\n1746:             3. Referee: Final call — confirm, downgrade, or mark false_positive\n1747:           Update finding_registry with adjudicated results.\n1748: \n1749:       step_emit_resource_map:\n1750:         action: \"Emit {state_paths.resource_map_output} from converged review deltas unless config.resource_map.emit is false\"\n1751:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} {reducer_artifact_arg} --create-missing-anchors --emit-resource-map\"\n1752:         read:\n1753:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1754:           - \"{state_paths.delta_dir}/iter-*.jsonl\"\n1755:         write:\n1756:           - \"{state_paths.resource_map_output}\"\n1757:         guarantee: \"Reducer skips cleanly when config.resource_map.emit == false and writes a deterministic resource-map when enabled.\"\n1758: \n1759:       step_resource_map_coverage_gate:\n1760:         action: \"If resource_map_present, compute the Resource Map Coverage Gate synthesis inputs; otherwise preserve the skip note\"\n1761:         note: \"Cross-check target_files from {spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md against {spec_folder}/resource-map.md. Report touched entries, untouched entries split into expected-by-scope vs gap, and implementation paths absent from the map. Findings raised here use category resource-map-coverage with severity calibrated to the gate outcome.\"\n1762: \n1763:       step_compile_review_report:\n1764:         action: \"Compile review/review-report.md with 9 core sections, a conditional Resource Map Coverage Gate section, and an embedded Planning Packet\"\n1765:         instructions: |\n1766:           Create review/review-report.md with the following sections:\n1767: \n1768:           1. **Executive Summary**\n1769:              - Overall verdict: PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL\n1770:              - hasAdvisories: true when PASS carries active P2 items\n1771:              - P0/P1/P2 counts (active only)\n1772:              - Review scope summary\n1773: \n1774:           2. **Planning Trigger**\n1775:              - State whether `/speckit:plan` is required\n1776:              - Include a fenced `json` block labeled `Planning Packet`\n1777:              - The packet MUST include: `triggered`, `verdict`, `hasAdvisories`, `activeFindings`, `remediationWorkstreams`, `specSeed`, `planSeed`, `findingClasses`, `affectedSurfacesSeed`, `fixCompletenessRequired`\n1778:              - Build `activeFindings`, `findingClasses`, and `affectedSurfacesSeed` from reducer-owned state plus iteration JSONL `findingDetails`; if a field is missing, mark it `UNKNOWN` instead of inferring it from prose\n1779: \n1780:           3. **Active Finding Registry**\n1781:              - Unified registry for active P0/P1/P2 findings\n1782:              - For each: ID, severity, title, dimension, file:line, evidence, impact, fix recommendation, disposition, findingClass, scopeProof, affectedSurfaceHints\n1783: \n1784:           4. **Remediation Workstreams**\n1785:              - Ordered action groups: P0 first, then P1, with P2 advisories separated\n1786: \n1787:           5. **Spec Seed**\n1788:              - Concrete seed bullets for follow-on spec updates\n1789: \n1790:           6. **Plan Seed**\n1791:              - Concrete starter tasks for `/speckit:plan`\n1792: \n1793:            7. **Traceability Status**\n1794:               - Summarize required core protocols first, then applicable overlay protocols\n1795:               - Include status, evidence, and any unresolved drift per protocol\n1796:               - Include `AC_COVERAGE` status for lifecycle-active spec-folder targets: exempt, disabled, pass, or advisory-shortfall, with covered/total and floor when available\n1797: \n1798:           If `resource_map_present` is true, insert **## Resource Map Coverage Gate** after `Traceability Status` with exactly three bullets:\n1799:              - `Entries touched`: count of resource-map paths that appear in applied reports\n1800:              - `Entries not touched`: paths in resource-map not in implementation, labeled `expected-by-scope` or `gap`\n1801:              - `Implementation paths absent from resource-map`: `target_files` in applied reports not on the map\n1802: \n1803:           8. **Deferred Items**\n1804:              - Advisory-only or backlog-worthy follow-ups that do not block the current verdict\n1805: \n1806:           **Dimension Expansion Map**\n1807:              - Insert `## Dimension Expansion Map` after Deferred Items and before Search Ledger.\n1808:              - Render reducer-owned `divergence.saturatedDirections`, completed pivots, failed pivots, audited overrides, Council artifact references, selected review directions, and remaining frontier.\n1809:              - This section records breadth only. It cannot alter the Executive Summary verdict, hasAdvisories, finding registry, or adversarial self-check results.\n1810: \n1811:           9. **Search Ledger**\n1812:              - Always include this section before the appendix.\n1813:              - Render reducer-owned `searchCoverage`, `candidateCoverage`, `searchDebt`, `ruledOutCandidates`, and `cleanSearchProof`.\n1814:              - If all arrays are empty or absent, include: `*No search-depth state captured (legacy v1 record)*`.\n1815:              - When `searchDebt` is non-empty, state `hasSearchDebt: true` and carry the dashboard verdict as CONDITIONAL unless active P0 findings make it FAIL.\n1816: \n1817:           10. **Audit Appendix**\n1818:              - Convergence summary, coverage summary, ruled-out claims, sources reviewed\n1819:              - Cross-reference appendix MUST be split into `Core Protocols` and `Overlay Protocols`\n1820: \n1821:           Preserve machine-owned markers so the reducer-owned registry, dashboard, and strategy anchors can be refreshed on re-run without mutating prior synthesis. (Note: `completed-continue` lineage branch is deferred — see `deep-review/references/protocol/loop-protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches`.)\n1822:         output: \"{state_paths.review_output}\"\n1823: \n1824:       step_convergence_report:\n1825:         action: \"Append convergence report to JSONL\"\n1826:         command: |\n1827:           node --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1828:           import { appendFileSync, existsSync, readFileSync, statSync } from 'node:fs';\n1829: \n1830:           const paths = {\n1831:             stateLog: String.raw`{state_paths.state_log}`,\n1832:             registry: String.raw`{state_paths.findings_registry}`,\n1833:             review: String.raw`{state_paths.review_output}`,\n1834:             dashboard: String.raw`{state_paths.dashboard}`,\n1835:           };\n1836: \n1837:           function hasFile(filePath) {\n1838:             try {\n1839:               return existsSync(filePath) && statSync(filePath).isFile();\n1840:             } catch {\n1841:               return false;\n1842:             }\n1843:           }\n1844: \n1845:           function readJson(filePath) {\n1846:             try {\n1847:               return JSON.parse(readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8'));\n1848:             } catch {\n1849:               return null;\n1850:             }\n1851:           }\n1852: \n1853:           function readJsonl(filePath) {\n1854:             if (!hasFile(filePath)) return [];\n1855:             return readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8')\n1856:               .split(/\\r?\\n/)\n1857:               .map((line) => line.trim())\n1858:               .filter(Boolean)\n1859:               .flatMap((line) => {\n1860:                 try {\n1861:                   return [JSON.parse(line)];\n1862:                 } catch {\n1863:                   return [];\n1864:                 }\n1865:               });\n1866:           }\n1867: \n1868:           function countIterationFindings(record) {\n1869:             if (!record || record.type !== 'iteration') return 0;\n1870:             const numeric = Number(record.findingsCount);\n1871:             if (Number.isFinite(numeric) && numeric > 0) return Math.floor(numeric);\n1872:             if (Array.isArray(record.findingDetails)) return record.findingDetails.length;\n1873:             return 0;\n1874:           }\n1875: \n1876:           function normalizeFindingKey(value) {\n1877:             return String(value || '').trim().toLowerCase().replace(/\\s+/g, ' ');\n1878:           }\n1879: \n1880:           function findingKeys(candidate) {\n1881:             if (typeof candidate === 'string') {\n1882:               const key = normalizeFindingKey(candidate);\n1883:               return key ? [key] : [];\n1884:             }\n1885:             if (!candidate || typeof candidate !== 'object' || Array.isArray(candidate)) return [];\n1886:             return [...new Set([\n1887:               candidate.id,\n1888:               candidate.findingId,\n1889:               candidate.title,\n1890:               candidate.summary,\n1891:               candidate.text,\n1892:               candidate.finding,\n1893:               candidate.description,\n1894:             ].map(normalizeFindingKey).filter(Boolean))];\n1895:           }\n1896: \n1897:           function collectIterationFindingGroups(record) {\n1898:             if (!record || record.type !== 'iteration' || !Array.isArray(record.findingDetails)) return [];\n1899:             return record.findingDetails\n1900:               .map(findingKeys)\n1901:               .filter((keys) => keys.length > 0);\n1902:           }\n1903: \n1904:           function collectRegistryFindingKeys(registry) {\n1905:             return [registry?.openFindings, registry?.resolvedFindings, registry?.repeatedFindings]\n1906:               .filter(Array.isArray)\n1907:               .flatMap((findings) => findings)\n1908:               .flatMap(findingKeys);\n1909:           }\n1910: \n1911:           function appendEvent(event) {\n1912:             appendFileSync(paths.stateLog, `${JSON.stringify(event)}\\n`, 'utf8');\n1913:           }\n1914: \n1915:           const registry = readJson(paths.registry);\n1916:           const openCount = Array.isArray(registry?.openFindings) ? registry.openFindings.length : null;\n1917:           const resolvedCount = Array.isArray(registry?.resolvedFindings) ? registry.resolvedFindings.length : 0;\n1918:           const repeatedCount = Array.isArray(registry?.repeatedFindings) ? registry.repeatedFindings.length : 0;\n1919:           const registryFindingCount = openCount === null ? null : openCount + resolvedCount + repeatedCount;\n1920:           const stateRecords = readJsonl(paths.stateLog);\n1921:           const iterationFindingCount = stateRecords.reduce((sum, record) => sum + countIterationFindings(record), 0);\n1922:           const identifiableFindingGroups = stateRecords.flatMap(collectIterationFindingGroups);\n1923:           const registryFindingKeys = new Set(collectRegistryFindingKeys(registry));\n1924:           const missingStructuredFindingCount = identifiableFindingGroups.filter((keys) => !keys.some((key) => registryFindingKeys.has(key))).length;\n1925:           const identifiableFindingCount = identifiableFindingGroups.length;\n1926:           const missingArtifacts = [\n1927:             ['registry', paths.registry],\n1928:             ['review', paths.review],\n1929:             ['dashboard', paths.dashboard],\n1930:           ].filter(([, filePath]) => !hasFile(filePath)).map(([name, filePath]) => ({ name, path: filePath }));\n1931:           const invariantFailures = [];\n1932:           if (missingArtifacts.length > 0) invariantFailures.push('missing_synthesis_artifacts');\n1933:           if (registryFindingCount === null) invariantFailures.push('registry_missing_openFindings');\n1934:           if (iterationFindingCount > 0 && (registryFindingCount ?? 0) === 0) invariantFailures.push('state_findings_not_reflected_in_registry');\n1935:           if (identifiableFindingCount > 0 && registryFindingCount !== null && registryFindingCount < identifiableFindingCount) invariantFailures.push('structured_state_findings_partially_reflected_in_registry');\n1936:           if (missingStructuredFindingCount > 0) invariantFailures.push('structured_state_findings_missing_from_registry');\n1937: \n1938:           if (invariantFailures.length > 0) {\n1939:             appendEvent({\n1940:               type: 'event',\n1941:               event: 'synthesis_incomplete',\n1942:               mode: 'review',\n1943:               severity: 'warning',\n1944:               totalIterations: Number('{iteration_count}'),\n1945:               activeP0: Number('{active_p0}'),\n1946:               activeP1: Number('{active_p1}'),\n1947:               activeP2: Number('{active_p2}'),\n1948:               dimensionCoverage: Number('{dimension_coverage}'),\n1949:               verdict: '{verdict}',\n1950:               releaseReadinessState: '{release_readiness_state}',\n1951:               stopReason: '{reason}',\n1952:               reason: 'synthesis_artifact_invariant_failed',\n1953:               invariantFailures,\n1954:               missingArtifacts,\n1955:               registryFindingCount,\n1956:               iterationFindingCount,\n1957:               identifiableFindingCount,\n1958:               missingStructuredFindingCount,\n1959:               timestamp: '{ISO_8601_NOW}',\n1960:             });\n1961:           } else {\n1962:             appendEvent({\n1963:               type: 'event',\n1964:               event: 'synthesis_complete',\n1965:               mode: 'review',\n1966:               totalIterations: Number('{iteration_count}'),\n1967:               activeP0: Number('{active_p0}'),\n1968:               activeP1: Number('{active_p1}'),\n1969:               activeP2: Number('{active_p2}'),\n1970:               dimensionCoverage: Number('{dimension_coverage}'),\n1971:               verdict: '{verdict}',\n1972:               releaseReadinessState: '{release_readiness_state}',\n1973:               stopReason: '{reason}',\n1974:               timestamp: '{ISO_8601_NOW}',\n1975:             });\n1976:           }\n1977:           EOF\n1978:         note: \"Emit as numeric ratio (e.g., 0.75), not quoted string. Compute: dimensions_covered / total_dimensions.\"\n1979: \n1980:       step_update_config_status:\n1981:         action: \"Mark config as complete\"\n1982:         edit: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1983:         set_field: { status: \"complete\" }\n1984: \n1985:       step_leave_artifacts_unstaged:\n1986:         action: \"Leave all synthesized artifacts unstaged for explicit operator review\"\n1987:         note: \"Synthesis must not mutate the shared Git index. The operator retains staging and commit authority after reviewing the complete artifact directory.\"\n1988: \n1989:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1990:   # PHASE 4: SAVE\n1991:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1992:   phase_save:\n1993:     purpose: Preserve review context to memory system\n1994:     steps:\n1995: \n1996:       step_compose_save_payload:\n1997:         action: \"Compose the structured JSON payload consumed by generate-context.js\"\n1998:         output: \"/tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json\"\n1999:         requirements:\n2000:           - \"Write this file before invoking generate-context.js; the loader fails closed if the explicit JSON file is absent.\"\n2001:           - \"Include `specFolder`, a concise `sessionSummary`, curated `observations`, `recent_context`, `toolCalls`, and `exchanges` from the completed review loop.\"\n2002:           - \"Use a session-scoped temp filename; do not use the retired shared `/tmp/save-context-data.json` path.\"\n2003:         example_payload: |\n2004:           {\n2005:             \"specFolder\": \"{spec_folder}\",\n2006:             \"sessionSummary\": \"Deep review completed; see review/review-report.md for verdict, findings, and workstreams.\",\n2007:             \"observations\": [\"Summarize the active findings, verdict, and remediation guidance.\"],\n2008:             \"recent_context\": [\"Point to the generated review artifacts and next action.\"],\n2009:             \"exchanges\": [],\n2010:             \"toolCalls\": []\n2011:           }\n2012: \n2013:       step_generate_context:\n2014:         action: \"Route continuity content into the correct canonical spec document via generate-context.js\"\n2015:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json {spec_folder}\"\n2016:         critical_rule: \"NEVER manually author files under retired memory/ paths (the runtime rejects them); use generate-context.js so the save routes into decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md\"\n2017: \n2018:       step_index_memory:\n2019:         action: \"Index the routed canonical spec document with memory_save when immediate MCP visibility is required\"\n2020:         mcp_tool: memory_save\n2021:         invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"[routed-canonical-spec-doc-path]\" })'\n2022:         note: \"Use the actual canonical spec-doc path returned by generate-context.js (decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md); memory_index_scan remains the bulk fallback\"\n2023: \n2024:       step_verify_save:\n2025:         action: \"Verify canonical save routed content into the correct spec document\"\n2026:         check: \"Does {spec_folder}/implementation-summary.md, {spec_folder}/decision-record.md, or {spec_folder}/handover.md carry the new continuity update?\"\n2027:         on_fail: \"Log warning but do not block completion\"\n2028: \n2029:       step_release_lock:\n\n(Showing lines 1640-2029 of 2123. Use offset=2030 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"      step_loop_decision:\n        action: \"Return to step_read_state for next iteration\"\n        goto: step_read_state\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_synthesis:\n    purpose: Compile all iteration findings into review/review-report.md\n    steps:\n\n      step_fanout_merge:\n        description: \"Merge N lineage registries with strongest-restriction; bind p0/p1/p2 counts for step_derive_verdict; skip when single-executor\"\n        skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs \\\n            --loop-type review \\\n            --artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-review-auto.yaml","text":"      step_loop_decision:\n        action: \"Return to step_read_state for next iteration\"\n        goto: step_read_state\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_synthesis:\n    purpose: Compile all iteration findings into review/review-report.md\n    steps:\n\n      step_fanout_merge:\n        description: \"Merge N lineage registries with strongest-restriction; bind p0/p1/p2 counts for step_derive_verdict; skip when single-executor\"\n        skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs \\\n            --loop-type review \\\n            --artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n        bind_from_output:\n          p0_count: \"active_p0\"\n          p1_count: \"active_p1\"\n          p2_count: \"active_p2\"\n\n      step_hydrate_summary_metrics:\n        action: \"Hydrate summary metrics before synthesis\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        extract:\n          - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n          - p0_count: \"Total P0 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n          - p1_count: \"Total P1 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n          - p2_count: \"Total P2 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n          - dimensions_covered: \"List of reviewed dimensions\"\n          - dimension_coverage: \"covered / total\"\n          - ac_coverage_signal: \"For spec-folder targets only: if level is 2+ and checklist.md exists and implementation-summary.md is in-progress or later, surface the AC_COVERAGE advisory status; otherwise mark exempt.\"\n          - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records\"\n          - reason: \"Use the latest stop reason if present, else the frozen default 'converged'. (Must be a member of the STOP_REASONS enum: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused.)\"\n\n      # H-1 verdict derivation: parse findings JSONL, map highest severity to verdict\n      # - PASS: no P0 or P1 findings (P2-only or clean)\n      # - CONDITIONAL: any P1 findings (no P0)\n      # - FAIL: any P0 findings\n      # Final line of iteration-NNN.md MUST be exactly: \"Review verdict: PASS\" / \"Review verdict: CONDITIONAL\" / \"Review verdict: FAIL\"\n      step_derive_verdict:\n        action: \"Derive review verdict from accumulated findings\"\n        algorithm: |\n          if p0_count > 0:\n            verdict = \"FAIL\"\n          elif p1_count > 0:\n            verdict = \"CONDITIONAL\"\n          else:\n            verdict = \"PASS\"\n          has_advisories = (verdict == \"PASS\" and p2_count > 0)\n          ac_coverage_signal is advisory while the validation rule is INFO/default-off; include it in synthesis traceability, but do not change the exact verdict enum from this signal alone.\n        outputs:\n          - verdict: \"PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL\"\n          - has_advisories: \"Boolean true when verdict is PASS and any active P2 findings exist\"\n          - ac_coverage_signal: \"exempt | disabled | pass | advisory-shortfall\"\n        contract: |\n          Every iteration-NNN.md must end with exactly: \"Review verdict: PASS\" (or CONDITIONAL or FAIL).\n          Downstream automation parses this final line via exact string match — do not vary the format.\n\n      step_read_all_iterations:\n        action: \"Read all iteration files and strategy\"\n        read_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n        read_also: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_build_finding_registry:\n        action: \"Build deduplicated finding registry from all iterations\"\n        algorithm: |\n          1. Extract all findings from iteration JSONL delta files\n          2. Compute content_hash for each finding (emission requirement):\n             content_hash = sha256(file_path + \"\\u001f\" + line_range + \"\\u001f\" + finding_type + \"\\u001f\" + normalized_description_80chars)\n             Normalized description = whitespace-collapsed, lowercased, first 80 chars of the finding description.\n          3. Two-tier dedup:\n             PRIMARY: group by content_hash field\n               - Same content_hash, multiple dimensions → single finding, merged `dimensions: [<all>]` array\n               - Keep highest severity on duplicates\n             FALLBACK (legacy records lacking content_hash): file:line + normalized_title\n               - Same file:line, multiple dimensions → single finding, multiple dimension tags\n               - Keep highest severity on duplicates\n          4. Track finding lifecycle:\n             - status: active | duplicate | upgraded | downgraded | contested | resolved_false_positive\n             - Record first_seen, upgraded_in, previous_severity for severity changes\n             - Record dimensions array reflecting all dimensions that emitted this finding\n          5. Resolve contradictions:\n             - Findings marked contested across iterations → referee pass\n             - Determine final severity and status\n          6. Count only 'active' findings for totals\n        outputs:\n          - finding_registry: \"Deduplicated list of all findings with metadata\"\n          - active_p0: \"Count of active P0 findings\"\n          - active_p1: \"Count of active P1 findings\"\n          - active_p2: \"Count of active P2 findings\"\n\n      step_adversarial_selfcheck:\n        action: \"Final adversarial self-check on all P0 and P1 findings\"\n        algorithm: |\n          For each active P0/P1 finding:\n            1. Hunter: Re-verify finding against source code (re-read file:line)\n            2. Skeptic: Challenge severity — is this really P0/P1? Could it be P2?\n            3. Referee: Final call — confirm, downgrade, or mark false_positive\n          Update finding_registry with adjudicated results.\n\n      step_emit_resource_map:\n        action: \"Emit {state_paths.resource_map_output} from converged review deltas unless config.resource_map.emit is false\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} {reducer_artifact_arg} --create-missing-anchors --emit-resource-map\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.delta_dir}/iter-*.jsonl\"\n        write:\n          - \"{state_paths.resource_map_output}\"\n        guarantee: \"Reducer skips cleanly when config.resource_map.emit == false and writes a deterministic resource-map when enabled.\"\n\n      step_resource_map_coverage_gate:\n        action: \"If resource_map_present, compute the Resource Map Coverage Gate synthesis inputs; otherwise preserve the skip note\"\n        note: \"Cross-check target_files from {spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md against {spec_folder}/resource-map.md. Report touched entries, untouched entries split into expected-by-scope vs gap, and implementation paths absent from the map. Findings raised here use category resource-map-coverage with severity calibrated to the gate outcome.\"\n\n      step_compile_review_report:\n        action: \"Compile review/review-report.md with 9 core sections, a conditional Resource Map Coverage Gate section, and an embedded Planning Packet\"\n        instructions: |\n          Create review/review-report.md with the following sections:\n\n          1. **Executive Summary**\n             - Overall verdict: PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL\n             - hasAdvisories: true when PASS carries active P2 items\n             - P0/P1/P2 counts (active only)\n             - Review scope summary\n\n          2. **Planning Trigger**\n             - State whether `/speckit:plan` is required\n             - Include a fenced `json` block labeled `Planning Packet`\n             - The packet MUST include: `triggered`, `verdict`, `hasAdvisories`, `activeFindings`, `remediationWorkstreams`, `specSeed`, `planSeed`, `findingClasses`, `affectedSurfacesSeed`, `fixCompletenessRequired`\n             - Build `activeFindings`, `findingClasses`, and `affectedSurfacesSeed` from reducer-owned state plus iteration JSONL `findingDetails`; if a field is missing, mark it `UNKNOWN` instead of inferring it from prose\n\n          3. **Active Finding Registry**\n             - Unified registry for active P0/P1/P2 findings\n             - For each: ID, severity, title, dimension, file:line, evidence, impact, fix recommendation, disposition, findingClass, scopeProof, affectedSurfaceHints\n\n          4. **Remediation Workstreams**\n             - Ordered action groups: P0 first, then P1, with P2 advisories separated\n\n          5. **Spec Seed**\n             - Concrete seed bullets for follow-on spec updates\n\n          6. **Plan Seed**\n             - Concrete starter tasks for `/speckit:plan`\n\n           7. **Traceability Status**\n              - Summarize required core protocols first, then applicable overlay protocols\n              - Include status, evidence, and any unresolved drift per protocol\n              - Include `AC_COVERAGE` status for lifecycle-active spec-folder targets: exempt, disabled, pass, or advisory-shortfall, with covered/total and floor when available\n\n          If `resource_map_present` is true, insert **## Resource Map Coverage Gate** after `Traceability Status` with exactly three bullets:\n             - `Entries touched`: count of resource-map paths that appear in applied reports\n             - `Entries not touched`: paths in resource-map not in implementation, labeled `expected-by-scope` or `gap`\n             - `Implementation paths absent from resource-map`: `target_files` in applied reports not on the map\n\n          8. **Deferred Items**\n             - Advisory-only or backlog-worthy follow-ups that do not block the current verdict\n\n          **Dimension Expansion Map**\n             - Insert `## Dimension Expansion Map` after Deferred Items and before Search Ledger.\n             - Render reducer-owned `divergence.saturatedDirections`, completed pivots, failed pivots, audited overrides, Council artifact references, selected review directions, and remaining frontier.\n             - This section records breadth only. It cannot alter the Executive Summary verdict, hasAdvisories, finding registry, or adversarial self-check results.\n\n          9. **Search Ledger**\n             - Always include this section before the appendix.\n             - Render reducer-owned `searchCoverage`, `candidateCoverage`, `searchDebt`, `ruledOutCandidates`, and `cleanSearchProof`.\n             - If all arrays are empty or absent, include: `*No search-depth state captured (legacy v1 record)*`.\n             - When `searchDebt` is non-empty, state `hasSearchDebt: true` and carry the dashboard verdict as CONDITIONAL unless active P0 findings make it FAIL.\n\n          10. **Audit Appendix**\n             - Convergence summary, coverage summary, ruled-out claims, sources reviewed\n             - Cross-reference appendix MUST be split into `Core Protocols` and `Overlay Protocols`\n\n          Preserve machine-owned markers so the reducer-owned registry, dashboard, and strategy anchors can be refreshed on re-run without mutating prior synthesis. (Note: `completed-continue` lineage branch is deferred — see `deep-review/references/protocol/loop-protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches`.)\n        output: \"{state_paths.review_output}\"\n\n      step_convergence_report:\n        action: \"Append convergence report to JSONL\"\n        command: |\n          node --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n          import { appendFileSync, existsSync, readFileSync, statSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n          const paths = {\n            stateLog: String.raw`{state_paths.state_log}`,\n            registry: String.raw`{state_paths.findings_registry}`,\n            review: String.raw`{state_paths.review_output}`,\n            dashboard: String.raw`{state_paths.dashboard}`,\n          };\n\n          function hasFile(filePath) {\n            try {\n              return existsSync(filePath) && statSync(filePath).isFile();\n            } catch {\n              return false;\n            }\n          }\n\n          function readJson(filePath) {\n            try {\n              return JSON.parse(readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8'));\n            } catch {\n              return null;\n            }\n          }\n\n          function readJsonl(filePath) {\n            if (!hasFile(filePath)) return [];\n            return readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8')\n              .split(/\\r?\\n/)\n              .map((line) => line.trim())\n              .filter(Boolean)\n              .flatMap((line) => {\n                try {\n                  return [JSON.parse(line)];\n                } catch {\n                  return [];\n                }\n              });\n          }\n\n          function countIterationFindings(record) {\n            if (!record || record.type !== 'iteration') return 0;\n            const numeric = Number(record.findingsCount);\n            if (Number.isFinite(numeric) && numeric > 0) return Math.floor(numeric);\n            if (Array.isArray(record.findingDetails)) return record.findingDetails.length;\n            return 0;\n          }\n\n          function normalizeFindingKey(value) {\n            return String(value || '').trim().toLowerCase().replace(/\\s+/g, ' ');\n          }\n\n          function findingKeys(candidate) {\n            if (typeof candidate === 'string') {\n              const key = normalizeFindingKey(candidate);\n              return key ? [key] : [];\n            }\n            if (!candidate || typeof candidate !== 'object' || Array.isArray(candidate)) return [];\n            return [...new Set([\n              candidate.id,\n              candidate.findingId,\n              candidate.title,\n              candidate.summary,\n              candidate.text,\n              candidate.finding,\n              candidate.description,\n            ].map(normalizeFindingKey).filter(Boolean))];\n          }\n\n          function collectIterationFindingGroups(record) {\n            if (!record || record.type !== 'iteration' || !Array.isArray(record.findingDetails)) return [];\n            return record.findingDetails\n              .map(findingKeys)\n              .filter((keys) => keys.length > 0);\n          }\n\n          function collectRegistryFindingKeys(registry) {\n            return [registry?.openFindings, registry?.resolvedFindings, registry?.repeatedFindings]\n              .filter(Array.isArray)\n              .flatMap((findings) => findings)\n              .flatMap(findingKeys);\n          }\n\n          function appendEvent(event) {\n            appendFileSync(paths.stateLog, `${JSON.stringify(event)}\\n`, 'utf8');\n          }\n\n          const registry = readJson(paths.registry);\n          const openCount = Array.isArray(registry?.openFindings) ? registry.openFindings.length : null;\n          const resolvedCount = Array.isArray(registry?.resolvedFindings) ? registry.resolvedFindings.length : 0;\n          const repeatedCount = Array.isArray(registry?.repeatedFindings) ? registry.repeatedFindings.length : 0;\n          const registryFindingCount = openCount === null ? null : openCount + resolvedCount + repeatedCount;\n          const stateRecords = readJsonl(paths.stateLog);\n          const iterationFindingCount = stateRecords.reduce((sum, record) => sum + countIterationFindings(record), 0);\n          const identifiableFindingGroups = stateRecords.flatMap(collectIterationFindingGroups);\n          const registryFindingKeys = new Set(collectRegistryFindingKeys(registry));\n          const missingStructuredFindingCount = identifiableFindingGroups.filter((keys) => !keys.some((key) => registryFindingKeys.has(key))).length;\n          const identifiableFindingCount = identifiableFindingGroups.length;\n          const missingArtifacts = [\n            ['registry', paths.registry],\n            ['review', paths.review],\n            ['dashboard', paths.dashboard],\n          ].filter(([, filePath]) => !hasFile(filePath)).map(([name, filePath]) => ({ name, path: filePath }));\n          const invariantFailures = [];\n          if (missingArtifacts.length > 0) invariantFailures.push('missing_synthesis_artifacts');\n          if (registryFindingCount === null) invariantFailures.push('registry_missing_openFindings');\n          if (iterationFindingCount > 0 && (registryFindingCount ?? 0) === 0) invariantFailures.push('state_findings_not_reflected_in_registry');\n          if (identifiableFindingCount > 0 && registryFindingCount !== null && registryFindingCount < identifiableFindingCount) invariantFailures.push('structured_state_findings_partially_reflected_in_registry');\n          if (missingStructuredFindingCount > 0) invariantFailures.push('structured_state_findings_missing_from_registry');\n\n          if (invariantFailures.length > 0) {\n            appendEvent({\n              type: 'event',\n              event: 'synthesis_incomplete',\n              mode: 'review',\n              severity: 'warning',\n              totalIterations: Number('{iteration_count}'),\n              activeP0: Number('{active_p0}'),\n              activeP1: Number('{active_p1}'),\n              activeP2: Number('{active_p2}'),\n              dimensionCoverage: Number('{dimension_coverage}'),\n              verdict: '{verdict}',\n              releaseReadinessState: '{release_readiness_state}',\n              stopReason: '{reason}',\n              reason: 'synthesis_artifact_invariant_failed',\n              invariantFailures,\n              missingArtifacts,\n              registryFindingCount,\n              iterationFindingCount,\n              identifiableFindingCount,\n              missingStructuredFindingCount,\n              timestamp: '{ISO_8601_NOW}',\n            });\n          } else {\n            appendEvent({\n              type: 'event',\n              event: 'synthesis_complete',\n              mode: 'review',\n              totalIterations: Number('{iteration_count}'),\n              activeP0: Number('{active_p0}'),\n              activeP1: Number('{active_p1}'),\n              activeP2: Number('{active_p2}'),\n              dimensionCoverage: Number('{dimension_coverage}'),\n              verdict: '{verdict}',\n              releaseReadinessState: '{release_readiness_state}',\n              stopReason: '{reason}',\n              timestamp: '{ISO_8601_NOW}',\n            });\n          }\n          EOF\n        note: \"Emit as numeric ratio (e.g., 0.75), not quoted string. Compute: dimensions_covered / total_dimensions.\"\n\n      step_update_config_status:\n        action: \"Mark config as complete\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n        set_field: { status: \"complete\" }\n\n      step_leave_artifacts_unstaged:\n        action: \"Leave all synthesized artifacts unstaged for explicit operator review\"\n        note: \"Synthesis must not mutate the shared Git index. The operator retains staging and commit authority after reviewing the complete artifact directory.\"\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 4: SAVE\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_save:\n    purpose: Preserve review context to memory system\n    steps:\n\n      step_compose_save_payload:\n        action: \"Compose the structured JSON payload consumed by generate-context.js\"\n        output: \"/tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json\"\n        requirements:\n          - \"Write this file before invoking generate-context.js; the loader fails closed if the explicit JSON file is absent.\"\n          - \"Include `specFolder`, a concise `sessionSummary`, curated `observations`, `recent_context`, `toolCalls`, and `exchanges` from the completed review loop.\"\n          - \"Use a session-scoped temp filename; do not use the retired shared `/tmp/save-context-data.json` path.\"\n        example_payload: |\n          {\n            \"specFolder\": \"{spec_folder}\",\n            \"sessionSummary\": \"Deep review completed; see review/review-report.md for verdict, findings, and workstreams.\",\n            \"observations\": [\"Summarize the active findings, verdict, and remediation guidance.\"],\n            \"recent_context\": [\"Point to the generated review artifacts and next action.\"],\n            \"exchanges\": [],\n            \"toolCalls\": []\n          }\n\n      step_generate_context:\n        action: \"Route continuity content into the correct canonical spec document via generate-context.js\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json {spec_folder}\"\n        critical_rule: \"NEVER manually author files under retired memory/ paths (the runtime rejects them); use generate-context.js so the save routes into decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md\"\n\n      step_index_memory:\n        action: \"Index the routed canonical spec document with memory_save when immediate MCP visibility is required\"\n        mcp_tool: memory_save\n        invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"[routed-canonical-spec-doc-path]\" })'\n        note: \"Use the actual canonical spec-doc path returned by generate-context.js (decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md); memory_index_scan remains the bulk fallback\"\n\n      step_verify_save:\n        action: \"Verify canonical save routed content into the correct spec document\"\n        check: \"Does {spec_folder}/implementation-summary.md, {spec_folder}/decision-record.md, or {spec_folder}/handover.md carry the new continuity update?\"\n        on_fail: \"Log warning but do not block completion\"\n\n      step_release_lock:","lineStart":1640,"lineEnd":2029,"totalLines":2123,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-review-auto.yaml","time":{"start":1784693596443,"end":1784693596452}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b27bb3727684a9c016a60435b5ef48191b4376f9450662c98"}},"id":"prt_f88071d01001JdnnJxm4cGFvHP","sessionID":"ses_07813ae6bffeXSfNUcMKmjadEz","messageID":"msg_f880713fa001dUCzcCUp7Sfkwm"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1784693596879,"sessionID":"ses_07813ae6bffeXSfNUcMKmjadEz","part":{"id":"prt_f880722cd001J98cQfrr0YRxNV","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"63110c392b53849533a812feebf9331b3966023f","messageID":"msg_f880713fa001dUCzcCUp7Sfkwm","sessionID":"ses_07813ae6bffeXSfNUcMKmjadEz","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":155431,"input":5329,"output":70,"reasoning":16,"cache":{"write":0,"read":150016}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1784693599074,"sessionID":"ses_07813ae6bffeXSfNUcMKmjadEz","part":{"id":"prt_f88072b60001eUPEvFRyCZNPME","messageID":"msg_f8807249b001lYTOAWU7aZb2Lj","sessionID":"ses_07813ae6bffeXSfNUcMKmjadEz","snapshot":"63110c392b53849533a812feebf9331b3966023f","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784693609110,"sessionID":"ses_07813ae6bffeXSfNUcMKmjadEz","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_CymK3Fs33XIoa3sgREtGrqzP","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/state/state-outputs.md","offset":1,"limit":180},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/state/state-outputs.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Deep Review State Outputs\"\n3: description: \"Focused reference for deep-review packet files, markdown outputs, reducer-owned views, and synthesis artifacts.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review state outputs\"\n6:   - \"review packet outputs\"\n7:   - \"review dashboard output\"\n8:   - \"review report output\"\n9: importance_tier: normal\n10: contextType: implementation\n11: version: 1.11.0.3\n12: ---\n13: \n14: # Deep Review State Outputs\n15: \n16: This reference explains the files operators read during and after a review loop. Use `references/state/state-format.md` for schemas and field-level contracts.\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n21: \n22: Deep-review outputs are audit artifacts. Iteration agents write evidence, the reducer writes derived state, and synthesis writes the release-readiness report.\n23: \n24: ---\n25: \n26: ## 2. PACKET FILES\n27: \n28: | File | Owner | Mutability | Purpose |\n29: |------|-------|------------|---------|\n30: | `deep-review-config.json` | Workflow | Immutable after init | Run parameters, lineage, threshold settings |\n31: | `deep-review-state.jsonl` | Workflow and iteration contract | Append-only | Config, iteration, blocked-stop, pause, synthesis events |\n32: | `deep-review-findings-registry.json` | Reducer | Regenerated | Active, resolved, repeated, and blocked findings |\n33: | `deep-review-strategy.md` | Reducer with operator-readable sections | Regenerated/updated | Dimension order, known context, next focus |\n34: | `deep-review-dashboard.md` | Reducer | Regenerated | Current status, trend, verdict preview |\n35: | `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Iteration agent | Write-once | Detailed findings for one pass |\n36: | `review-report.md` | Synthesis | Final output | Findings-first release-readiness report |\n37: | `resource-map.md` | Synthesis | Final or disabled | Converged delta evidence map |\n38: \n39: ---\n40: \n41: ## 3. ITERATION MARKDOWN\n42: \n43: Each iteration file must be non-empty and end with exactly one final verdict line:\n44: \n45: ```text\n46: Review verdict: PASS\n47: ```\n48: \n49: ```text\n50: Review verdict: CONDITIONAL\n51: ```\n52: \n53: ```text\n54: Review verdict: FAIL\n55: ```\n56: \n57: The line maps to the findings in that iteration only. Synthesis computes the final release verdict from the full state.\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ## 4. DASHBOARD\n62: \n63: The dashboard is a status view, not the source of truth. It should display:\n64: \n65: - Current iteration and next focus.\n66: - Active P0/P1/P2 counts.\n67: - Dimension coverage.\n68: - Convergence trend.\n69: - Gate blockers.\n70: - Provisional verdict.\n71: \n72: If dashboard data disagrees with JSONL, JSONL wins and the reducer must regenerate the dashboard.\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: ## 5. FINAL REPORT\n77: \n78: `review-report.md` is the handoff artifact. It carries:\n79: \n80: - Executive summary.\n81: - Planning trigger.\n82: - Active finding registry.\n83: - Remediation workstreams.\n84: - Spec seed.\n85: - Plan seed.\n86: - Traceability status.\n87: - Deferred items.\n88: - Audit appendix.\n89: - Optional Resource Map Coverage Gate section when a map existed at init.\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ## 6. RELATED RESOURCES\n94: \n95: - `references/state/state-format.md` for schemas.\n96: - `references/state/state-reducer-registry.md` for reducer ownership.\n97: - `references/convergence/convergence-signals.md` for STOP fields shown in dashboard/report.\n\n(End of file - total 97 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review State Outputs\"\ndescription: \"Focused reference for deep-review packet files, markdown outputs, reducer-owned views, and synthesis artifacts.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review state outputs\"\n  - \"review packet outputs\"\n  - \"review dashboard output\"\n  - \"review report output\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.11.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Outputs\n\nThis reference explains the files operators read during and after a review loop. Use `references/state/state-format.md` for schemas and field-level contracts.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/state/state-outputs.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review State Outputs\"\ndescription: \"Focused reference for deep-review packet files, markdown outputs, reducer-owned views, and synthesis artifacts.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review state outputs\"\n  - \"review packet outputs\"\n  - \"review dashboard output\"\n  - \"review report output\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.11.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Outputs\n\nThis reference explains the files operators read during and after a review loop. Use `references/state/state-format.md` for schemas and field-level contracts.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nDeep-review outputs are audit artifacts. Iteration agents write evidence, the reducer writes derived state, and synthesis writes the release-readiness report.\n\n---\n\n## 2. PACKET FILES\n\n| File | Owner | Mutability | Purpose |\n|------|-------|------------|---------|\n| `deep-review-config.json` | Workflow | Immutable after init | Run parameters, lineage, threshold settings |\n| `deep-review-state.jsonl` | Workflow and iteration contract | Append-only | Config, iteration, blocked-stop, pause, synthesis events |\n| `deep-review-findings-registry.json` | Reducer | Regenerated | Active, resolved, repeated, and blocked findings |\n| `deep-review-strategy.md` | Reducer with operator-readable sections | Regenerated/updated | Dimension order, known context, next focus |\n| `deep-review-dashboard.md` | Reducer | Regenerated | Current status, trend, verdict preview |\n| `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Iteration agent | Write-once | Detailed findings for one pass |\n| `review-report.md` | Synthesis | Final output | Findings-first release-readiness report |\n| `resource-map.md` | Synthesis | Final or disabled | Converged delta evidence map |\n\n---\n\n## 3. ITERATION MARKDOWN\n\nEach iteration file must be non-empty and end with exactly one final verdict line:\n\n```text\nReview verdict: PASS\n```\n\n```text\nReview verdict: CONDITIONAL\n```\n\n```text\nReview verdict: FAIL\n```\n\nThe line maps to the findings in that iteration only. Synthesis computes the final release verdict from the full state.\n\n---\n\n## 4. DASHBOARD\n\nThe dashboard is a status view, not the source of truth. It should display:\n\n- Current iteration and next focus.\n- Active P0/P1/P2 counts.\n- Dimension coverage.\n- Convergence trend.\n- Gate blockers.\n- Provisional verdict.\n\nIf dashboard data disagrees with JSONL, JSONL wins and the reducer must regenerate the dashboard.\n\n---\n\n## 5. FINAL REPORT\n\n`review-report.md` is the handoff artifact. It carries:\n\n- Executive summary.\n- Planning trigger.\n- Active finding registry.\n- Remediation workstreams.\n- Spec seed.\n- Plan seed.\n- Traceability status.\n- Deferred items.\n- Audit appendix.\n- Optional Resource Map Coverage Gate section when a map existed at init.\n\n---\n\n## 6. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n- `references/state/state-format.md` for schemas.\n- `references/state/state-reducer-registry.md` for reducer ownership.\n- `references/convergence/convergence-signals.md` for STOP fields shown in dashboard/report.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":97,"totalLines":97,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/state/state-outputs.md","time":{"start":1784693609095,"end":1784693609100}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0c862113325414ab016a604368fe588191bf54a148829a8bea"}},"id":"prt_f88075280001lXJs9IFxtUpJbB","sessionID":"ses_07813ae6bffeXSfNUcMKmjadEz","messageID":"msg_f8807249b001lYTOAWU7aZb2Lj"}}
