ivation-verification/013-compiled-coverage-buildout/checklist.md\",\"line\":58,\"description\":\"The packet claims complete while P1 checklist rows and operator sign-off remain open and plan/tasks/decision metadata remain planned.\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\"checklist.md:52-58\",\"checklist.md:92\",\"checklist.md:123-124\",\"checklist.md:197-208\",\"plan.md:11,77-82\",\"tasks.md:10-20,114-121\",\"decision-record.md:11-18\"],\"scopeProof\":\"All canonical packet documents were compared.\",\"affectedSurfaceHints\":[\"spec status\",\"checklist protocol\",\"plan definition-of-done\",\"task ledger\",\"decision metadata\",\"operator sign-off\"],\"status\":\"active\",\"claim\":\"The packet's complete status conflicts with its own P1 completion protocol.\",\"finalSeverity\":\"P1\",\"confidence\":0.98},{\"findingId\":\"F003\",\"severity\":\"P2\",\"category\":\"traceability\",\"finding_class\":\"instance-only\",\"title\":\"SD-015 limitation and follow-up are stale\",\"file\":\".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/013-compiled-coverage-buildout/implementation-summary.md\",\"line\":208,\"description\":\"The summary says there is no dedicated SD-015 lock-in test, but the test suite contains a named positive clause test and an adversarial served-route counterexample.\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\"implementation-summary.md:204-220\",\"compiled-routing-parity.vitest.ts:468-537\"],\"scopeProof\":\"Directly read the named test block and stale follow-up entry.\",\"affectedSurfaceHints\":[\"implementation summary\",\"checklist evidence\",\"follow-up ledger\"],\"status\":\"active\",\"claim\":\"The SD-015 test-gap limitation is stale documentation, not missing test coverage.\",\"finalSeverity\":\"P2\",\"confidence\":0.99},{\"findingId\":\"F004\",\"severity\":\"P2\",\"category\":\"maintainability\",\"finding_class\":\"synchronization-risk\",\"title\":\"Default-on cohort is maintained in multiple independently edited sources\",\"file\":\".opencode/bin/lib/compiled-routing/011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs\",\"line\":34,\"description\":\"The seven-hub cohort is repeated in the promoted resolver, authored resolver twin, and advisor TypeScript flag module rather than generated from one canonical source.\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\".opencode/bin/lib/compiled-routing/011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs:29-42\",\".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs\",\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/lib/compiled-routing-flag.ts:24-40\",\".opencode/bin/compiled-routing-foundation.vitest.ts:70-74\"],\"scopeProof\":\"The same cohort literal exists in three maintained source surfaces; tests detect divergence only after an edit.\",\"affectedSurfaceHints\":[\"runtime resolver\",\"authored resolver twin\",\"advisor enrichment flag\",\"generated/promoted closure\"],\"status\":\"active\",\"claim\":\"A future cohort change can update one source while leaving another stale; current tests observe but do not prevent this drift.\",\"counterevidenceSought\":\"Checked sync tooling and foundation tests for a generator or pre-write canonical source; none was found for the advisor cohort.\",\"alternativeExplanation\":\"The current test suite catches divergence in CI, reducing impact but not removing the maintenance hazard.\",\"finalSeverity\":\"P2\",\"confidence\":0.92,\"downgradeTrigger\":\"All cohort consumers derive from one source or a generation gate makes stale copies impossible to package.\"}],\"traceabilityChecks\":{\"summary\":{\"required\":3,\"executed\":3,\"pass\":2,\"partial\":1,\"fail\":0,\"blocked\":0,\"notApplicable\":0,\"gatingFailures\":0},\"results\":[{\"name\":\"resolver_lockstep\",\"status\":\"partial\"},{\"name\":\"cohort_consistency\",\"status\":\"pass\"},{\"name\":\"serving_boundary\",\"status\":\"pass\"}]},\"newFindingsRatio\":0.25