{\"name\":\"resolved_artifact_exclusion\",\"status\":\"pass\"},{\"name\":\"completion_gate\",\"status\":\"fail\"},{\"name\":\"overall_review\",\"status\":\"partial\"}]},\"newFindingsRatio\":0.0,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Final convergence found no new issue after iteration 5; four substantive findings remain, with one reducer artifact resolved.\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-luna... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"totalIterations\":10,\"activeP0\":0,\"activeP1\":2,\"activeP2\":2,\"dimensionCoverage\":1,\"verdict\":\"CONDITIONAL\",\"releaseReadinessState\":\"release-blocking\",\"stopReason\":\"maxIterationsReached\",\"reviewReport\":\"review-report.md\",\"resourceMap\":\"resource-map.md\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-luna-xhigh-1784691838667-iv78vk\",\"generation\":1,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-22T04:55:00.000Z\"}","lineStart":10,"lineEnd":14,"totalLines":14,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/013-compiled-coverage-buildout/review/lineages/luna-xhigh/deep-review-state.jsonl","time":{"start":1784693796763,"end":1784693796778}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_01c050d7c5b749f0016a6044249dac81919f54d52c56b87452"}},"id":"prt_f880a2f86001vVno7V5wq1QaIv","sessionID":"ses_07813ae6bffeXSfNUcMKmjadEz","messageID":"msg_f880a0455001G8vqwE94m2Url2"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784693796783,"sessionID":"ses_07813ae6bffeXSfNUcMKmjadEz","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_vFkXoat4XiZrAP7qd2YDeXPj","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/013-compiled-coverage-buildout/review/lineages/luna-xhigh/review-report.md","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/013-compiled-coverage-buildout/review/lineages/luna-xhigh/review-report.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Deep Review Report: Compiled Coverage Buildout\"\n3: description: \"Final conditional review for the detached luna-xhigh lineage.\"\n4: sessionId: \"fanout-luna-xhigh-1784691838667-iv78vk\"\n5: verdict: \"CONDITIONAL\"\n6: ---\n7: \n8: # Deep Review Report\n9: \n10: ## 1. Executive Summary\n11: \n12: - **Verdict:** CONDITIONAL\n13: - **Active findings:** 0 P0, 2 P1, 2 P2\n14: - **Resolved findings:** 1 reducer-only summary artifact\n15: - **Iterations:** 10/10\n16: - **Convergence:** 1.00\n17: - **Search debt:** none\n18: - **Corruption:** none\n19: - **Scope:** compiled-routing manifest refresh, resolver/cohort behavior, parity and sync controls, packet completion evidence, and regression boundaries\n20: \n21: The runtime surfaces are substantially fail-closed and the seven-hub default-on claims have broad parity evidence. The review does not issue PASS because the refresh path lacks concurrency protection and the packet's completion metadata contradicts its own required evidence protocol.\n22: \n23: ## 2. Planning Trigger\n24: \n25: `/speckit:plan` is required for the two active P1 remediation workstreams. The P2 items can be handled as documentation and maintenance follow-ups.\n26: \n27: ```json\n28: {\n29:   \"triggered\": true,\n30:   \"verdict\": \"CONDITIONAL\",\n31:   \"hasAdvisories\": true,\n32:   \"activeFindings\": [\n33:     {\"id\":\"F001\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"title\":\"Concurrent refreshes can lose a generation/policy update\",\"file\":\".opencode/bin/lib/compiled-route-manifest.cjs\",\"line\":588},\n34:     {\"id\":\"F002\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"title\":\"Completion status conflicts with required packet gates\",\"file\":\".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/013-compiled-coverage-buildout/checklist.md\",\"line\":58},\n35:     {\"id\":\"F003\",\"severity\":\"P2\",\"title\":\"SD-015 limitation and follow-up are stale\",\"file\":\".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/013-compiled-coverage-buildout/implementation-summary.md\",\"line\":208},\n36:     {\"id\":\"F004\",\"severity\":\"P2\",\"title\":\"Default-on cohort is maintained in multiple independently edited sources\",\"file\":\".opencode/bin/lib/compiled-routing/011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs\",\"line\":34}\n37:   ],\n38:   \"remediationWorkstreams\": [\n39:     \"Serialize or compare-and-swap refresh writes and add a concurrent-refresh regression test.\",\n40:     \"Reconcile packet statuses, task/checklist completion, P1 deferrals, and operator sign-off.\",\n41:     \"Mark the SD-015 follow-up resolved with its existing test evidence.\",\n42:     \"Generate or gate all default-on cohort copies from one canonical source.\"\n43:   ],\n44:   \"specSeed\": [\n45:     \"Document refresh concurrency semantics and the accepted rollback/locking behavior.\",\n46:     \"Reconcile the packet's completion contract with remaining unchecked evidence.\"\n47:   ],\n48:   \"planSeed\": [\n49:     \"Add a refresh race test using two concurrent refresh processes.\",\n50:     \"Choose and implement a lock or compare-and-swap protocol.\",\n51:     \"Synchronize plan.md, tasks.md, decision-record.md, checklist.md, and sign-off.\"\n52:   ],\n53:   \"findingClasses\": [\"class-of-bug\",\"matrix/evidence\",\"instance-only\",\"synchronization-risk\"],\n54:   \"affectedSurfacesSeed\": [\"canonical manifest refresh CLI\",\"activation manifest state\",\"packet completion metadata\",\"runtime/advisor cohort copies\"],\n55:   \"fixCompletenessRequired\": true\n56: }\n57: ```\n58: \n59: ## 3. Active Finding Registry\n60: \n61: ### F001 - P1\n62: \n63: - **Title:** Concurrent refreshes can lose a generation/policy update\n64: - **Evidence:** `.opencode/bin/lib/compiled-route-manifest.cjs:564-588`; `.opencode/bin/tests/compiled-route-manifest.test.cjs:457-472`\n65: - **Impact:** Two valid refreshes can read the same generation and later overwrite each other's policy state. The concurrent test covers atomic mint, not refresh.\n66: - **Recommendation:** Serialize refreshes or use compare-and-swap on generation/hash, then add a concurrent refresh regression test.\n67: - **Disposition:** Active, confirmed across iterations 1-10.\n68: \n69: ### F002 - P1\n70: \n71: - **Title:** Completion status conflicts with required packet gates\n72: - **Evidence:** `checklist.md:52-58,92,123-124,197-208`; `plan.md:11,77-82`; `tasks.md:10-20,114-121`; `decision-record.md:11-18`\n73: - **Impact:** The packet claims complete while required P1 rows, planned metadata, stale blockers, and formal operator sign-off remain unresolved.\n74: - **Recommendation:** Reconcile all lifecycle metadata and checklist/task state, or record explicit operator-approved deferrals before claiming complete.\n75: - **Disposition:** Active, confirmed across iterations 4-10.\n76: \n77: ### F003 - P2\n78: \n79: - **Title:** SD-015 limitation and follow-up are stale\n80: - **Evidence:** `implementation-summary.md:204-220`; `compiled-routing-parity.vitest.ts:468-537`\n81: - **Impact:** The packet understates its regression coverage and leaves an inaccurate follow-up open.\n82: - **Recommendation:** Mark the limitation resolved and cite the positive and adversarial SD-015 tests.\n83: - **Disposition:** Active documentation drift.\n84: \n85: ### F004 - P2\n86: \n87: - **Title:** Default-on cohort is maintained in multiple independently edited sources\n88: - **Evidence:** promoted resolver `resolve.cjs:29-42`; authored resolver twin; `compiled-routing-flag.ts:24-40`; `compiled-routing-foundation.vitest.ts:70-74`\n89: - **Impact:** A future cohort change can update one source while leaving another stale. Current tests detect divergence after the fact.\n90: - **Recommendation:** Generate all cohort consumers from one canonical source or add a pre-packaging generation gate.\n91: - **Disposition:** Active maintainability advisory.\n92: \n93: ## 4. Remediation Workstreams\n94: \n95: ### Workstream A - Refresh Atomicity\n96: \n97: - Add a deterministic concurrency test for `refreshCanonicalManifest`.\n98: - Choose lock, compare-and-swap, or equivalent serialized replacement semantics.\n99: - Preserve the existing fail-closed compile-error and manifest-validation behavior.\n100: \n101: ### Workstream B - Completion Evidence Reconciliation\n102: \n103: - Align `spec.md`, `plan.md`, `tasks.md`, `checklist.md`, `decision-record.md`, `implementation-summary.md`, and `handover.md`.\n104: - Mark completed tasks with evidence and separately record unresolved acceptance follow-ups.\n105: - Obtain or explicitly record the required operator disposition for remaining P1 rows and sign-off.\n106: \n107: ### Workstream C - Documentation and Cohort Maintenance\n108: \n109: - Correct the SD-015 limitation and follow-up.\n110: - Establish one canonical default-on cohort or a generated synchronization check covering runtime, authored, promoted, and advisor surfaces.\n111: \n112: ## 5. Spec Seed\n113: \n114: - Add a requirement that concurrent manifest refreshes cannot publish a stale generation or silently lose a policy update.\n115: - Add acceptance evidence for refresh serialization/compare-and-swap and concurrent execution.\n116: - Define packet completion as separate from implementation shipment, with explicit P1 deferral and operator sign-off semantics.\n117: \n118: ## 6. Plan Seed\n119: \n120: - **T1:** Reproduce the refresh race with concurrent CLI invocations.\n121: - **T2:** Implement and test serialized or compare-and-swap refresh publication.\n122: - **T3:** Re-run manifest and fleet regression suites.\n123: - **T4:** Reconcile packet lifecycle metadata and checklist evidence.\n124: - **T5:** Replace duplicated cohort literals with generated or preflight-validated sources.\n125: - **T6:** Correct the stale SD-015 follow-up and rerun strict packet validation.\n126: \n127: ## 7. Traceability Status\n128: \n129: | Protocol | Status | Evidence |\n130: |---|---|---|\n131: | `spec_code` | partial | Runtime delivery is supported, but completion metadata conflicts with required packet state. |\n132: | `checklist_evidence` | fail | Required unchecked rows and blank operator sign-off coexist with `complete`. |\n133: | `feature_catalog_code` | notApplicable | No catalog mutation was evaluated in this detached lineage. |\n134: | `playbook_capability` | partial | Parity and adversarial tests exist; the SD-015 follow-up text is stale. |\n135: | `AC_COVERAGE` | advisory-shortfall | Level-3 packet lifecycle is active; exact covered/total counts are UNKNOWN, with open P1 evidence rows and sign-off. |\n136: \n137: The resource map was absent at lineage initialization, so the conditional resource-map coverage gate was skipped. Synthesis still emitted `resource-map.md`; it contains zero automatically extracted references because the delta records did not identify implementation target entries.\n138: \n139: ## 8. Deferred Items\n140: \n141: - Full seven-hub LUNA-HIGH acceptance sweep remains a separate follow-up recorded by the packet.\n142: - The operator-gated merge to v4 remains out of scope.\n143: - F003 and F004 are non-blocking after the P1 workstreams are dispositioned.\n144: \n145: ## Dimension Expansion Map\n146: \n147: - Correctness: covered in iterations 1, 2, 6, 7, 8, 9, and 10.\n148: - Security: covered in iterations 3, 7, and 8; no new security finding.\n149: - Traceability: covered in iteration 4 and revisited in iteration 9.\n150: - Maintainability: covered in iteration 5.\n151: - Remaining frontier: remediation of F001/F002 and canonical packet-state reconciliation.\n152: \n153: ## 9. Search Ledger\n154: \n155: - Search debt: none.\n156: - Candidate coverage: no unresolved search candidates recorded.\n157: - Ruled-out directions: path traversal, symlink escape, invalid-flag enablement, missing SD-015 tests, and parity false-pass leakage were directly checked and not confirmed.\n158: - Clean search proof: ten iterations completed; no new findings after iteration 5.\n159: \n160: ## 10. Audit Appendix\n161: \n162: - **Lineage:** `fanout-luna-xhigh-1784691838667-iv78vk`\n163: - **Executor:** `cli-opencode`, `openai/gpt-5.6-luna-fast`, `xhigh`\n164: - **Stop reason:** `maxIterationsReached`\n165: - **Release readiness:** `release-blocking` while active P1 findings remain\n166: - **Reducer:** `openFindingsCount=4`, `resolvedFindingsCount=1`, `convergenceScore=1`, `corruptionCount=0`\n167: - **Iteration verification:** iterations 1-10 each passed `verify-iteration.cjs`\n168: - **State integrity:** JSONL parsed cleanly under the reducer; canonical finding records carry content hashes for deduplication\n169: - **Core protocols:** `spec_code`, `checklist_evidence`\n170: - **Overlay protocols:** `feature_catalog_code` not applicable; `playbook_capability` partial\n171: - **Resolved artifact:** `SUMMARY-P1-001` was a reducer-only summary artifact from iteration 2 and was explicitly resolved in iteration 3\n172: - **User boundary honored:** all writes remained inside the `luna-xhigh` lineage directory; no graph/database or canonical packet files were modified\n173: \n174: ## Cross-Reference Appendix\n175: \n176: ### Core Protocols\n177: \n178: - `spec_code`: implementation evidence confirmed; lifecycle contradiction remains F002.\n179: - `checklist_evidence`: failed for unconditional completion because open P1 rows and sign-off remain.\n180: \n181: ### Overlay Protocols\n182: \n183: - `feature_catalog_code`: not applicable to this lineage's review scope.\n184: - `playbook_capability`: parity and negative-path tests are present; stale SD-015 documentation remains F003.\n\n(End of file - total 184 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review Report: Compiled Coverage Buildout\"\ndescription: \"Final conditional review for the detached luna-xhigh lineage.\"\nsessionId: \"fanout-luna-xhigh-1784691838667-iv78vk\"\nverdict: \"CONDITIONAL\"\n---\n\n# Deep Review Report\n\n## 1. Executive Summary\n\n- **Verdict:** CONDITIONAL\n- **Active findings:** 0 P0, 2 P1, 2 P2\n- **Resolved findings:** 1 reducer-only summary artifact\n- **Iterations:** 10/10\n- **Convergence:** 1.00\n- **Search debt:** none\n- **Corruption:** none\n- **Scope:** compiled-routing manifest refresh, resolver/cohort behavior, parity and sync controls, packet completion evidence, and regression boundaries\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0089-sk-doc-default-routing-cutover/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/013-compiled-coverage-buildout/review/lineages/luna-xhigh/review-report.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review Report: Compiled Coverage Buildout\"\ndescription: \"Final conditional review for the detached luna-xhigh lineage.\"\nsessionId: \"fanout-luna-xhigh-1784691838667-iv78vk\"\nverdict: \"CONDITIONAL\"\n---\n\n# Deep Review Report\n\n## 1. Executive Summary\n\n- **Verdict:** CONDITIONAL\n- **Active findings:** 0 P0, 2 P1, 2 P2\n- **Resolved findings:** 1 reducer-only summary artifact\n- **Iterations:** 10/10\n- **Convergence:** 1.00\n- **Search debt:** none\n- **Corruption:** none\n- **Scope:** compiled-routing manifest refresh, resolver/cohort behavior, parity and sync controls, packet completion evidence, and regression boundaries\n\nThe runtime surfaces are substantially fail-closed and the seven-hub default-on claims have broad parity evidence. The review does not issue PASS because the refresh path lacks concurrency protection and the packet's completion metadata contradicts its own required evidence protocol.\n\n## 2. Planning Trigger\n\n`/speckit:plan` is required for the two active P1 remediation workstreams. The P2 items can be handled as documentation and maintenance follow-ups.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"triggered\": true,\n  \"verdict\": \"CONDITIONAL\",\n  \"hasAdvisories\": true,\n  \"activeFindings\": [\n    {\"id\":\"F001\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"title\":\"Concurrent refreshes can lose a generation/policy update\",\"file\":\".opencode/bin/lib/compiled-route-manifest.cjs\",\"line\":588},\n    {\"id\":\"F002\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"title\":\"Completion status conflicts with required packet gates\",\"file\":\".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/013-compiled-coverage-buildout/checklist.md\",\"line\":58},\n    {\"id\":\"F003\",\"severity\":\"P2\",\"title\":\"SD-015 limitation and follow-up are stale\",\"file\":\".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/013-compiled-coverage-buildout/implementation-summary.md\",\"line\":208},\n    {\"id\":\"F004\",\"severity\":\"P2\",\"title\":\"Default-on cohort is maintained in multiple independently edited sources\",\"file\":\".opencode/bin/lib/compiled-routing/011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs\",\"line\":34}\n  ],\n  \"remediationWorkstreams\": [\n    \"Serialize or compare-and-swap refresh writes and add a concurrent-refresh regression test.\",\n    \"Reconcile packet statuses, task/checklist completion, P1 deferrals, and operator sign-off.\",\n    \"Mark the SD-015 follow-up resolved with its existing test evidence.\",\n    \"Generate or gate all default-on cohort copies from one canonical source.\"\n  ],\n  \"specSeed\": [\n    \"Document refresh concurrency semantics and the accepted rollback/locking behavior.\",\n    \"Reconcile the packet's completion contract with remaining unchecked evidence.\"\n  ],\n  \"planSeed\": [\n    \"Add a refresh race test using two concurrent refresh processes.\",\n    \"Choose and implement a lock or compare-and-swap protocol.\",\n    \"Synchronize plan.md, tasks.md, decision-record.md, checklist.md, and sign-off.\"\n  ],\n  \"findingClasses\": [\"class-of-bug\",\"matrix/evidence\",\"instance-only\",\"synchronization-risk\"],\n  \"affectedSurfacesSeed\": [\"canonical manifest refresh CLI\",\"activation manifest state\",\"packet completion metadata\",\"runtime/advisor cohort copies\"],\n  \"fixCompletenessRequired\": true\n}\n```\n\n## 3. Active Finding Registry\n\n### F001 - P1\n\n- **Title:** Concurrent refreshes can lose a generation/policy update\n- **Evidence:** `.opencode/bin/lib/compiled-route-manifest.cjs:564-588`; `.opencode/bin/tests/compiled-route-manifest.test.cjs:457-472`\n- **Impact:** Two valid refreshes can read the same generation and later overwrite each other's policy state. The concurrent test covers atomic mint, not refresh.\n- **Recommendation:** Serialize refreshes or use compare-and-swap on generation/hash, then add a concurrent refresh regression test.\n- **Disposition:** Active, confirmed across iterations 1-10.\n\n### F002 - P1\n\n- **Title:** Completion status conflicts with required packet gates\n- **Evidence:** `checklist.md:52-58,92,123-124,197-208`; `plan.md:11,77-82`; `tasks.md:10-20,114-121`; `decision-record.md:11-18`\n- **Impact:** The packet claims complete while required P1 rows, planned metadata, stale blockers, and formal operator sign-off remain unresolved.\n- **Recommendation:** Reconcile all lifecycle metadata and checklist/task state, or record explicit operator-approved deferrals before claiming complete.\n- **Disposition:** Active, confirmed across iterations 4-10.\n\n### F003 - P2\n\n- **Title:** SD-015 limitation and follow-up are stale\n- **Evidence:** `implementation-summary.md:204-220`; `compiled-routing-parity.vitest.ts:468-537`\n- **Impact:** The packet understates its regression coverage and leaves an inaccurate follow-up open.\n- **Recommendation:** Mark the limitation resolved and cite the positive and adversarial SD-015 tests.\n- **Disposition:** Active documentation drift.\n\n### F004 - P2\n\n- **Title:** Default-on cohort is maintained in multiple independently edited sources\n- **Evidence:** promoted resolver `resolve.cjs:29-42`; authored resolver twin; `compiled-routing-flag.ts:24-40`; `compiled-routing-foundation.vitest.ts:70-74`\n- **Impact:** A future cohort change can update one source while leaving another stale. Current tests detect divergence after the fact.\n- **Recommendation:** Generate all cohort consumers from one canonical source or add a pre-packaging generation gate.\n- **Disposition:** Active maintainability advisory.\n\n## 4. Remediation Workstreams\n\n### Workstream A - Refresh Atomicity\n\n- Add a deterministic concurrency test for `refreshCanonicalManifest`.\n- Choose lock, compare-and-swap, or equivalent serialized replacement semantics.\n- Preserve the existing fail-closed compile-error and manifest-validation behavior.\n\n### Workstream B - Completion Evidence Reconciliation\n\n- Align `spec.md`, `plan.md`, `tasks.md`, `checklist.md`, `decision-record.md`, `implementation-summary.md`, and `handover.md`.\n- Mark completed tasks with evidence and separately record unresolved acceptance follow-ups.\n- Obtain or explicitly record the required operator disposition for remaining P1 rows and sign-off.\n\n### Workstream C - Documentation and Cohort Maintenance\n\n- Correct the SD-015 limitation and follow-up.\n- Establish one canonical default-on cohort or a generated synchronization check covering runtime, authored, promoted, and advisor surfaces.\n\n## 5. Spec Seed\n\n- Add a requirement that concurrent manifest refreshes cannot publish a stale generation or silently lose a policy update.\n- Add acceptance evidence for refresh serialization/compare-and-swap and concurrent execution.\n- Define packet completion as separate from implementation shipment, with explicit P1 deferral and operator sign-off semantics.\n\n## 6. Plan Seed\n\n- **T1:** Reproduce the refresh race with concurrent CLI invocations.\n- **T2:** Implement and test serialized or compare-and-swap refresh publication.\n- **T3:** Re-run manifest and fleet regression suites.\n- **T4:** Reconcile packet lifecycle metadata and checklist evidence.\n- **T5:** Replace duplicated cohort literals with generated or preflight-validated sources.\n- **T6:** Correct the stale SD-015 follow-up and rerun strict packet validation.\n\n## 7. Traceability Status\n\n| Protocol | Status | Evidence |\n|---|---|---|\n| `spec_code` | partial | Runtime delivery is supported, but completion metadata conflicts with required packet state. |\n| `checklist_evidence` | fail | Required unchecked rows and blank operator sign-off coexist with `complete`. |\n| `feature_catalog_code` | notApplicable | No catalog mutation was evaluated in this detached lineage. |\n| `playbook_capability` | partial | Parity and adversarial tests exist; the SD-015 follow-up text is stale. |\n| `AC_COVERAGE` | advisory-shortfall | Level-3 packet lifecycle is active; exact covered/total counts are UNKNOWN, with open P1 evidence rows and sign-off. |\n\nThe resource map was absent at lineage initialization, so the conditional resource-map coverage gate was skipped. Synthesis still emitted `resource-map.md`; it contains zero automatically extracted references because the delta records did not identify implementation target entries.\n\n## 8. Deferred Items\n\n- Full seven-hub LUNA-HIGH acceptance sweep remains a separate follow-up recorded by the packet.\n- The operator-gated merge to v4 remains out of scope.\n- F003 and F004 are non-blocking after the P1 workstreams are dispositioned.\n\n## Dimension Expansion Map\n\n- Correctness: covered in iterations 1, 2, 6, 7, 8, 9, and 10.\n- Security: covered in iterations 3, 7, and 8; no new security finding.\n- Traceability: covered in iteration 4 and revisited in iteration 9.\n- Maintainability: covered in iteration 5.\n- Remaining frontier: remediation of F001/F002 and canonical packet-state reconciliation.\n\n## 9. Search Ledger\n\n- Search debt: none.\n- Candidate coverage: no unresolved search candidates recorded.\n- Ruled-out directions: path traversal, symlink escape, invalid-flag enablement, missing SD-015 tests, and parity false-pass leakage were directly checked and not confirmed.\n- Clean search proof: ten iterations completed; no new findings after iteration 5.\n\n## 10. Audit Appendix\n\n- **Lineage:** `fanout-luna-xhigh-1784691838667-iv78vk`\n- **Executor:** `cli-opencode`, `openai/gpt-5.6-luna-fast`, `xhigh`\n- **Stop reason:** `maxIterationsReached`\n- **Release readiness:** `release-blocking` while active P1 findings remain\n- **Reducer:** `openFindingsCount=4`, `resolvedFindingsCount=1`, `convergenceScore=1`, `corruptionCount=0`\n- **Iteration verification:** iterations 1-10 each passed `verify-iteration.cjs`\n- **State integrity:** JSONL parsed cleanly under the reducer; canonical finding records carry content hashes for deduplication\n- **Core protocols:** `spec_code`, `checklist_evidence`\n- **Overlay protocols:** `feature_catalog_code` not applicable; `playbook_capability` partial\n- **Resolved artifact:** `SUMMARY-P1-001` was a reducer-only summary artifact from iteration 2 and was explicitly resolved in iteration 3\n- **User boundary honored:** all writes remained inside the `luna-xhigh` lineage directory; no graph/database or canonical packet files were modified\n\n## Cross-Reference Appendix\n\n### Core Protocols\n\n- `spec_code`: implementation evidence confirmed; lifecycle contradiction remains F002.\n- `checklist_evidence`: failed for unconditional completion because open P1 rows and sign-off remain.\n\n### Overlay Protocols\n\n- `feature_catalog_code`: not applicable to this lineage's review scope.\n- `playbook_capability`: parity and negative-path tests are present; stale SD-015 documentation remains F003.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":184,"totalLines":184,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/015-routing-coverage-activation-verification/013-compiled-coverage-buildout/review/lineages/luna-xhigh/review-report.md","time":{"start":1784693796774,"end":1784693796781}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_01c050d7c5b749f0016a6044249db48191a7df1df09e9d25e2"}},"id":"prt_f880a2f9e001v8t7SX0Dt6S7yt","sessionID":"ses_07813ae6bffeXSfNUcMKmjadEz","messageID":"msg_f880a0455001G8vqwE94m2Url2"}}
